title: california yogurt soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except parsley and dill.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Garnish with parsley and dill just before serving.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Scald milk in double boiler.
Combine sugar, salt, flour and cornstarch in saucepan.
Pour in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly and thick.
Cook for 15 minutes in double boiler.
Beat egg yolks, stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add butter; cool. Stir in 1/3 mixture, then 1/2 bananas, 1/3 mixture, 1/2 bananas, remaining mixture.
Add meringue.

title: reese's peanut butter candy
directions: Melt oleo; add peanut butter.
Mix with dry ingredients and put into pan (11 x 15-inch) until smooth.
Melt chocolate bits and
spread
over
peanut
butter
mixture.
May
set in refrigerator
for
about
an hour.	Remove and let set at room temperature before cutting.

title: mayhaw shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Wrap a half a bacon slice around shrimp and secure with toothpick.
Mix together mayhaw jelly, chili sauce, butter and garlic powder.
Pour sauce over shrimp and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
The next day, place shrimp on broiler rack and broil shrimp for five minutes on each side or until bacon is browned.
Serve warm.

title: yakisoba(main dish)
directions: Cut pork, carrot, onions and cabbage into narrow strips. Sprinkle or rinse water over the noodles.
Sprinkle sesame oil over noodles.
Fry pork in tablespoon of oil.
When the color of pork changes, add carrots and 2 minutes later, add onions and cabbage. When vegetables become tender, add 3 tablespoons oil and 2 tablespoons sesame oil.
Put noodles in and mix.
Add salt.
Pour soy sauce along the edge of pan.
Add seasoning and pepper. Decorate the served noodles, placing narrow strip of red ginger on the top and center.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Mix soup and water. Add wine. Stir in with rice and pork chops.
Put in buttered casserole. Spread soup mix on top. Sprinkle with slivered almonds and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: giblet gravy(low-fat)
directions: Dissolve the cornstarch in cool broth and add fat to giblets. Stir until gravy thickens and becomes a smooth texture.
A small saucepan or double boiler is satisfactory.
Allow the gravy to bubble in the center of the pan, about 3 minutes cooking time. Serve over celery dressing.

title: tom xao mien(vietnamese shrimp and vermicelli)
directions: Soak bean thread in warm water, about 15 minutes.
Drain water.
Cut bean thread to about 6 inches long.
Clean and devein shrimp.
Clean and slice celery, carrots and spring onion.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Prick pastry shell and bake 12 minutes. Remove shell and reduce temperature to 375°.
In a large bowl, mix cheeses, sausage and onion.
In a smaller bowl, beat eggs with cream.
Combine ingredients and pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt.
In a saucepan, combine water and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and pour over flour mixture.
In another bowl, mix eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture, blending well.
Pour into a greased 10 1/2 x 12 1/2-inch jelly roll pan or 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Microwave 2 1/4 minutes on High.
Stir once.
Remove from oven.
Add vanilla; mix until smooth.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Stir together sweetened condensed milk, pineapple and whipped topping. Put into pie crusts.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.

title: brown sugar crisps
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Beat sugars, butter, egg, vanilla, allspice and cinnamon until smoothe and creamy. Stir in baking mix and nuts. Drop by slightly rounded teaspoons, about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until light brown, 12 to 15 minutes. Immediately remove from cookie sheet. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: venison jelly
directions: Follow directions on Sure-Jell recipes for cooking jelly.

title: battered fried mushrooms
directions: Clean and remove end of stem from mushrooms.
Mix all ingredients, except oil and mushrooms.
Beat batter well.
Heat oil in frying pan at 375°.
Coat mushrooms with batter and slip into hot oil.
When brown on one side, turn.
Drain on paper towels; serve hot.

title: very easy veggie a.b.c. soup
directions: In soup pot, bring water to a boil.
Stir in all ingredients. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream sugar, salt and butter thoroughly in small mixing bowl. Add vanilla.
Gradually stir flour into creamed ingredients.
Work nuts into dough.
Chill well before baking.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 10 to 12 minutes, until set but not brown.
Roll in 10x sugar immediately.
Cool on rack.
Roll in sugar again after they are cold.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 inch x 13 inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes. Best with cream cheese icing.

title: chocolate easter eggs
directions: In a saucepan, combine the pudding mixes, butter and milk. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil. Cook and stir 1-2 minutes longer or until thickened. Remove from heat; stir in sugar and peanut butter. Cool slightly. Shape 1/2 cupfuls into egg shapes. Place on a waxed paper-lined baking sheet; refrigerate until set.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Put margarine and cocoa in skillet.
Mix and melt over a low heat.
Beat eggs lightly in a bowl and add sugar, cocoa, butter mixture, flour, nuts, salt and vanilla. Bake at 350° in a well greased and floured 10 x 14 x 2-inch pan for 35 minutes.
Top with miniature marshmallows while still hot and pour on icing.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time; beat well.
Add crushed graham crackers, then milk.
Mix well.
Add other ingredients, mixing well.
Bake in 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and add reserved orange liquid; stir in sherbet and chill until thickened.
Add orange pieces and chill until congealed; cut into squares.
To serve, place Orange Salad squares on lettuce leaves in individual salad plates; top each with a spoonful of Cool Whip and garnish with a mint leaf.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: german potato soup(low-fat)
directions: Combine ingredients in large saucepan.
Cover and simmer until potatoes and carrots are very tender, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fruit mix
directions: Cook pudding mix with pineapple juice until clear.
Cool.
Mix with cherries, pineapple and oranges.
Last, add sliced bananas (any amount you want).

title: mexican chip dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in salsa.
Spread mixture into a casserole dish.
Spread sour cream on top of beef mixture. Sprinkle on cheese.
Top with olives.
Heat in microwave until cheese is melted and serve with tortilla chips.

title: fireside chocolate
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate melts and mixture is hot.
Remove from heat.
Remove and discard cinnamon sticks. Beat mixture at high speed with an electric mixer 1 to 2 minutes. Pour into mugs.
If desired, dollop with whipped cream and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
4 1/2 cups.

title: st. patrick's day punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ice cubes; mix well in punch bowl.
Add ice cubes just before serving.

title: fruit kugel *
directions: Combine pineapple, apples, oil, sugar and matzo meal.
Mix well.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Mix well.
Add prunes and apricots. Beat egg whites into peaks.
Fold into batter.
Pour into well-greased two-quart baking dish and bake for one hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: "you won't know it's vegetarian lasagna"
directions: In 2 gallon kettle, bring 6 quarts salted water to rapid boil. Add 1 tablespoon olive oil and lasagna noodles, 2 or 3 at a time. Cook 8 to 10 minutes; drain.
Return to kettle with warm water to prevent sticking.

title: heath bar dessert
directions: Crush vanilla wafers with rolling pin or food processor. Mix with melted butter. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan, reserving some for garnish. Mix the instant pudding with milk, then add the softened ice cream and blend together. Pour over crust mixture. Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle Heath bars on top along with remaining crust mix. Refrigerate 2 hours. (Ice cream should be soft but not completely melted.)

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions coarsely.
Mix vinegar, sugar and salt.
Add to peppers and onions.
Bring to a boil and cook 20 minutes.
Seal in hot, sterilized jars.

title: blue cheese dressing(does snappy things to green salad)
directions: Put ingredients in bottle or jar.
Cover and shake well.
Shake again just before using.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: school district peanut butter brownies
directions: Mix butter and peanut butter.
Add corn syrup.
Add sugar and salt.
Mix 10 minutes (stay with mixer).
Add eggs and then flour. Bake at 350°
about 25 minutes in jelly roll pan.
Ice with chocolate peanut butter frosting.

title: frosted triple orange dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in thawed orange juice.
Add in undrained pineapple.
Chill until partially set (the consistency of unbeaten egg whites).
Fold in oranges and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until almost firm.

title: noodle-meat casserole
directions: Boil and drain noodles.
Mix with chopped eggs.
Add remaining ingredients; mix.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs and half and half.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish, layer croutons, then sausage, then cheese.
Pour egg and milk mixture over these ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
The next morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: spaghetti dinner
directions: Melt margarine or butter in a heavy skillet and saute onion, bell pepper and celery.
Add ground beef and stir until beef loses its redness.
Add tomatoes, ketchup, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, for about one hour.
Additional seasonings may be added if desired:
such as celery seed, chili powder or oregano.
Use salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.
Serves 4.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Season pork chops and flour; brown on both sides, then put in baking dish.
Mix ketchup, water and brown sugar.
Pour over chops. Slice lemon and lay on top of pork chops.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Place meat, eggs, bread crumbs, milk, soup mix, salt, pepper, garlic salt and parsley into a large bowl.
Using your hands, mix mixture well.
Shape into loaf and place in a large rectangular baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Drain fat.
Cover with spaghetti sauce and continue baking for additional 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bilon(philippines chow mein)
directions: Fry garlic until it's brown;
add the onion and chicken. When the meat is done, add the rest of the ingredients.
Remove from the skillet or pan.
Put 2 cups of water to the remaining juice in the pan and add soy sauce and pepper to taste.
Let it boil, then put the Bihon until it's cooked.
Mix them with the vegetables and serve.
Garnish with sliced boiled eggs and green onions.
Serves 4.

title: grecian style beef(48 servings)
directions: Defrost spinach; drain.
Cook ground beef, onion and garlic until just browned.
Pour off drippings.
Add tomato paste, salt and cinnamon to meat.
Cook until heated through.
Combine butter, spinach and lemon juice; mix well.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Add 3 cups cheese to macaroni; mix well.
Spray three 20 x 12 x 2-inch pans with Pam.
Layer, starting with 2-quart macaroni mixture, then 3 1/2 cups spinach mixture, 2 1/4-quart meat and 1 quart macaroni mixture.
Sprinkle each with 1 1/3 grated cheese.
Beat eggs; add flour, milk, salt, pepper and nutmeg; mix well.
Pour 1/3 egg mixture over each pan.
Cover tightly; bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: mexican cake
directions: In one bowl, mix sugar, eggs and soda powder.
In another bowl, mix pineapple, flour and nuts.
Mix together in long pan.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.

title: scallopini burgers
directions: Mix veal with following 5 ingredients.
Form meat into 6 patties.
Brown in pan. Pour off fat.
Mix tomato sauce in bowl with mushrooms, wine and seasonings.
Pour sauce over drained meat patties in pan and simmer with cover on for about 25 to 30 minutes.
May throw over noodles.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Add apples and mix well.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Fold in nuts and flavoring and blend well.
Bake in preheated 350° oven in Bundt pan for 1 hour 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Can also be baked in 9 x 12-inch pan for 45 minutes.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add 2 cans drained vegetables, salt and pepper.
Remove from stove and put in casserole dish. Cover ground beef mixture with mashed potatoes.
Pour tomato sauce over top.
Bake at 350° until heated through (30 to 40 minutes).

title: good potato soup
directions: Boil the potatoes and carrots in water and chicken broth. When done set aside but leave it in the pot. In a skillet melt margarine, add celery and onion and cook until tender. Add flour and cook a few minutes until creamy. Add one cup of potato broth, milk and half and half. Add this to potatoes and carrots and cook 10 to 15 minutes longer on medium heat.

title: dolma(stuffed grape leaves)
directions: Combine rice, lamb (or beef), salt, spice, pepper, raisins (optional), garlic, half the tomato sauce and 1 tablespoon vegetable oil.
Mix by hand well; set aside.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook onions in margarine.
Add milk and cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: one dish dinner
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef and drain fat.
Cut up tomatoes and add along with juice to beef.
Add beans, water and noodles magic.
Bring mixture to a simmer, cover and cook 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken and chop up in small pieces.
Put layer of chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour cream of chicken soup over chicken.
Add another layer of chicken.
Pour the rest of the cream of chicken soup over this.
Add dressing (Pepperidge Farm) on top.
Pour broth from chicken over dressing until very moist. Do not stir.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: some like it hot; some like it cold!
directions: Hot:
Mix water, coffee and sweetener.
Add milk.
Add Kahlua. Top with whipped cream.

title: mimi's pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Add molasses and pumpkin.
Combine flour with salt, soda and spices.
Add water.
Beat until smooth. Pour into 3 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix grated cheese, onion, mayonnaise and pecans; shape into ring.* Chill and serve on Ritz crackers with preserves.
(Use hand grater, blender makes lumpy.)

title: beef with broccoli
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat in hot oil, cook beef and garlic until beef is browned.
Add onion.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling; add broccoli.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over rice or noodles.
(Recipe may be doubled.)
Cooking time:
10 to 15 minutes.
Preparation time:
20 minutes.

title: christmas ornaments
directions: You will need cookie cutters, a small paintbrush, paints, glitter and ribbon.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix yeast, flour and sugar.
Add water, oil and egg. Mix well and put in refrigerator.
You do not have to let these rise before baking.
Pour batter into greased muffin tins or pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Combine carrots and water in a 2 1/2-quart casserole. Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes or until carrots are tender-crisp, stirring twice.
Combine cooled and drained carrots with remaining ingredients.
Marinate refrigerated overnight. Drain for serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: hamburger-corn bake
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion in skillet.
Add the cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup, corn and sour cream.
Mix well.
Cook the noodles and drain.
Add to hamburger mixture.
Also add 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Melt the butter and mix in the soft bread crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: casserole
directions: Let the meat boil in a covered pot until done.
Remove from bone and cut in small pieces.
Put in casserole baking container. Add celery, bell pepper and butter.
Pour over the mixture 1 can of chicken noodle soup.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
A serving for 4 or more.

title: hamburger and macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni according to the package directions.
Set aside. In a skillet, saute the onion and bell pepper in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add meat and brown.
Pour off excess fat.
Add garlic salt, tomato soup and cubed Velveeta cheese until melted.
Blend in the cooked macaroni and serve.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.
Delicious on Ritz crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook
chicken.
Remove
chicken
from bone and place in bottom of casserole.
Mix other ingredients and add to casserole. Crumble
crackers
on
top.
Melt oleo and drizzle over crackers. Top with poppy seed.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix with 1/2 cup milk and butter.
Pour half of batter into greased 11 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 5 to 6 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Stir over medium heat, the marshmallows, milk, chocolate chips and salt until mixture has melted and is thick.
Remove from heat and cool thoroughly.
Line bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan with wafers.
Crumble wafers to fill spaces.
Spoon half of ice cream over wafers.
Cover with half of the sauce.
Repeat again. Sprinkle nuts over top, wrap in foil and place in freezer until ready to serve.

title: kara's cauliflower parmesan
directions: Cut cauliflower into small pieces and boil until tender. Drain cauliflower.
Melt butter and pour over cauliflower. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs to coat cauliflower. Add salt and pepper on top.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and fruit cocktail with juice together.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together butter, brown sugar and chopped nuts.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Prepare whipped topping with milk, as directed on package.
Fold topping into peanut butter mixture.
Spoon into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts and chill several hours before serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Crumble 1/3 of Doritos in bottom of baking dish.
Brown meat and onion together.
Drain.
Add beans, soup and taco sauce.
Heat until warm.
Spoon over chips.
Top with remaining crumbled Doritos.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
In last 10 minutes, add shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: summery congealed salad
directions: Make Jell-O by directions in a mold or large casserole dish. Chill in refrigerator until it is the consistency of raw egg whites.
Add pineapple, carrots and pecans and mix evenly.
Chill until firm.
This recipe can be doubled if you have a large mold.

title: vivons kentucky pudding pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add 4 cups of flour alternately with stewed apples.
Dredge raisins and nuts with remaining 1/2 cup flour.
Add spices.
Fold in cherries and pineapple.
Add raisins and nuts last.
Line greased tube pan with wax paper.
Bake 2 hours at 250°.
Makes 2 large cakes.
Halve recipe for one.
Freezes nicely.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in butter.
Remove.
Add flour to butter and cook until dark brown.
Add tomatoes, sauteed onions and bell pepper.
Simmer.

title: sausage bread
directions: Thaw loaf and roll out.
Brown sausage; spread on dough.
Put shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
If you like, put hot sauce on top of cheese.
Roll like you would for cinnamon rolls and bake on cookie sheet at 375° until bread is cooked thoroughly.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Saute meat in butter.
Drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients except onion rings.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crumbled onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 4.

title: lentil soup
directions: Cook lentils in broth with salt and pepper for 1 1/2 hours. Add other ingredients and cook for 30 to 45 minutes more until tender.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix by hand cream cheese and butter, blend in egg yolk and vanilla. Add dry cake mix 1/3 at a time, mixing after each addition. Cover and chill 30 minutes or overnight. Heat oven to 375°. Roll onto teaspoon and put on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until starting to brown. Cool slightly before removing from pan. Makes 6 dozen small cookies. Great for showers!

title: bavarian meat balls and pears
directions: Drain pears; reserve syrup for later.
Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, onions, parsley, egg, milk, salt, pepper and allspice.
Mix well and shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.

title: oven omelet
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan to coat bottom.
Beat eggs, sour cream, milk and salt together until smooth.
Pour into dish and sprinkle green onion on top.
Bake 30 minutes or until eggs set.
Test with knife blade.
Cut in squares. Serves 12.

title: old-fashioned skillet corn bread
directions: Melt butter or margarine in heavy iron skillet in oven while it's being preheated to 350°.
Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in mixing bowl.
In separate bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk and 2 tablespoons melted margarine from skillet. Quickly stir milk into cornmeal mixture.
Pour batter into remaining margarine in hot skillet.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Goes great with chili!
Can also be done in round cake pan.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Add vinegar, water, sugar and salt.
This is enough for 1 1/2 pounds shredded lettuce or celery and cabbage or shredded cabbage.

title: chip beef dip
directions: Mix ingredients in ovenware bowl; sprinkle with walnuts and bake for 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: tarragon pickles
directions: Drain sour pickles; slice.
Layer pickles in a large mixing bowl or crock with equal amounts of sugar (no juice).
Place pickling spice, garlic and tarragon vinegar on top.
Weigh down with a plate.
Refrigerate for 3 days, stirring thoroughly, once a day (first time after 25 hours).
At end of 3 or 4 days, put in clean jars (after removing garlic).

title: maple syrup barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Cool.
Pour mixture into container of an electric blender; process until smooth.
Remove 1 cup for basting and brush sauce over meat the last 30 minutes of cooking time.
(Discard any remaining basting sauce.)
Serve meat with remaining sauce.
Yield:
3 1/2 cups.

title: green grape salad
directions: Make a white sauce of the butter, flour and milk.
Add the marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Pour sauce over the remaining ingredients. Chill before serving.

title: butter pecan squares
directions: Mix together; pour into well greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut while warm in small pieces as it is very rich.

title: salmon fritters
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid; flake.
Add milk to salmon liquid to make 1/2 cup.
Add this to baking mix with egg and lemon juice.
Blend in salmon, vegetables, salt and pepper.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into hot oil in deep fryer.
Fry for about 3 minutes or until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towel.

title: wonderful meatballs and spaghetti sauce
directions: Put ground beef in a large bowl; salt and pepper.
Add the white, wet bread and sprinkle on the Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning.
Add egg and mix well and make quarter size balls (steam thoroughly) and put into the sauce which is cooking at same time.
Should be steamed enough to have no pink in them before sauced.

title: turkey and artichoke casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In skillet, saute green pepper and onions in margarine until crisp-tender.
Add soup, half and half and sherry; mix well.
In a large bowl, combine soup mixture, turkey, artichokes, bacon, carrots and Mozzarella cheese.
Spread white and wild rice evenly over bottom of prepared pan.
Top rice with turkey mixture; spread evenly.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; uncover.
Bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes or until casserole is thoroughly heated.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: krinkle's hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and fold into a greased casserole pan.
Top with grated cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375° or until heated through.
This can also be made with leftover Thanksgiving turkey!

title: daffodil dip
directions: Mix well cheese and Miracle Whip.
Add parsley and finely chopped egg white.
Add rest and mix well.
Put on a serving dish and garnish with egg yolk, if wanted.
(Push egg yolk through a tea strainer over mix.)
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: victorian tea pastry
directions: Combine the butter, sugar, milk and almond extract and spread over warm pastries.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: italian gravy and meatball
directions: Place olive oil in large saucepan. Add bay leaves and hot sausage. Brown sausage until well cooked about 30 minutes. Add peeled tomatoes to the sausage. Simmer this for about 20 minutes. While simmering, add garlic powder and a little dried parsley. After you simmer, 3 to 4 cans of water to the tomatoes. When it starts to boil, lower to a medium heat and add Hunt's tomato paste. Let this cook for 3 to 4 hours on medium-low heat, just until you see a slight boil. Stir frequently so not to have it stick to the bottom of the pan.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Simmer the hamburger and drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: sweet milk griddle cakes
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Beat egg, add milk and pour slowly on first mixture.
Beat thoroughly and add butter.
Cook as sour milk griddle cakes.

title: cereal treats
directions: Spray a 9-inch square pan with Pam cooking spray. Spray the back of a large spoon with Pam. Melt margarine in large saucepan over medium heat. Add marshmallows and cook until melted, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and gently stir in cereals. Pour mixture into pan. With back of spoon, press mixture evenly in pan. Cool 30 minutes or until completely cooled. Cut into bars. Enjoy!

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla and lemon juice.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add bananas.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder together.
Add alternately with sour cream to banana mixture.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° until brown and firm (about 30 minutes).
Yummy!

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange vegetables in bottom of 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Blend soup and milk and pour over all. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until hot.

title: hot beef
directions: Combine wine, salad oil, green pepper, onion, garlic, pepper and tomato sauce to make the marinade.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: david's bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs, yolks and sugar until thick lemon color.
Add milk, vanilla, lemon rind, lemon juice, nutmeg and salt; mix well. Place bread cubes into large buttered baking dish; pour mixture over.
Let sit 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Set dish in pan of hot water; bake for 45 minutes, or until top sets and is brown. Serve hot or warm.

title: fruit salad
directions: Make lemon pudding as directed on box.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip. Add fruit cocktail and marshmallows.
Chill overnight or at least 4 hours.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients. Set aside. Sift in large mixing bowl the flour, salt, nutmeg, baking powder, baking powder and cinnamon. Combine all and bake at 350°. Can be made in loaf pan. I use soup cans or vegetable cans that I save. Flour and grease cans good. Cool. Wrap in foil or can be frozen. Makes 7 to 8 loaves, if soup cans are used.

title: mary's never fail meringue
directions: In saucepan,
combine
water,
sugar and starch.
Heat, stirring until thick
and
clear.
Remove
from heat;
stir in vanilla.
In large bowl,
whip egg whites with a pinch of salt until droopy peaks form;
continue whipping as you slowly pour in the sugar
water
mixture.
Whip
until
peaks
stand
up. Spread over warm
filling
pushing
up meringue against crust. Bake at 450° for 5 to 7 minutes or until nicely browned.
Cool on rack away
from draft.
Do not refrigerate until completely cool.

title: fat free french fries
directions: Toss frozen fries in egg whites until well coated.
Place onto a cookie sheet pan which has been coated with fat free cooking spray.
Put into oven at 400 degrees.
Keep a close watch and turn ever so often until desired browning is reached.

title: chocolate cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add the milk, Crisco and melted chocolate.
Beat vigorously by hand or at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla. Beat two minutes more.

title: cranberry nut loaf
directions: Pour juice, rind and oil in cup.
Add enough boiling water to make 3/4 cup.
Combine with well-beaten egg.
Stir in dry ingredients until damp.
Add nuts and cranberries.
Pour into pan and let set for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: In small saucepan, stir together sugar, cornstarch, salt and orange peel.
Slowly stir orange juice into sugar mixture.
Add butter.
Cook, stirring constantly, on low heat.
Place in casserole and bake 7 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: tortilla bake
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain well.
Combine all remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Simmer on stove until well mixed (20 minutes).
Layer tortillas and meat in a 13 x 9-inch pan with tortillas on the bottom, ending with meat sauce on top (like lasagna).
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° (will bubble slightly). Turn oven off and cover with cheese.
Leave in oven until cheese is melted.
Cut into 2 to 3-inch squares and serve.
Best when assembled the day before and refrigerated overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together in a bowl.
Then form into a ball and place in a saucer.
Put in refrigerator and let set up for about 1 hour.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until well blended.
Add sugar gradually; mix well. Add salt and vanilla; pour in cream and milk.
Pour into gallon freezer.
Freeze.

title: sugar-free banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix corn meal, flour, rolled oats and wheat germ.
Add other ingredients and stir well. Pour mixture into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 45 minutes or until done.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine 1/2 cup margarine, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese; mix well.
Stir in potatoes.
Spoon into greased 2 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Mix the remaining margarine and cornflakes; sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni seafood salad
directions: Cook macaroni and cool.
Stir in remaining ingredients to cooled macaroni.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.
Enjoy.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Grind celery, mango and garlic.
Saute in olive oil until brown.
Add meat.
Cook until meat is well done.
Add tomato products and seasoning.
Simmer until done.

title: thick & chewy pizza dough
directions: 1. Combine 1/4 c. of the water with yeast and sugar.
Stir to dissolve the yeast and let stand until bubbly (about 5 minutes). 2. Put flour, oil, and salt into food processor and process about 5 seconds.

Add yeast mixture to flour mixture and process about 10 seconds until blended. 3. Turn on processer and drizzle just enough of the rest of the water through the feed tube so the dough forms a ball that cleans the sides of the bowl. 4. Process so that the ball turns around about 25 times.

Put the dough ball onto a 14-inch pizza pan or large cookie sheet. 5. Cover with a bowl or plastic wrap and let stand 10 minutes. 6. Put the dough out so that it covers the pan leaving a ridge on the edges.
Spread with pizza sauce and add cheese and toppings. 7. Bake at 425° for 15-20 minutes or until crust is golden and the cheese is bubbly.

title: mixed fruit salad
directions: Drain peaches, pineapple and oranges, saving juice.
Add water to fruit juice to make 3 cups liquid. Add both boxes of pudding to the liquid in a quart dish. Cover and microwave on High until thick (3 to 4 minutes).
Cool pudding mix.
Cut pineapple and peaches into bite size pieces.
Mix with pudding mix and oranges. Just before serving, add bananas, grapes, strawberries and cherries.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside.
Cream margarine, peanut butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Slowly add dry ingredients.
When all mixed, add milk, vanilla and nuts.
Drop with a spoon onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Saute garlic in oil.
Stir in onion.
Add cabbage, salt and pepper.
Stir-fry until cabbage is tender, about 10 minutes.

title: california hurry-up meal
directions: Fry hamburger, onions and green peppers.
When almost done, put to side of pan and scramble eggs in same pan.
When done, add cooked rice.
Add soy sauce, salt and pepper to flavor.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add remaining ingredients.
Mold into small finger size rolls. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar when cool.

title: all american meat casserole
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients, then add next 5 ingredients. Meanwhile, cook noodles 5 minutes.
Drain and toss in 3 tablespoons butter.
Saute beef in 1 to 2 tablespoons butter (take off heat).
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and last 3 ingredients.
Then in casserole, put 1/2 tomato meat sauce, 1/2 noodles, cheese mixture, 1/2 noodles and 1/2 tomato meat sauce.
Can be refrigerated.
Take out of fridge 20 minutes before cooking for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons butter in a skillet.
Cook the onion, green pepper and celery for 5 minutes.
Add the rice, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Bring to the boiling point.
Simmer gently for 5 minutes. Add the cheese and serve at once.
Serves 4.

title: egg salad dip
directions: Boil eggs until hard.
Cool and peel.
Put through Foley food mill so eggs are finely ground.
Add 1/2 cup mayonnaise or enough to make smooth consistency.
Add 1/4 teaspoon salt to taste.

title: micro "baked" chicken(cooking time 15 to 20 minutes)
directions: Place chicken pieces in 9-inch square casserole dish. Sprinkle with salt and lemon pepper.
Cover with plastic wrap. Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn dish half turn after 10 minutes. Yields 4 servings.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Mix together butter, peanut butter and brown sugar; cream. Add eggs, one at a time; beat until fluffy.
Mix honey, flour, wheat germ, baking powder and soda.
Add other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 375°
for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pam's cheese cake
directions: Make or buy a 9-inch deep-dish graham cracker crust.

title: turkey quiche
directions: Mix and pour in a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: dorito delight
directions: Spread Doritos in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown hamburger, onion, salt and pepper.
Add and heat:
mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, evaporated milk and green chili peppers.
Top with cheese. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients on wax paper.
In mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients and mix well with dry ingredients.
Stir in 1 cup chopped walnuts.
Pour into two greased 8-inch baking pans. Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Use Brown Sugar Icing and decorate with Halloween candy.

title: cheesers
directions: Chop lunch meat and onion.
Shred cheese; add seasoning.
Mix well.
Dip biscuit pods in flour; stretch to a large circle.
Fill with mixture (1 large tablespoon each).
Pinch edges together to form pea pod.
Baste with beaten egg.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add to ingredients and cook over low heat until warm.
Baste chicken often when cooking.
Skin will get very crispy but will taste great.
Okay if it has a burnt look.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Melt butter or oleo and mix in the rest of the ingredients. Put half of this mixture in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Scatter over it 1
large cherry pie filling. Cover with the other half of the crumb mixture. Bake until golden, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish.
Stir and bake for 4 hours at 275°.

title: corn pone
directions: Mix everything together well; pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° until done, about 35 minutes.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
Mix all ingredients until blended.
Add enough milk to make soft dough.
Roll out on floured board and cut with biscuit cutter or may be rolled in hands.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Refrigerate unused portion.

title: dallas dip
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients. Add the salad oil, vinegar and garlic powder.

title: seafood delight(crabmeat dip)
directions: Cut seafood into thin slices.
Combine with cheese, mayonnaise, horseradish and garlic powder.
Heat in microwave for 7 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with crackers, pretzels or raw vegetables.
A delicious finger food!

title: easy chimichangas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray large baking sheet with cooking spray for 2 seconds.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Beat milk and pudding until thick. Add Cool Whip and blend well. Place a layer of graham crackers in a 9 x 12 pan. Pour half of pudding mixture over graham crackers. Top with another layer of graham crackers. Add the other half of the pudding mixture. Top with 1 more layer of graham crackers. Melt the tub of icing in the microwave 15 to 30 seconds. Pour icing over the top layer of graham crackers and spread evenly. Refrigerate until crackers have softened (overnight works well).

title: easy manicotti florentine
directions: Combine spinach, cheeses, pepper and salt until well blended. Stuff uncooked shells.
Pour 1 cup sauce plus 1/4 cup water into an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Place shells in pan; cover with remaining sauce. Cover with foil; bake until shells are tender, 45 to 50 minutes, at 375°.
Uncover; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: maryland crab imperial
directions: Make white sauce using the first 6 ingredients.
Add green pepper, Worcestershire sauce and crabmeat and pour into a casserole.
Cover with bread crumbs and bake at 450° until brown. Serves 4.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt.
In separate bowl, cream together the oil, vanilla, eggs, walnuts and apples.
Mix together both mixtures.
Put in a 9 x 11-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: black bean salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill. Serve with Scoops.

title: marshmallow applesauce dessert
directions: Mix applesauce and spices; heat.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows while cooling.
Stir until smooth.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: egg pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time.
Cream well. Add the rest of the mixture and cook at 350° until firm.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in bacon grease until tender.
Add tomato sauce, sugar and thyme.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice and oleo. Cook in microwave 2 minutes or in double boiler until thick.
When this mixture cools, fold in whipped cream, fruits and marshmallows.
Chill for 24 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix
together
all ingredients (except about 1/4 cup of stuffing
mix)
in
large
casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over
top
and bake, uncovered, at 350° until bubbly, approximately 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato log roll
directions: Grease and flour bottom and sides of a 15 x 10 x 2-inch jelly roll pan; line bottom of pan with waxed paper.

Beat eggs at high speed of electric mixer until thick and lemon colored (about 5 minutes); gradually add sugar, beating 5 additional minutes. Continue beating and gradually add sweet potato and lemon juice. Combine dry ingredients and stir into sweet potato mixture.
Pour batter into prepared pan, spreading evenly.
Sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: copper pennies
directions: Bring soup and other ingredients to a boil.
Pour over carrots and other vegetables.
This will keep for several weeks, if stored covered in the refrigerator.
Can be reheated or served cold.

title: lemon crisp
directions: Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Frost with a mix of 1 cup powdered sugar, 1 tablespoon butter and the juice and rind of 2 lemons.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine in casserole.
Mix all ingredients and pour into 10 x 10 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: savory lemon sauce
directions: Combine salad dressing and juice.
Mix well.
Serve over hot cooked asparagus or broccoli.
Makes 1 cup.

title: chocolate fondue dip
directions: Place all ingredients in a ceramic fondue pot over low heat. Stir constantly until the mixture is melted and smooth. Do not allow to bubble. Arrange an assortment of bite-sized dipping foods on a tray. Some suggestions are strawberries, bananas, apples, grapes, cherries, pound cake, marshmallows, raisins and shelled nuts. Spear with fondue forks or wooden skewers, dip swirl and enjoy!

title: ginger pork roast with prune (or apricot) stuffing(servings:  8)
directions: Turn each peeled potato on its side and cut in 1/8-inch slices, but do not cut all the way through.
Leave intact at bottom.
Place potatoes in ice water for one hour.
Pierce a hole through trimmed pork roast and push prunes (or apricots) into this hole.
Rub roast on all sides with the lemon.
Sprinkle with ginger, salt and pepper.
Place roast in shallow pan with fat side up; let meat rest on its bones.
Pour beef broth around the roast. Cover pan with foil and roast for 30 minutes at 350°.
Drain potatoes and pat dry with paper towels.
Roll in melted butter mixed with paprika.
Remove roast from oven and place potatoes around the roast in pan.
Pour paprika-butter mixture over the potatoes.
Return roast and potatoes to the oven, uncovered, and baste often with pan drippings.
Add water if needed.
Roast 1 hour and 20 minutes (175° on a meat thermometer).
Remove roast and potatoes to a heated platter and keep warm while making the gravy.

title: nana's lemon pineapple salad
directions: Put jello in 6 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Dissolve with 1 cup boiling water.
Mash cream cheese in it with fork.
Add crushed pineapple and fold in whipping cream.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix milk and margarine.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla together.
Add milk and margarine.
Add bread cubes.
Pour into greased casserole.
Place casserole into pan of water in 325° oven. Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Raisins may be added when bread cubes are added, if desired.
Pudding is done when knife inserted in middle can be removed clean.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground meat and onion.
Saute in picante sauce.
Add oregano and garlic salt.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
In a large bowl, chop lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
To this mixture, add 2 cans of pinto beans, which have been drained.
Crunch Fritos and mix together with meat mixture and add Catalina dressing.
Add to bowl of stuff and mix.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well. Better if it sets overnight.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Arrange tomato slices on a baking sheet coated with butter flavored vegetable cooking spray. Brush dressing on each slice. Combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of crumb mixture on each tomato slice. Spray each slice with cooking spray. Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Yields 4 servings with 81 calories per 2 slice serving.

title: asparagus appetizer
directions: Cut crust off bread and flatten with palm.
Spread with cream cheese.
Lay one asparagus tip at one end and roll it up in the bread.
Secure with toothpick and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Can be cut in half.

title: sweet-sour franks
directions: In a large saucepan, combine brown sugar, flour, pineapple juice, vinegar, dry mustard and soy sauce.
Mix well. Bring to a boil.
Add hot dogs.
Stir to cover hot dogs with sauce.
Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, until hot dogs are heated through.
Serve in a chafing dish with wooden picks.

title: unbaked peanut butter bars
directions: In saucepan, melt shortening, peanut butter and chips.
Cool slightly. Add marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Butter an 11 x 16-inch pan and pat mixture into it.
Sprinkle with more coconut, if desired.
Cool until firm in refrigerator.
Cut and enjoy.

title: scallops supreme(serves 4)
directions: Wash scallops; dry.
Put scallops in shallow dish and pour wine over them.
Marinate for 10 minutes.
Pour all wine off.
Put scallops in baking dish.
Pour 1/4 pound melted butter over scallops.
Crumble crackers and add to scallops.
Season.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Heat to a boil.
Put into jars and seal.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Can make only one batch at a time.
In a glass or metal bowl, put oil and water.
Shake (do not stir) until oil and water are mixed well.
Will be cream-colored.
Add flour and stir with a fork to form a ball.
Divide into half.
Roll between waxed paper. Turn into pie pan.
This makes 2 one-crust pies or 1-two crust pie.

title: super mix
directions: Just mix and serve!

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Mix eggs, salt, pepper and onion soup mix; add mayonnaise. Stir in cooked broccoli.
Place in a greased souffle dish that's been dusted with 1 tablespoon bread crumbs or matzoh meal. Sprinkle top with 1 tablespoon bread crumbs or matzoh meal.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until dry on top.

title: valley eggplant parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut eggplants into 1/2-inch slices. Brush some of the oil onto two large baking sheets.
Arrange eggplant slices in single layer on sheets and brush tops with additional oil.
Bake until eggplants are fork-tender, about 20 minutes.

title: coca-cola cake with icing
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients, just to a boil.
Remove from heat and add next 4 ingredients.
Mix together well and add last 2 ingredients.
Mix together.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fun fruit salad(very low in fat)
directions: Mix marshmallows, fruit and sour cream.
Refrigerate several hours.
Sprinkle with coconut just before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crock-pot split pea soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a slow cooker (crock-pot) and cover. Turn heat to low.
Cook 10 to 12 hours until peas are softened. Cut meat away from ham hock and add to soup.
Makes 12 (1 cup) servings.

title: tartar sauce(makes 1 cup.)
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Serve with fish and other seafoods.

title: ham and cheese biscuit pleasers
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits.
Pat or roll out into a 4-inch circle.
Wrap ham slice around cheese cube.
Wrap biscuit dough around ham and cheese, pressing edges to seal.
Dip in melted butter, then in cracker crumbs.
Place, seam side down, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 10.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli by directions on the package, then drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Stir well.
Grease casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Crush potato chips and put on top, then put back in oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Drain juice from sweet potatoes and pineapple.
Combine both juices, brown sugar and cornstarch.
Pour over sweet potatoes and pineapple.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: kathleen lafon's potato salad
directions: Mix together sugar, salt, flour and eggs. Put in a pan and stir while adding water, then the vinegar. Cook over medium or low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add diced eggs, onions and cooled dressing to potatoes. The potatoes will soak up dressing. Keep salad refrigerated.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon; set aside 2 tablespoons of the juice.
In a medium mixing bowl mix salmon, egg, onion and celery until sticky. Stir in flour.
Add baking powder to salmon juice and then stir this into the salmon mixture.
Form into patties and fry in hot Crisco oil over medium heat until golden brown (about 5 minutes), turning only once so they'll be nice and crisp.
Drain on paper towels.

title: nut cake
directions: Have milk, eggs and shortening at room temperature.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into large bowl.
Drop in shortening; pour in milk, vanilla and 2 of the eggs.
Beat 300 brisk round-the-bowl strokes with spoon or 2 minutes on medium speed with electric mixer.
Add remaining 2 eggs; fold in nuts. Turn into tube pan and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done. Cool in pan on rack 10 or 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool. Glaze if desired.

title: best ever zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With mixer, mix together eggs and oil. Combine sugar, salt, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and flour.
Gradually add to eggs and oil, blending well.
Stir in extract, walnuts and zucchini.
(If batter is too thick, add some water.)
Pour into greased loaf or cake pans.
Bake for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: oatmeal zucchini nut bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs and sugar.
Add oil and vanilla. Mix in flour, oatmeal, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Stir in zucchini, nuts and raisins.
Mix well.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Mix dressing, onion soup mix and preserves.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tropical fruit cup
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Cut oranges in half.
Combine pineapple and oranges.
Add coconut and chill.
Combine cheese and 1/3 cup juice.
Stir brown sugar into cheese mixture.
Spoon atop fruit-coconut mixture.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: split pea or lentil vegetable soup
directions: Wash and drain peas.
Cut up potato, carrots, celery and onion.
Bring water to boil in large saucepan.
Add onion, split pea or lentils and oil.
Cover and boil gently for 30 to 45 minutes or until peas are tender.
Add potato, carrots, celery, salt, and pepper.
Cook until just tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Place the crescent rolls on a greased pizza pan; press out and up the side of the pan to form a crust.
Fry sausage; drain well and sprinkle on the crust.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of sausage, followed by hash browns.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper; beat well.
Pour over top of other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Mix the mixed fruit, cherries, pineapple, raisins and nuts; set aside.
Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Combine with fruit mixture.
Add to batter; mix well.
Pour in 3 (8-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 350° until sides leave pan.

title: crabmeat puffs
directions: Mix together and spread on 12 English muffin halves cut into sixths.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
May make ahead and freeze.
Bake prior to serving.

title: skillet chicken parmesan
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat and brown chicken, turning once.
Add Ragu pasta sauce and bring to a boil. Sprinkle with cheese.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with hot cooked spaghetti or in Italian rolls.

title: cauliflower and carrot salad
directions: In large saucepan mix vinegar, oil, water, sugar, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, add cauliflower, bell pepper and carrots.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add pimentos and mushrooms.
Return to a boil, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes.
Makes 12 cups, 7 1/2 calories per cup.

title: strawberry-rhubarb yes!
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In ungreased baking bowl or pan, mix rhubarb, strawberries, 1 1/2 cups of sugar and 1/2 cup of water; place in oven.
Measure flour, 3 tablespoons sugar, 3 teaspoons baking powder and salt into bowl.
Pour oil and milk into measuring cup (do not stir together); pour all at once into flour mixture.
Stir until mixture cleans the side of bowl and forms a ball.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto hot fruit.
Dot each biscuit with butter and sprinkle on the 2 tablespoons of sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon, mixed together.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Rinse frozen peas and carrots under cold water to separate; drain.
Heat butter in 2-quart saucepan over low heat until melted.
Stir in flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in turkey and vegetables.
Prepare pastry. Pour turkey mixture into pastry-lined pan.
Bake at 425° about 35 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry hamburg, sausage and onion together.
Combine well all remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly 2 to 3 hours.

title: artichoke balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; roll into small balls.
Roll in extra cheese; bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: maple candied walnuts
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients over low heat until sugar dissolves.
(Candy thermometer should read 238°, soft ball stage.) Remove from heat and blend in maple flavoring and butter.
Add walnut halves.
Stir gently until creamy.
Turn out onto waxed paper and separate.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed; add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Freeze in bowls.
Two or 3 hours before party, take out of freezer.
Put in punch bowl.
Before serving, add Mountain Dew. Can make 2 months ahead.

title: barbecued cabbage
directions: You will also need foil.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients well.
Add cream cheese, whip until smooth and then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into baked shell or graham cracker crust.
Keep refrigerated.

title: raw apple cake(8-inch layer)
directions: Cream oil, sugar and egg. Sift flour with salt and soda. Add to cream mixture. Add vanilla. Fold in nuts, raisins and apples. Bake in square pan, floured, oiled and lined with wax paper. Bake at 325° about 40 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Sprinkle peaches with cinnamon.
Mix sugar, flour and egg (mixture will be crumbly).
Sprinkle on top of peaches.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop onions and peppers very fine.
Add to other ingredients. Roll on wax paper and form a ball.
Cover with chopped pecans. Chill 2 to 4 hours.

title: cranberry cheese bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, add cranberries, cheese or nuts, egg and juice/Crisco/water mix.
Stir and spoon into 1 loaf pan or 3 small loaf pans.
Large loaf bakes at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes; 3 small loaves bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
This makes a great holiday bread.
If you once exchange this bread with neighbors at holiday time, they will always look forward to it!!!

title: caramel icing
directions: Place 1/2 cup sugar in iron skillet over low heat.
Mix in saucepan 2 cups sugar, milk, egg and oleo or butter.
Cook and stir this mixture over low heat until oleo or butter melts.
Increase heat and cook until it boils rapidly.
(Scorches easily.) Meanwhile, the sugar in the skillet has begun to melt.
When it is a light brown, pour it into the other boiling mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Beat until consistency to spread.
(I use this on 1-2-3-4 cake layers.)

title: strawberry fig jam
directions: Mix ingredients together and cook 15 minutes over low heat until it boils, then cook 15 minutes more.
Seal in jars and top with paraffin.

title: apricot-apple muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a separate bowl, stir together eggs, half and half and cooled melted margarine. Add apples, apricots and bran cereal to dry ingredients.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients.
Stir only until moistened.
Do not overmix.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fill greased muffin tins about 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, until lightly browned.
Serve hot from oven.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: Rinse grapes.
Cut in half and remove seeds.
Place in bottom of a glass serving bowl.
Peel and slice bananas.
Place over grapes.
Drain peaches well and cut into small pieces.
Place on top of bananas.
Rinse berries and put on top of peaches.
Peel oranges and remove the white skin.
Slice and cut into small pieces and put on top of berries.
Peel and slice kiwis.
Add to salad.
Pour orange juice over top of salad and sprinkle with the powdered sugar.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: cathead biscuits
directions: Sift and mix dry ingredients then blend with lard. Add buttermilk. For each biscuit, pinch off a portion of dough about the shape of a large egg and pat out with your hands. Bake at 475 until lightly brown.

title: curried rice
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook, covered, in top of double boiler until all moisture is absorbed and rice is tender and fluffy, about 40 to 50 minutes.
Rice may be cooked also in heavy-duty pan with close fitting lid.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour cream.
Blend.
Then add flour, cocoa, baking soda, cloves, cinnamon and salt.
Stir together.
Add zucchini and mix well.
In a 13 x 9-inch well-greased and floured pan, spoon mixture and add chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour wings
directions: Preheat fryer to 375°. In a large bowl, combine flour, salt and pepper. In a medium bowl, add milk. Dredge chicken wing halves in flour mixture, then in milk and then again in the flour mixture. Shake off excess flour. Carefully place wing halves in fryer and fry wing halves for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Mix horseradish, apple, salt, mustard and sugar.
Whip cream until stiff.
Fold into first mixture.
Serve with baked ham, pot roast, roast lamb or veal.

title: cho-fudge
directions: Combine
cocoa,
sugar and salt in large pan.
Add milk and bring to bubbly boil on high heat.
Reduce heat to medium and boil
without
stirring
until small balls form in water; remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla to mixture and beat by
hand until it loses glossy look.
Quickly pour in buttered pan; cool.

title: jane's sweet-sour chicken
directions: Mix cornstarch in 1/3 cup water in cup.
Mix all ingredients, except chicken, in saucepan and bring to boil.
Discard garlic. Place skinned chicken legs, thighs and drumsticks (as many as you want) in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour boiled mixture over chicken. Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake 1/2 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: mediterranean macaroni
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Cook and stir garlic in spread 1 minute.
Add beans, tomatoes, basil, oregano and pepper; cook over low heat 4 minutes.
Add dinner and parsley; mix lightly. Makes 4 servings.
Prep time:
10 minutes.
Cooking time:
10 minutes.

title: black cherry salad
directions: To hot water add fruit juice, cold water and lemon juice.

title: frozen corn
directions: Mix all together and put in containers and freeze.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Peel carrots; wash.
Remove ends.
Cut in half lengthwise and crosswise in 2 to 3 pieces.
Add carrots to boiling water.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes until tender; drain.
Save cooking liquid. Combine butter, sugar and cooking liquid; bring to a boil and cook, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.

Add drained carrots and continue cooking until carrots are completely glazed. Stir gently to prevent breaking carrots. Remove from heat. Combine the glazed carrots with 1/2 cup chopped parsley just before serving.
Makes 24 servings.

title: cool whip lemon pie
directions: In a bowl combine Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Stir in lemon juice to taste.
Pour in crust; chill for 1 hour.

title: quick butterscotch sauce
directions: In small heavy gauge saucepan, combine butterscotch morsels and heavy cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm over ice cream or other desserts; top with nuts.
Refrigerate leftover sauce.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: casper's cracker cookies
directions: Spread the crackers liberally with the peanut butter.
Set aside.
Melt white dipping chocolate in a double boiler.
Holding each cracker with tongs, dip into the melted chocolate.
Spread wax paper under cooling rack and let the crackers dry on a rack.
Store in a cool place.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: peanut butter butterscotch treats
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In large bowl, combine sugars.
Add butter and mix to form grainy paste, scraping sides of bowl.
Add eggs, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix until fluffy.
Add in flour. Do not overmix.
Add in 1 1/2 cups of butterscotch chips.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet 1 1/2-inches apart.
Flatten down balls with wet fork.
Not too flat!
Bake about 15 minutes.
Cookies should be slightly brown on the edges. Let cool and serve.
Yield:
3 1/2 dozen.

title: swiss cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup and milk together and pour 2/3 of the mixture over the broccoli.
Slice the boiled eggs and place in pan, forming a layer over the soup mixture.
Crumb bacon over the eggs.
Spread 2/3 can of Durkee onions, sprinkle cheese and add the remaining soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Add the remaining onions the last 10 minutes.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Heat water and margarine to a boil. Add flour and mix until it forms a ball (almost immediately). Let cool. When cool, add eggs one at a time. Mix in good. Grease a 9 x 13 glass pan and spread mixture on bottom and a little up sides. Bake 35 minutes at 400°. Should be puffy. Let cool.

title: stars and stripes
directions: Slice 1 cup strawberries; set aside.
Line bottom of 12 x 8-inch glass baking dish with cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Place strawberry halves and blueberries over Cool Whip to create a flag design.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: corn broccoli bake
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients and place in a buttered 1-quart casserole dish.
Mix cracker crumbs with remaining 2 tablespoons of butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: can't fail caramels
directions: Cook all ingredients except vanilla, slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook to medium soft ball stage (240°).
Remove from heat; add vanilla and nuts, if desired.
Pour into buttered pan (9 x 13-inch).
Mark squares and wrap in waxed paper.

title: microwave cobbler
directions: Layer 5 pats of butter.
Sprinkle cake mix over.
Spread pie filling over top.
Cook 10 minutes.
Rotate, then cook 10 minutes more.

title: busy woman's dream
directions: Crumble raw ground chuck in bottom of 10 x 10-inch baking dish.
Spread soup evenly over meat.
Place Tater Tots evenly over top.
(No other liquid is needed.)
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 45 minutes, until bubbly and Tater Tots are brown.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add onion, green pepper, pepperoni and mushrooms.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cooked and drained pasta and sauce, stirring thoroughly.
Place half of pasta mixture in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with half the cheese.
Add remaining pasta and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: slush punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 4 cups boiling water.
Add sugar with 8 cups water and boil 3 minutes.
Add pineapple and orange juice. Freeze.
Thaw 2 1/2 hours before serving.
Add 2 quarts of ginger ale to each gallon.
(Add 2 packages of Kool-Aid, same flavor as Jell-O used, to make a richer and deeper color, if desired.)

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Mix flour, lard and salt.
Stir in liquids.
Makes 4 to 5 crusts.
Can be frozen.

title: cornmeal pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add syrup, milk and vanilla.
Mix well. Fold in cornmeal and flour.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300°.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes longer or until pie tests done.
Cool.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.

title: cut-it-out cookies
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat butter or margarine with electric mixer on medium speed until softened.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Gradually beat in flour until well mixed.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
Wrap each part in clear plastic wrap.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours or until firm enough to roll out. Turn oven to 375°. Remove 1 piece of dough from refrigerator and unwrap.
On a lightly floured surface, roll out dough so it's 1/4-inch thick.
(Use floured cookie cutters.)
Bake in 375° oven about 8 minutes.
Makes 36 to 48 cookies.

title: rosamarina salad
directions: Cook sugar, salt, flour, eggs and juices.
Cool to make custard.
Cook rosamarina macaroni.
Rinse with cold water; drain. Add the custard and fruits.
Let stand a couple of hours or overnight.
(Keep in refrigerator.)
Stir in large Cool Whip and serve.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Make white sauce of first 5 ingredients. Place half the potatoes in greased 2 quart casserole. Cover with half onion and half sauce. Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: broccoli corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except butter and crumbs.
Spread this in bottom of baking dish.
Combine butter and crumbs; spread on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown roast on both sides; add enough water to cover.
Cook on top of stove until done.
Cool.
Pull meat apart like barbecue. Put meat and other ingredients; cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Serve on toasted buns.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook meat, onion and garlic until meat is browned.
Drain off fat.
Stir in the undrained tomatoes and next 4 ingredients. Cover; simmer 15 minutes, stirring often.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: In large cake pan, crush cookies and put in bottom of pan. Melt margarine and dribble over the crust.
Freeze.
Spread ice cream over the crust.
Freeze.

title: never-fail spoon rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast in very warm water and dissolve.
Melt margarine.
Cream margarine and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add beaten egg and dissolved yeast-water to mixture.
Add flour to the mixture and stir well.
May be used immediately or
stored in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.
Drop by spoonful into greased muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Rolls will not be very brown on top.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar and one egg at a time, beating after each.
Measure sifted flour in sugar box and add to creamed mixture.
Mix well and add flavoring.
Start in cold oven and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar together; set aside.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cornstarch and sugar mixture.
Bring to a boil until thick.
Cool and add strawberries.
Put in cool crust that has been browned in oven.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Also tastes great if you add in ham or sausage.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove from bones.
Set aside. Use two cups of chicken broth.
Cook rice in broth.
Combine all other ingredients in a saucepan; cook until tender.

title: frozen pink salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill for at least 2 hours.

title: mamma's own:  salmon patties
directions: When I was learning to cook, my mother started me on this recipe for salmon patties.
You can add a little more seasoning if you like, but this will surely get you started on something simple yet a delight to eat.
Hint:
Prepare side dishes of sweet peas and macaroni and cheese.
A great combination!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Chop into bite-size pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients with chicken.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: rancho beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Drain well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Cook in crock-pot 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours on high or 4 to 8 hours on low or bake 30 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: mrs. bonham's fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together oil, eggs and sugar.
Sift together next five ingredients.
Add sifted, dry ingredients alternately with apples, to egg mixture and mix well.
Stir in pecans and half of morsels.
Spread batter in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with remaining morsels.
Bake at 350° for 1
hour.

title: rice krispies balls
directions: Melt oleo and peanut butter together.
Add powdered sugar and Rice Krispies.
Roll in balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin together.
Roll balls in chocolate mixture and cool on wax paper. Very easy to double this recipe.

title: congealed buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple; add Jell-O and stir until well dissolved.
Let stand until cool.
Add buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into mold or pan and chill until firm.

title: no fat pork and zucchini stir-fry
directions: Combine tenderloin, sugar, cornstarch, soy sauce, dark soy sauce and ginger wine and mix well.
Combine zucchini and kosher salt.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Rinse, drain and squeeze.
In frying pan, bring broth to boil.
Add mushroom and carrot.
Stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes.
Add zucchini; stir-fry until zucchini is heated through.
Remove to platter, leaving liquid in pan.
Bring broth to boil; stir-fry until pork is just done.
Stir in vegetables. Adjust seasoning and serve.
Serve over rice.
To make ginger wine, peel fresh ginger.
Wash.
Pat dry.
Slice thinly.
Place in a clean glass jar with tightly fitting lid.
Cover with pale dry sherry.
Will keep in refrigerator for up to 3 months.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.

title: summer sausage
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well, cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Remove from refrigerator and mix well again.
Shape into 5 rolls.
Preheat oven to 150°.
Place rolls on baking pan and bake 8 hours.
Turn 2 times during baking.
Cool and wrap in foil. Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix beaten egg, sugar, oil, salt, soda and flour in a medium size bowl.
Pour can of fruit cocktail and juice over mixture. Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased well.
Cover batter with nuts and brown sugar mixed well.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: yeast rise biscuits
directions: Sift flour and sugar in large bowl.
Mix warm water and yeast together.
Add to flour/sugar mixture with buttermilk and shortening.
Mix thoroughly.
Knead and put in greased bowl. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out biscuits and bake at 400° until brown.

title: dad's apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare 2 crusts.
Put one in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cut slits in other crust; set aside. Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, allspice and salt (for juicy pie, use 1/4 cup flour).
Add sugar mixture to apples; toss to coat fruit.
Turn into baking dish (apples will mound higher than sides).
Dot with butter.
Carefully place pastry atop apples; flute to the sides but not over the edge.
Brush with milk; sprinkle with sugar.
Cover edge of pie with foil.
Bake in oven for 25 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes more.

title: new england pumpkin pie
directions: Separate egg.
Beat yolk and add to 1 1/2 cups hot milk and pumpkin
mixture.
Beat
egg white and fold carefully into mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Turn oven to 350° for 30 more minutes, or until firm.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread coconut on bottom of greased 13 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top of coconut.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over coconut and pecans. Combine margarine, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in a bowl and mix well. Drop this mixture by teaspoonfuls on top of cake batter. Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: shrimp harnisch
directions: Clean shrimp.
In frying pan, saute shrimp in olive oil.
Add vegetables, stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce and spice to taste.
Let simmer 12 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except the last 3 together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with the last 3 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crepes fines sucrees(light batter for crepes)
directions: You will also need an electric blender and a rubber scraper. (If you don't have an electric blender, proceed as follows: Gradually work the egg yolks into the flour with a wooden spoon; beat in the liquids by droplets, then strain batter through a fine sieve.)

title: pizza snacks
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Put Mozzarella cheese on rye bread. Add 1 teaspoon tomato sauce; add crumbled sausage.
Sprinkle oregano and dash of garlic salt.
Top with mushrooms and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown and cheese melted. Serve warm.
(Can be made ahead and frozen until ready to serve.)

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer wafers and bananas in large bowl.
Alternate the layers.

title: crab cakes
directions: Stir together 2 cups cracker crumbs and next 9 ingredients. Fold in crabmeat. Shape into 8 (3-inch) patties; dredge in remaining 1 cup cracker crumbs.

title: mixed clam dip
directions: Drain clams, reserving juice.
Combine minced clams with cream cheese, mayonnaise, grated onion, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend thoroughly.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together for a salad.
Stir in one bottle of Catalina salad dressing.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Bring sugars, salt and sour cream to a boil, stirring often. Cook to soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Cool and add the vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until thick.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch dish.
This is easy to make and is really delicious.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix all other ingredients with spinach.
Form into small balls the size of a walnut.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.
May be frozen and warmed in the microwave.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Dip cookies in milk and put them in a glass dish.
Cover with some of the Cool Wip.
Continue layers until dish is full.
End up with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle crumbled Oreos over the top.
This is very good.

title: fried crawfish
directions: Make a mixture of eggs, milk, baking powder and vinegar. Marinate crawfish tails in this for about 2 hours. Remove and season with salt and red pepper. Dip in flour and fry in hot fat until done. Doesn't take long.

title: stewed rabbit
directions: Cut up rabbit into serving size pieces.
Salt and pepper each piece and brown with onion in oil.
Add ham, some water (about 1 cup), wine, mushrooms, bay leaves and garlic.
Season again with salt to taste and simmer for about 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: heavenly gold salad
directions: Heat 1 can nectar and dissolve jello in that.
Add remaining nectar and other ingredients.
Chill until firm in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in crock-pot which has been greased with 2 teaspoons margarine (or sprayed with Pam).

title: meat dip
directions: Brown ground meat and sausage together and drain.
Melt the cheese with the cream of mushroom soup and add Ro-Tel tomatoes. Mix this mixture with the meat.
Serve with chips.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar, and vanilla thoroughly.
Stir flour and salt together, blend in.
Mix in nuts.
Chill dough.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10-12 minutes until set, not brown.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool.
Roll in sugar again.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: one pot pork chops
directions: Use large frying pan with cover or electric skillet.
Salt and pepper chops on both sides.
Brown in small amount of oil in pan. Remove chops.

title: fudgy chocolate ice cream
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat chocolate, condensed milk, egg yolks and vanilla.
Stir in half and half, whipping cream and nuts, if desired.
Pour into an ice cream freezer container. Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: miles' favorite french toast
directions: Pour milk in a mixing bowl, add eggs and mix well.
Put 1/2 stick butter in frying pan and melt.
Take a slice of bread and place in milk and egg mixture turning bread to coat evenly, place bread in pan and turn often to brown on both sides.
Place on plate, sprinkle with cinnamon (if desired), pour on syrup and enjoy.

title: beef ragout(microwave)
directions: Combine onion, green pepper and olive oil in a 3-quart casserole.
Microwave at High until peppers are tender, 2 to 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; microwave at High for 10 minutes.
Reduce power to Medium.
