Microwave until beef and potatoes are tender, 50 minutes to 1 hour, stirring after 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over rice, noodles or potatoes, if desired.

title: the meridien's chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water or in microwave.
Set aside. Beat egg whites until fairly firm peaks form.
Then beat in sugar gradually, 2 tablespoons at a time, until stiff peaks form.
Whisk butter and egg yolks into chocolate.
Fold egg whites into chocolate mixture.
Add rum. Turn into serving dish or individual molds.
Chill for several hours.
If desired, serve with custard sauce made with remaining egg yolks, or garnish with thin, thin candied orange slices and peel.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Beat flour, salt, margarine and sugar in bowl on medium until crumbly.
Press in dish firmly.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: pork chop or chicken bake(casserole)
directions: Put rice and water in flat 10 x 10 x 2-inch casserole pan. Stir in onion soup mix, onion, pepper and corn; mix well.
Flour meat and place on top of soup mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: miniature cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to rolling boil in saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs in thoroughly, one at a time.
Beat until smooth.
Drop dough by slightly rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake about 25 minutes or until puffed, golden brown and dry. Remove from baking sheet and allow to cool.
Bakes about 70 puffs.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Melt oleo; stir in flour and salt.
Gradually add milk while stirring.
Then add cheese and garlic.
Stir over medium-high heat until thickened.
Makes 3 cups.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Remove crusts; cube bread. Butter a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Put a layer of bread, then cheese; repeat.
Melt butter and cool. Beat eggs, milk, salt and cooled butter.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: hotel pierre, new york, saffron rice
directions: Dissolve saffron in 1/2 cup hot water.
Combine the dissolved saffron, butter, rice, onion, salt and 1 cup of the hot water in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 20 minutes or until rice is very dry, stirring at end of 10 minutes. Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups hot water, cover and return to hot oven for 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook 5 minutes longer.
Fluff with fork before serving.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook hamburger meat and drain.
Add onion (chopped),
tomatoes, tomato sauce, potatoes and kidney beans. Cook until potatoes are done.
Chop up the cabbage and add to this mixture.
Cook about 20 minutes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Mix any kind of Stove Top dressing. Place about 1/2 cup dressing on
each
chop.
Then
put water by the chops.
Bake, covered, at
350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 15 minutes. Before
serving,
pour a small amount of gravy on top of each chop.

title: rich sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and flavoring; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Wrap dough in waxed paper; chill for several hours or overnight.
Roll very thin, 1/16-inch thick, on a floured pastry cloth. Cut into desired shapes.
Place on cookie sheets and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in a hot oven, 425°, for about 5 to 7 minutes or until delicately browned.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: quick sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients together and add together.
Drop on ungreased sheet.
Bake 6 minutes at 400°.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat milk and cream cheese 15 minutes in mixer.
Add lime juice and vanilla.
Pour in crust and garnish with whipped cream and twist of lime.

title: chocolate dipped horns
directions: Spoon peanut butter in a small plastic bag. Squeeze a small amount of peanut butter into each corn snack. Dip each in chocolate coating and place on waxed paper to dry. Store chocolate covered snacks in an airtight container. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: homemade cream cordial
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend until smooth.
Store, tightly covered, in refrigerator up to one month.
Stir before serving.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: In small bowl, mix together gelatin, salt and 1/2 cup sugar. In 2-quart saucepan, whisk egg yolks, lemon juice and water until well mixed, about 1 minute.
Sprinkle gelatin mixture over liquid. Let stand 5 minutes to soften gelatin.
Put saucepan over medium-high heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to boil, 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and pour into bowl. Cover and refrigerate until mixture is partially set, about 45 minutes.
Put egg whites in a clean, grease-free bowl.
Beat on low speed until frothy.
Increase speed to high and beat until soft peaks result, another 1 to 2 minutes.
Gradually add remaining 1/2 cup sugar, beating constantly until stiff peaks form, another minute or two.
Fold 1/4 of beaten whites into lemon mixture to lighten it.
Fold in remaining whites.
Pour into baked pie crust. Chill until firm 3 to 4 hours.
Decorate top of pie with rosettes of whipped cream just before serving, if desired.

title: pumpkin pies
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour in unbaked pie shells. Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
This recipe makes two pies.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix all together; fix like pancakes.
Add milk, if needed. Butter and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt butter and sugar together.
Remove from heat and add nuts, flour and baking powder.
Add beaten egg yolks and stir until well blended.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into mixture. Pour in greased oblong pan (11 x 14-inch).
Bake 30 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut in squares.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in heated skillet.
Spoon batter (1 to 2 tablespoons) in pan to brown on one side, then flip and brown other side.
The pancake will be soft and moist.
Serve as a potato replacement, plain or topped with grated Parmesan cheese, sour cream, chives or tomato sauce.
Serves 2 to 3 people.

title: tired grandma cake
directions: Combine butter, cake mix, cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple and juice.
Stir lightly.
Place in sheet cake pan. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: kelly's spaghetti sauce
directions: Add all ingredients except the hamburger and sugar into a 2 or 3-quart pot, burner to medium for 15 minutes, while stirring sauce often.
Then lower heat to simmer for 1 to 2 hours and add sugar (sprinkled over the top of the sauce), then brown and drain hamburger and add.
Cover.
Remember to stir sauce every 15 to 20 minutes or more to assure no burning and even seasoning.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: minty sugar cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and eggs; blend well.
Add beaten egg, sour cream and mint extract, then blend in the flour and add chopped mint leaves.
Let chill for at least 1 hour.

title: pretzels
directions: Add yeast to a large bowl, then add warm water and mix.
Add flour, 1 teaspoon salt and sugar.
Mix, mix, mix.
Turn out on floured surface.
Punch down and fold.
Repeat this 10 to 20 times. Make 6 to 8 balls.
Roll and shape into a pretzel (or any shape you prefer).
Brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Remove and cool 10 minutes.

title: brandied potted cheese(servings: 1)
directions: Blend the cream cheese and the cream together Add the toasted onion dip mix and combine thoroughly. Add the ground Cheddar and, with a wooden spoon, mix and beat until well combined. Add the brandy and blend. Pack into small crocks or jars. Cover and refrigerate. Keeps well for several weeks. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: rich vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, flour
and
salt
in
a mixing bowl; add eggs. Beat at high speed of an electric mixer for 1 minute or until dry ingredients
are
moistened.
Heat	milk
in a large Dutch oven over
medium
heat	until
hot.
Add
egg
mixture, stirring until blended.
Cook
until
mixture boils, stirring constantly. Remove from
heat.	Chill at least 2 hours.
Stir in whipping cream
and	vanilla.
Pour	into freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturers instructions.
Let ripen 1 1/2 to 2 hours before serving.
Yields 5 quarts.

title: turtles candy
directions: Melt caramels and milk over water in a double boiler.
Remove and add pecans.
Put by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin together.
Dip candy in chocolate mixture. Makes 40 to 50.

title: pecan pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Set aside about 1/3 cup flour.
Combine remaining sifted flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beating well after each addition.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Dredge pecans in reserved flour and fold into batter.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool for 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: chile rellano'slubbock, texas
directions: Batter can be covered and stored for reuse.

title: popcorn
directions: You will also need 1 popcorn popper or deep pan with lid.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butterscotch pieces and shortening together. Stir in the sugar. Add eggs and vanilla, beating well after each addition. Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Use a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: judy's salad dressing
directions: Place ingredients into deep bowl.

Whip with electric mixer adding milk a little at a time until consistency that you prefer. Three tablespoons yellow mustard may also be added for flavor. Use for potato salad, macaroni salad, cole slaw and 7-layer salad.

title: haricots verts a l'ail(green beans with garlic; from provence, france)
directions: Drop beans into large pot of boiling salted water; cook uncovered on high for 6 to 8 minutes or slightly crisp.
Drain in colander, then drop them immediately into large quantity of very cold water.
Drain.
Heat oil in nonstick 10-inch saute pan over low heat.
Add garlic, bread crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper; cook, stirring, for 1 minute.
Add butter; when it is melted, add the beans and stir to heat.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar until thick and foamy. Stir in gently the vanilla, zucchini, pineapple, flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Bake in 2 greased 5 x 9-inch pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all together and bake at 325° in unbaked pie shell for 40 minutes.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in the order listed.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cool in pan 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool thoroughly.
Can be frozen.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread as directed on package and crumble.
Add chopped tomatoes, bacon, bell pepper, onion and pickle relish to cornbread.
Mix mayonnaise and pickle juice.
Put one-half of cornbread mixture in dish and cover with one half of mayonnaise mixture.
Put other half of cornbread mixture and top with remaining mayonnaise mixture.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix with all other ingredients except cornflakes.
Crush cornflakes on top.
Bake one hour at 300°. Makes 2 casseroles, or may be frozen to be baked later.

title: irish bread
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Bake in 350° oven.
Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl and then in a separate bowl mix eggs and milk together (eggs first and then add the milk).
Add milk and egg mixture to the dry ingredients and then add the melted butter. Combine the walnuts and raisins (and currants if used) to mixture. Sprinkle a little sugar on top before baking.
Takes about 60 minutes.
About 10 minutes before it is done, you can spread some butter on top to make it golden brown.
Before adding raisins, soak them in hot water for a few minutes to soften.
Drain well.

title: jiffy cake bake
directions: Bake box of white or yellow cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool.
Beat cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk.
Mix 1 1/2 cups milk with box of instant vanilla pudding.
Crushed pineapple may be added to cream cheese and spread on top of cake.
Pineapple can be omitted and pie filling of choice can be spread on top of cream cheese layer.
Top with Cool Whip, nuts and coconut.

title: **frozen candied fruit cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, beat in the egg.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Blend in pecans, fruit and cherries.
Form in rolls 2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in Saran Wrap; freeze.
Heat oven to 375°.
Slice very thinly.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.
Yields about 10 dozen.

title: everyday broccoli cheese chicken
directions: Step 1:
In skillet, over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Spoon off fat.

title: fudge cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and cream of tartar in bowl.
Add milk, vanilla and shortening.
Mix.
Add melted chocolate, then mix.
Add eggs and beat 2 minutes, then add baking soda and water; beat for 1 minute.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix thoroughly with crackers.
Put 1/2 cracker crumbs on bottom of greased casserole pan.
Divide asparagus and almonds.
Pour 1/2 over crumbs, then sauce, then last 1/2 of asparagus and almonds.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: avocado salad
directions: Toss lettuce and avocado in bowl.
Toss with dressing.
Serves 5.

title: 6 min fix
directions: Mold hamburger with pit.
Insert prepared uncooked dressing in cavity. Cover with cream of mushroom soup. Cook in oven at about 325° for approximately 40 to 60 minutes, depending on thickness of meat.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger,
Drain.
Mix mayonnaise, milk, cornstarch. Add to hamburger and then add cheese.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry drink
directions: Prepare Roselle by taking the petals off and washing them before measuring.
Grind all the fruit together; add 1 cup water and boil for 5 minutes.
Strain and add sugar.
While hot, add cinnamon and cloves.
Cool and when ready to serve.
Add water to taste.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Fry hamburger and onion.
Heat sour cream, mushroom soup, evaporated milk and cheese; when blended, add green chilies.
Fry tortillas until soft in small amount of oil.
Roll hamburger in tortillas and place in baking dish.
Pour sauce over; heat at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: chicken chili
directions: Brown chicken, bacon, sausage, garlic and onion together.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes to one hour, stirring to prevent sticking to pot.

title: mom's veggie soup
directions: Brown bacon and hamburger in frypan.
Put cabbage, carrots, onions and celery in food processor (one item at a time).
Add peas, green beans and tomatoes to pot.

title: marinated beef
directions: Cook meat until tender.
Mix sauce.
Add meat.
Marinate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours or until all sauce is absorbed.

title: red bean casserole
directions: Wash, soak and cook beans until tender.
Remove bay leaf. Drain beans.
Thoroughly drain tomatoes and cut into spoon size pieces.
Mix and cook all ingredients, except bacon and cheese. Put mixture into casserole and top, in order, with cheese and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Place casserole under broiler about 5 minutes or until evenly crisped.
Makes 5 (5 ounce) servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add mashed bananas and beaten eggs.
Sift together and add flour, soda and salt.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 (1 1/4 lb.) loaves.

title: salmon souffl(serves 4 to 6 people)
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water in a mixing bowl.
Stir in boiling water and whisk until gelatin dissolves.
Cool to room temperature.
Whisk in mayonnaise, lemon juice, grated onion, paprika, Tabasco sauce, salt and dill.
Stir and blend. Refrigerate for 20 minutes until it thickens.
Fold in the salmon. Whip the heavy cream and fold into the mixture.
Transfer to a large deep dish that holds 12 portions.
Cover and chill 4 hours. Garnish with watercress.
Serve with crackers.

title: party bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and spread on cocktail bread.
Place on cookie sheet and heat for about 10 minutes or until heated through.

title: pumpkin upside-down cake
directions: Sprinkle cake mix over pumpkin pie mixture.
Drizzle butter or margarine over top of cake mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle chopped pecans or English walnuts (1 cup) over top of cake.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove and cool.

title: pecan chewies
directions: Beat margarine and brown sugar until blended.
Add eggs, one at at time, until creamy.
Add vanilla.
Gradually mix in flour. Fold in pecans.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Allow to cool somewhat before cutting.

title: buttermilk icing
directions: Place oleo, cocoa and buttermilk into a pan.
Bring to a boil. Remove and add powdered sugar.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth and add vanilla; mix.
Spread while cake is warm.
Use your favorite chocolate cake recipe.

title: macaroni and bacon dish
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and fry until crisp. Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain macaroni and mix other ingredients.
Season to taste and simmer about 20 minutes.

title: old fashioned chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt. Mix both mixtures together thoroughly.
Put about a tablespoonful on a cookie sheet; bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 1 to 1 1/2 dozen or 3 to 3 1/2 dozen (small).

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs lengthwise.
Take out yolks and mix with all other ingredients. Put mixture back inside egg whites and sprinkle with paprika.

title: creamed tuna on toast
directions: Slowly add milk to the soup in a 3-quart saucepan.
When creamy, add tuna, peas and chopped eggs.
Serve over buttered toast.
Great for a lunch or quick supper.

title: pumpkin pie crumble
directions: Add pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar and spice together.
Pour into greased 8 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle box of dry cake mix over the pumpkin mixture covering completely.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mixture. Drizzle top of nuts with melted butter and remaining top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour; cool completely before cutting into squares.
Can top with whipped cream.
Really delicious.

title: spiced peach butter
directions: Peel and cut peaches into chunks.
Process until coarsely chopped.
Combine juice, spices and peaches in a heavy pan. Simmer 1 to 2 hours, stirring frequently, until thick.
Sweeten to taste and stir thoroughly to mix sugar.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: malted
directions: Blend; pour into glasses.

title: kowpot
directions: Boil chicken in enough salted water to make 4 cups stock. Remove meat from bones and cut into bite-size pieces.
Reserve stock.
Chop cabbage and stir-fry in small amount of oil until tender.
Cook rice in chicken stock until done.
Saute pepper and green onions until tender.
Mix all ingredients.
Add mushrooms. Add egg.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Season with soy sauce.
Serves 12 easily.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with Pam cooking spray or grease with Crisco or butter.
Mix together flour, sugar, salt and butter in a bowl.
Use a pastry blender or 2 knives until you have crumbs.
Reserve 3/4 cup crumbs for topping. In a medium bowl, mix water, molasses and baking soda.
Add to the flour mixture, mixing well.
Pour into baking pan.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with cream, if desired.

title: sugar peanuts
directions: Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When water is absorbed and the sugar sticks to the peanuts, put them on a cookie sheet and bake 30 minutes at 300°, stirring every 5 minutes.

title: flight line wine soaked ribeye beef loin
directions: Marinate beef loin in bag or bowl overnight.
Take loin out. Make small deep slits in various spots in top of loin.
Place 1 clove of garlic, thyme and rosemary in slits.
Use pepper and garlic granules generously.
Use indirect cooking on charcoal grill.
Insert meat thermometer. Cook until thermometer reaches 140° for rare, 160° for medium-rare and 170° for well done.
If using oven, cook at 325° to 350° until thermometer reaches desired temperature.
Let stand 15 minutes after removing from grill or oven before carving.

title: stuffed peppers in foil
directions: Cook and stir onion and celery in butter until tender.
Stir in croutons, cheese and salt.
Cut thin slices from stem end of peppers.
Remove seeds and membranes.
Wash inside and out.
Place each pepper on a piece of double thickness heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Fill peppers with cheese stuffing.
Wrap securely in foil. Cook directly on medium coals 15 to 20 minutes or on grill 3 to 4 inches from hot coals for 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn once.
Serves 4. Serve as a vegetable or main dish or great with steak on the grill.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Cut shortening and sugar into flour.
Add other ingredients and stir well.
Can be used immediately or refrigerated and used as needed.
Roll and cut as biscuits.
Cook in moderate oven until done.

title: calico macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and mustard together.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift all dry ingredients together and cut in shortening.
Stir yeast into buttermilk and mix into smooth dough.
Roll out and cut as regular biscuits.
Brush top with melted butter.
Let rise a little before baking.
Bake in a 400° oven until done.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and add onion, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Grate cheese; add chilies and olives (set aside). Heat soups together.
Cook tortillas (keep them hot).
Alternately put meat mixture and cheese mixture in tortillas.
Roll and put in long baking pans.
Pour soups over top of tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen raspberry mousse
directions: Fold beaten cream and egg whites together.
Add raspberry Melba sauce by gently folding into beaten mixture.
Pour into ungreased mold.
Cover with Saran and foil wrap and freeze. Unmold and garnish.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix in blender first 4 ingredients.
Add vinegar, then add salad oil.
Add 1 1/2 tablespoons of poppy seed while still blending.
Refrigerate.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and vanilla.
Add flour and chips.
Form 1-inch balls and press down with floured glass bottom.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes until golden.
Serve at "Tea Time"!

title: cheese cake
directions: Put cottage cheese through sieve (makes it smoother).
Soften cream cheese in mixer; gradually add cottage cheese.
Blend together eggs, sugar, cornstarch, vanilla and lemon juice.
Add to softened cheeses.
Blend in flour, sour cream and melted butter.
Pour into spring-form pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Turn off heat and let stand in oven 2 hours.
Remove from oven. Loosen pan, cool and remove from pan.
Enjoy!

title: raspberry bars
directions: Beat butter or margarine and brown sugar in a bowl until fluffy.
Stir together flour, soda and salt.
Stir into butter-sugar mixture.

title: trash cookies
directions: Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and margarine 3 minutes in microwave.
Put Crispix in bowl and pour melted ingredients over it.
Use white trash bag (no other bag).
Put half of powdered sugar in it.
Pour the cereal and ingredients in on top of powdered sugar.
Add the rest of the powdered sugar.
Shake well.
Pour into a big bowl and you have your trash cookies.
No cutting or rolling, just fun.

title: the perfect chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Combine dry ingredients in large bowl. Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla. Beat for 2 minutes on medium speed. Stir in boiling water (batter will be thin). Pour into two 9-inch round greased and floured pans or one 13 x 9-inch rectangle pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean. Cool completely. Remove from pan(s) and frost.

title: sugar coated pecans
directions: Melt butter in pot.
Add everything except pecans.
Heat to simmering, stirring constantly for about 5 minutes.
Add pecans. Pour onto baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes. Transfer to wax paper to dry.

title: baked rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a greased dish.
Set dish in water in oven and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: nippy beets
directions: Drain beets and save juice.
Combine next 4 ingredients.
Add beet juice.
Cook until thickened.
Add oleo and horseradish and pour sauce over the beets.
Heat and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: date bars
directions: In a saucepan, combine dates, sugar and water and cook, stirring frequently until very thick.
Stir in walnuts.
Cool. Sift flour, salt and soda together in a mixing bowl; add oats and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle water over mixture; stir lightly.
Pat half of mixture into a greased 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread with date mixture; cover with remaining oat mixture and pat lightly.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into bars.
Can yield up to 48 bars depending on size you cut.

title: banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg with fork.
Stir in milk and oil.
Blend dry ingredients in a mixer bowl.
Process bananas, then stir the bananas into the mixer bowl.
Stir in the raisins and walnuts.
Spoon the batter into 22 muffin cups coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until a golden brown.
Remove from the tins immediately.
Makes 22 muffins.

title: chocolate mint coffee
directions: Brew coffee as usual.
Drop one mint into each cup.
Stir until melted.
Serve hot.

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: Sift flour, measure and sift with soda and salt.
Cream shortening	and
spices,
gradually
add
sugar
and
continue creaming.
Add
egg
and
molasses.
Alternately add the flour mixture with
the
sour milk, beginning and ending with flour. Add raisins.
Drop
by	teaspoon on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° about 15 minutes.
Makes 3 or 4 dozen.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Cook milk and butter over low heat until butter melts.
Add dry ingredients and then add egg yolks and vanilla.
Cook until thickened.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Brown in oven.
Cool and serve.

title: our mother's cocoa cream pie
directions: Mix cocoa, flour, sugar and salt.
Add milk and egg yolks. Mix well.
Cook in skillet until thick.
Add vanilla and butter. Stir well.	Pour in baked pie shell.
Cover with egg whites (which have been beaten with 2 tablespoons sugar until stiff peaks form). Brown in oven until light brown.

title: chicken fillets parmigiana
directions: Flatten fillets and dip into milk-egg mixture and then bread crumbs with spices and grated cheese.
Saute fillets in hot oil until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Spread 1 cup sauce on bottom of 2 shallow greased baking dishes.
Pour remaining sauce on top of fillets arranged in pans or dish.
Top with sliced cheese and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Freeze 1 dish.
Serve other after baking at 350° for 45 minutes.
Bake frozen dish 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cheryl's sirloin roast
directions: Brown roast on all sides in hot oil in a large Dutch oven; remove meat and set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in drippings. Add roast, hot water, catsup, vinegar, brown sugar, salt and bay leaf in Dutch oven.
If handles are not ovenproof, cover with aluminum foil.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours or 225° for 6 hours or until roast is tender.
Remove and discard bay leaf. Remove roast from Dutch oven; cut into serving size pieces and place on a warm serving platter.
Measure liquid in pan; for every one cup liquid, combine 2 Tbsp. flour and 2 Tbsp. water; stir well.
Stir flour mixture into hot liquid in pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until gravy is smooth and thickened.
Serve with roast.

title: baked potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a well-greased casserole. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until firm. Exact time will depend on depth of potatoes in casserole.

title: cream cheese kifli
directions: Mix softened cheese and butter. Add flour; mix together well. Make into balls and refrigerate an hour or so. Roll each ball out on lightly floured board. Fill with filling of choice. Bake on greased cookie sheet in preheated 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Easy! Delicious! Makes 28 to 30 Kifli.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix together; shape into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: easy cappuccino
directions: In a large measuring cup, combine Taster's Choice, hot chocolate mix and water and mix well.
In blender container, process milk at high speed until foamy.
Pour coffee mixture into heat-proof mugs.
Top with frothy milk and sprinkle with cinnamon. Yields 5 (6 oz.) servings.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook veggies, hot water, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder.
Cool 10 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir in 2 cups pulled apart bread pieces. Reserve for topping.

title: honey barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side down, in single layer in baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Combine remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour over chicken and bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes. Turn pieces and bake for 20 to 30 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: hillbilly casserole
directions: Cook and drain elbow macaroni.
Brown hamburger, onion and 4 strips of green pepper.
Combine macaroni and meat mixture with tomato soup, cream style corn, American cheese, salt and pepper. Bake in greased casserole with dots of butter on top 1 hour in a 350° oven.
This freezes well, baked or unbaked.
Put in 2 small casseroles.
Use one and freeze one.

title: kathleen's pumpkin tea bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Shape ingredients into volcano shape.
Mix all wet ingredients together, then pour in volcano.
Mix until smooth.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans (or cupcakes).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: madona salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, pineapple and dry jello; bring to a boil.
Set aside to cool.
Mix cream cheese and baby food thoroughly.
Whip topping as per directions on package.
When jello mix is cooled, mix in cream cheese mixture.
Fold in topping and chill.

title: oven roasted onions
directions: Grease
two 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pans with 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Cut onions crosswise into 3/4-inch thick slices.
Place onion slices in single layer in pans.
Mix 2 tablespoons of olive oil with 1 teaspoon of salt.
Brush onion slices with half of oil mixture.
Place pans in oven and roast at 400° for 45 minutes.
Watch closely!

title: dirt cake
directions: Chop cookies in blender.
Set aside.
Set out cream cheese for one hour.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Set aside. Make pudding according to package directions.
Add cool whip to pudding.
Add cream cheese and sugar to pudding.
Layer cooking and pudding mixture in flower pot, starting and ending with cookies.
Add gummy worms throughout or on top.
Can be made without flower pot and gummy worms.

title: haluski(cabbage and noodles)
directions: Boil egg noodles in salted water; drain and mix with 1/2 stick of melted oleo.
Saute chopped cabbage, minced onion, salt and pepper with 1 stick oleo until transparent.
Add to noodles.
Heat and serve.

title: all-in-one hamburger casserole
directions: Spread rice on bottom of a greased 2-quart casserole.
Mix flour, chili powder, salt and pepper together.
Sprinkle 1/3 mix over the rice.
Dot with 1/2 tablespoon butter.
Mix hamburg and onion.
Spread over rice.
Repeat flour mixture and butter as before.
Make a layer of tomatoes, including liquid..
Repeat flour and butter.
Spread corn on top.
Dot with remaining butter. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and mandarin oranges. Combine all ingredients together; chill and serve.

title: homemade creole seasoning
directions: Mix together.
Store, tightly covered, at room temperature. Use in meats, fish, vegetables and soups.
Makes 1/4 cup.
Use 1 teaspoon per pound meat.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla for 1 minute.
Add mix.
Mix well and cool mixture for at least 45 minutes.
Place 1-inch balls about 3 inches apart and flatten with fork.
Bake approximately 8 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: apple-celery salad
directions: Mix horseradish and mayonnaise and toss with other ingredients.
Cover and place in refrigerator until serving time. Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: pot roast meat loaf
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large bowl.
Shape mixture into a loaf in center of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Place vegetables in layers around meat.
Sprinkle each layer with parsley and black pepper.
Cover casserole tightly with foil. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Remove foil; bake 10 more minutes to brown meat.

title: sausage dressing
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Cook onion and celery in oleo.
Mix together.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Spread thawed potatoes in 12 x 9-inch dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade cocktail sauce
directions: Mix everything together.
Good served on little necks.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Cook cake as directed in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle pecans on top after baking.
Punch several holes with fork in cake.
Blend Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut.
Put over top of cake.
Cool in refrigerator.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Best if kept refrigerated a couple of hours before serving.

title: raspberry dream
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over water in small saucepan; let stand 1 minute.
Cook over low heat, stirring until gelatin dissolves. Set aside.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, almond extract and salt; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth and creamy. Gradually add milk and gelatin mixture to creamed mixture.
Beat cream until soft peaks form.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Pour into a slightly oiled 4 cup mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold dessert onto serving dish and spoon Raspberry Sauce over dessert. Yield:
8 servings.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook beef, chicken and pork in water to cover in saucepan until tender.
Drain saucepan, reserving broth.
Cool and shred meat.
Cook tomatoes, potatoes, beans, corn and onion in reserved broth in saucepan until tender.
Add meat, catsup, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, salt and cayenne pepper.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours or to desired consistency.
Chill for several days and reheat for best flavor.
May substitute canned vegetables for fresh, if preferred.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: "chinese almond cookies"(serve these traditional cookies with hot tea.)
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt together into bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Add egg and almond extract; mix well.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese in heavy metal 2-quart pan on medium heat.
Add vanilla and cocoa.
Stir well until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar.
Mix well until smooth.
Fold in nuts and spoon into buttered pan or dish.
Spread and let cool completely before cutting into squares.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3 cups water.
When cool add fruits.
Pour 1/2 in a pan.
Spread sour cream over the top.
Add other half of fruit.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces and cook.
Mix soups, tomatoes, onions and broth to make sauce.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch greased pan:
chips, chicken, sauce and cheese, ending with chips and cheese for topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: midwest chops and potatoes
directions: Sprinkle chips with seasoning salt and pepper. Brown both sides in hot vegetable oil in large skillet; set aside. Stir together soup, milk, sour cream, half of cheese and half of onions. Add hash browns and mix well. Pour mixture in 9 x 13 casserole dish. Lay pork chops on top of mixture. Cover with foil and cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until chops are tender. Uncover and add rest of onions and cheese. Cook for 15 minutes until cheese melts and onions are crisp.

title: fudge
directions: Start on high.
When starts to boil, reduce to medium heat. Cook until hard ball forms in water, about 4 or 5 minutes after it starts bubbling, never reducing heat.
Remove.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: cheese things
directions: Line oblong pan with peppers.
Mix cheeses and eggs well. Pour over peppers.
Cook at 400° for 30 minutes.
Can use half of recipe.

title: golden cornbread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients into bowl.
Add egg, milk and shortening.
Beat with eggbeater until smooth, about 1 minute.
Do not overbeat.
Bake in greased 8-inch square pan in hot oven (425°) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 9 servings.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to package directions.
Set aside.

title: easy banana-nut muffins
directions: Melt margarine; blend in sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and lemon juice.
Break up bananas and add, mixing until batter is nearly smooth.
Add flour, soda, salt and chopped pecans.
Fill muffin cups (spray with cooking spray or line) 2/3 full; top each with pecan half.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 jumbo or 16 to 18 average-sized muffins.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar and flour in top of a double boiler; blend in milk, a small amount at a time.
Add water; cook, stirring to a boil.
Beat egg yolks lightly, beat small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Add egg yolks to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Add salt and 1 teaspoon vanilla; remove from heat. Cool custard for about 10 minutes.
Layer half the wafers, half the bananas and half the custard in baking dish; repeat layers.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add 2 tablespoons of sugar and remaining vanilla, beating until meringue is stiff and glossy.
Spread meringue over pudding.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: 3 day pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and pour 1 gallon water to 1 cup lime.
Let stand overnight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and cook just tender, taking care not to overcook. Combine soup, sour cream, squash and carrot.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing mix.
In a large buttered casserole dish, layer stuffing and squash mixture, repeating layers and ending with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beth's chile cups
directions: Saute sausage meat and cook.
Add chilies, salsa and cheese. Spray mini-muffin pan with baking spray; individually fit wonton wrappers into pans as a shell.
Spoon in filling.
Cook at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Garnish with sour cream and chopped scallions before serving.

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift flour and set aside 8 teaspoons.
Have butter and cheese at room temperature.
Add salt and pepper and gradually work flour in until all is mixed well.
Put in a cookie press or make your own design.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: cherry nut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except paraffin and chocolate chips; chill.
Make into balls and chill.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: three-cheese potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in baking dish coated with nonstick spray. Combine Parmesan and 3/4 cup of each cheese and sprinkle over potatoes.
Top with bacon, butter, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° until tender.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: marinade for chicken or turkey
directions: Use boneless, skinless meat.
Mix lemon juice and garlic. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Turn 2 to 3 times.
Broil, bake or grill as usual.

title: fig cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light; add eggs, beating after each.
Stir in vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and quarter potatoes lengthwise. Place in a 3 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients except chicken stock.
Coat potatoes evenly with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add chicken stock and bake 1/2 to 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Turn potatoes a few times while baking.
Near the end of the baking time, dust the potatoes with flour.
Place them under broiler until nicely browned.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: chop suey - chicago style
directions: Trim skin and excess fat off meat.
Brown in hot shortening in heavy skillet; add onion and continue browning.
Pour off excess shortening and cover meat and onion with water.
When it begins to boil, add chopped celery, salt, pepper, soy sauce, molasses and sugar.
Simmer about 2 hours.

title: crab quiche
directions: Mix together and pour into 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: supreme beef roast
directions: Place roast in roasting pan.
Sprinkle salt over roast.
Pour soup in pan.
Add water.
Place in preheated oven of 150° to 200°. Cook for 6 to 8 hours.
Check at 5 1/2 hours and turn roast in pan. Finish cooking.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions, using 3 cups cold milk, then fold in half of Cool Whip.
Place a layer of vanilla wafers, then bananas and then the filling.
Do each layer until all of filling has been used.
Garnish with the remaining Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate.

title: quick yellow cake
directions: Blend flour, sugar and oleo.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat for 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Add eggs and beat 2 minutes. Bake in greased and floured 8-inch pans, 30 to 35 minutes, at 350°.

title: wassail
directions: In large crock-pot, combine juices and sugar. Mix well. Add cinnamon sticks and allspice. Poke cloves into orange and add to mixture. Cook on high for 1 hour, then low 4 to 8 hours. Serve hot.

title: delicious pie crust
directions: Mix well
flour, Crisco, sugar, salt and baking powder. Add egg, water and vinegar.
Makes 3 two-crust pies.

title: dixie lollipops
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin.
Dissolve completely.
Let stand to cool for 15 minutes.
Pour into 4 paper cups. Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture.
Melt 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons butter in a large skillet; add chicken, several pieces at a time, and brown on both sides.
Remove chicken from skillet; place in a lightly greased shallow roasting dish.
Set aside.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and put in casserole.
Melt cheese and butter together and pour over Veg-All. Crumble crackers on top.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and pour over top. Cook at 350° until cheese bubbles and the top is brown.

title: swiss steak in onion soup
directions: Pound flour and pepper into steak.
Brown in skillet.
Remove to casserole and pour soup over meat.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 and 1/4 hours.
Uncover and bake another 15 minutes.
Top with parsley.
Delicious!

title: barbecued hamburgers
directions: Pour oil into large pan.
Add onions and peppers.
Season to taste.
Cover and steam about 10 minutes, then add 1 bottle of catsup plus 1 bottle of water, 1 bottle chili sauce plus 1 bottle water and 1 small can tomato sauce plus 1 can water.
Simmer, uncovered, for about 15 minutes.
Mix and brown hamburgers and add to sauce.
Cook until hamburgers are done (well cooked).

title: refrigerator sliced cukes
directions: Cover with water 2 hours.
Drain and mix 1 1/2 cups sugar and mix until dissolved.
Add 1/2 cup vinegar.
Mix well.
Put in refrigerator.
May be frozen but let stand a day or two before you freeze.

title: red or green punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
For red punch, use cherry Kool-Aid.
For green punch, use lime Kool-Aid.
Chill. When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Serves 25.

title: chili pie
directions: Press crescent rolls into a 9-inch pie plate. Brown in oven at 350° until slightly brown. Brown ground beef and chopped onion, then drain. Mix with refried beans and chili mix. Pour mixture into crust and sprinkle with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Coat potato slices on both sides with cooking oil.
Season with salt, pepper and
parsley flakes.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until tender and lightly browned.

title: red cabbage
directions: Microwave bacon slices until brown. Take crumbled bacon and drippings.
Slice onion and saute.
Add bay leaves and cloves. Put shredded cabbage on top of this mixture in the crock-pot.
Add water, apple, salt and sugar.
Close lid and simmer until soft. Season with vinegar and sugar to taste while simmering in crock-pot.

title: butternut drops
directions: Cream butter, vanilla, lemon juice, rinds and sugar thoroughly. Beat in egg yolk.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to the creamed mixture mixing until blended.
Drop mixture by 1/2 teaspoon into egg whites which have been slightly beaten.
Roll in nuts. Place on greased cookie sheet 1-inch apart.
Press half candied cherry on top of each.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 72.

title: trifle cake
directions: Prepare and bake 2 layer chocolate cake.
With a thread, slice both cooled cakes in half.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Marinate chicken 4 to 5 hours or longer.
Grill over low heat. Slice very thin.
Serve with flour tortillas and any of the following:
shredded lettuce, tomato, sour cream, guacamole, shredded Cheddar cheese, steamed green peppers, onion or salsa.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Let set.
Put marshmallows on top of set Jell-O.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a large oblong pan (14 1/2 x 8 x 2-inch), layer in order: chicken, mixed vegetables and sliced eggs.
In saucepan, heat together broth, margarine and soup.
Pour this mixture over layers.
Mix together flour, milk, baking powder and salt.
Mix well and pour evenly over ingredients in pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Add all other ingredients.
Form into walnut sized balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: carrot and apple casserole
directions: Peel and cook carrots until tender.
Spread carrots and apples in flat casserole dish.
Sprinkle sugar and spices on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Tastes good with pork or poultry.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: colcannon
directions: Cook cabbage, covered, in a small amount of boiling salted water 5 to 7 minutes or until tender.
Drain and set cabbage aside.
Cook potatoes in boiling salted water to cover 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add butter and next 3 ingredients; mix well.
Add cabbage, stirring well.
Serve immediately.

title: easy black forrest cake
directions: In flan, bake half the batter of the chocolate cake mix. (Freeze the other half or make two flans).
Bake the cake and cool.

title: micro chicken casserole
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, put the soup, green onions and salt. Arrange the chicken, heavier pieces to the outside.
Cook 16 minutes.
Rearrange chicken halfway through.
Add the frozen vegetables, which have been rinsed and thawed.
Cook 4 to 8 minutes more.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Place apples in buttered casserole.
Mix all other ingredients and spread on top of apples.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine first three ingredients and soak at least 8 hours or overnight.
Drain and rinse.
Combine all other ingredients.
Make sauce and add veggies and simmer 30 minutes.
Place in sterilized jars and seal.

title: party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In open roasting pan, melt margarine in oven.
Stir in all the ingredients, stirring all pieces until coated.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towel to cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 4 cups.

title: old-time beef stew
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meat in shortening, turning often.
Add 2 cups hot water, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, onion, bay leaves, salt, sugar, paprika, pepper and allspice or cloves.
Cover; simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally, to keep from sticking. Remove bay leaf and garlic.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Slowly blend 1/3 cup cold water and flour together.
Stir slowly into hot stew mixture. Cook and stir until bubbly.
Cook and stir 3 minutes longer. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: beef stick
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread ground beef in a flat dish. Cover and refrigerate all day.
Mix again the second day.
Mix again the third day.
Mix again on the fourth day.
On fourth day, roll into sticks the size you want and place on a broiler pan in the oven.
Cook 12 to 13 hours at 350°, turning every 2 hours. Crack oven door slightly during this process.

title: tropical punch
directions: In large pitcher, combine punch mix with water.
Stir to dissolve.
Add orange juice and diet ginger ale.
Serve over ice. Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: In a small bowl, combine buttermilk and soda; set aside. Using a sharp knife, slice dates, pineapple and raisins into tiny pieces.
Place chopped fruits and nuts in large mixing bowl. Dredge with 1 cup of the flour; set aside.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: In a salad bowl stir together the sliced cucumbers and onion rings.
In a small bowl, stir together the sour cream, sugar, vinegar and pepper.
Pour over cucumbers and onion.
Toss lightly to coat.
Cover and chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Stir the salad before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Spread oleo on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place pieces of beef over this. Arrange chicken over beef.
Repeat until desired amount.
Combine sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken and bake at 275° until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer lettuce, cauliflower and onion in a large bowl.
Place on top, fried crisp bacon.
Mix cheese, mayonnaise and sugar. Pour on top.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Toss together one hour before serving.

title: doodle cake
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Tear cake in small pieces and set aside. Crush candy bars. Set aside. Mix egg yolks, butter, sugar and vanilla with mixer on low speed until well blended. Stir in Cool Whip. Layer cake on bottom. Add some filling, then candy. Repeat layers until all used up, ending with candy.

title: golden cheese toast
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Mix together cheese, eggs, Worcestershire sauce, salt and dry mustard in a bowl and set aside.
With a glass or pastry cutter, cut bread into 3-inch rounds.
Spread with cheese mixture.
Cut bacon slices in 1/2. Top each round with a 1/2 slice of bacon.
Cook in oven 15 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Serve.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well before placing on low heat. After the mixture begins to boil, stir occasionally.
Cook until the syrup will form a soft ball in cold water.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until it begins to thicken.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
This must be done quickly or it will be too thick.
It may be poured into a buttered dish and cut into squares.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs until blended.
Add sugar, melted margarine, flour, milk and vanilla.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch pie pans or 1 (10-inch) pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Let set until cool.

title: bakewell cream biscuits
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add shortening and mix with pastry blender or fork.
Add milk all at once and stir quickly. Some flour may need a bit more milk to make soft dough.
Turn onto floured board and knead 5 to 6 times.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 475° for 5 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel, core and grate apples in large mixing bowl.
Pour sugar over apples and let stand 10 minutes.
In the meantime, sift flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Mix with nuts.
Add eggs and margarine to apples.
Combine the two mixtures.
Place in greased pan and bake at 350° approximately 1 1/4 hours for Bundt pan or 1 hour for 2 loaf pans.
Check for doneness approximately 15 minutes before time is up.
May be served warm or cool.

title: cream puffs(from home ec class of 1940)
directions: Combine shortening
and
water	in saucepan; bring to a boil. Drop in
all
the flour at once; stir until the mixture forms a ball
in the center of the pan.
Remove from heat; let cool 15 minutes
or
more.	Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat each time until
mixture goes together again.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet; do not flatten.
Give plenty of room. Bake at 425° for
minutes, then at 325° for 40 to 60 minutes.
(Don't look in oven first 10 minutes.)

title: quick salad
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Cover and chill 2 hours.

title: punch
directions: Make tea as directed.
Combine the the first 6 ingredients. Pour into 2 (1-gallon) milk cartons; freeze until very firm.
To serve, break up frozen juices.
Add the orange juice, ginger ale and frozen strawberries.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix this up and bake in oven for 1 hour.

title: people chow
directions: Melt together.
Add 1/2 box Crispix cereal.
Place in bag and shake with 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar.

title: savory pie
directions: Beat eggs in a bowl; add all ingredients.
Stir.
If ingredients are sticking together, add another egg.
Fill pastry that was previously prepared in a spring-form pan.
Spread out filling and smooth; top with crust.
Push down over filling.
Trim with scissors.
Brush dough with egg; prick with a fork.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: ravissant
directions: Cut steak into 1/3 x 5-inch strips.
Heat margarine in a large skillet and stir-fry steak strips until brown.
Add onion. Sprinkle with seasoning and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir well and then add tomato juice.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: chocolate angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add salt and cream of tartar and beat until peaks form.
Add sugar slowly, beating until very stiff. Add vanilla.
Grease a large glass pie plate.
Pour and arrange as crust.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes in 300° oven.

title: hoot-nanny cake
directions: Grease Bundt or angel food tube pan and flour.
Mix cake according to directions on box.
Place 1/3 cup of pecans on bottom of pan.
Pour 1/3 of cake mix batter over pecans; sprinkle 1/3 of cinnamon and sugar mixture over cake batter.
Repeat this procedure until mixture is gone.
Heat oven to temperature given on cake mix box and bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese in microwave and add picante sauce and hamburger.
Serve with chips or veggies.

title: coquille st. jacques
directions: In saucepan, saute scallops on low heat for 10 minutes.
Drain in sautepan.
Cook together mushrooms and onions in margarine until tender.
Add soup, wine, parsley and scallops.
Heat and stir occasionally, keeping pan covered.
Spoon into individual baking dish or clam shells.
Top with bread crumbs.
Place under broiler until browned.

title: 100 hole cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on box.
Add dry pudding to cake batter.
Bake cake.
Turn upside down and let cool.

title: pear honey
directions: Peel, core and cut pears in French fry size.
Place in a large pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook to a preserve state.

title: coconut dessert
directions: Add ingredients in order and mix well.
Pour into Pyrex pie pan and bake at 325° until golden brown or straw tests clean. Serves 8.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1-inch Pyrex pie dish. Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper; put in dish.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick until smooth.
Pour over meat. Bake for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven; top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake about 10 more minutes.

title: baked meat balls
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients.
Shape into golf ball sized balls. Place in 2-quart casserole. Mix mushroom soup with water and rest of ingredients. Pour over meat.
Cover.
Bake in moderate oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef with onions, garlic and seasoning salt.
Drain; add soups and water.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: joy's sweet fried carrots
directions: Clean and scrape carrots.
Slice carrots in 1/2-inch lengths. Cook until very tender.
After carrots are tender, add brown sugar.
Let carrots stand for about 1 hour.
Drain sugar off carrots.
Melt butter in skillet; saute carrots.
Makes a great side dish for fried rice.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Spoon into a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, milk, eggs, spices and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: red lobster cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Combine biscuit mix, milk and cheese with wooden spoon until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop dough by heaping tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 450° oven 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.
Before removing from cookie sheet brush melted butter and garlic powder over warm biscuits. Serve warm.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: german chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sweetened condensed milk and beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over graham cracker crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until center is set.
Cool.
Top with Coconut Pecan Topping.

title: leeza's chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar, and vanilla until creamy. Beat in eggs. Gradually beat in flour, soda, and salt. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop by tablespoonfuls
onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9 - 11 minutes at 375 until edges are brown and centers feel gooey.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar (to which cornstarch and nutmeg has been added).
Add Karo syrup and beaten egg yolks, then cream. Pour in 9-inch pie shell and bake at 400° until done.
Check pie by inserting knife in center of pie, when knife comes out clean, pie is done.
Beat the egg whites and add 1 tablespoon sugar for each white, adding gradually when whites are stiff.
Keep beating while adding sugar.
Spread over pie being sure the edges are sealed good.
Bake until lightly browned.
(This is a delicious pie but rich.
Cut in real small pieces.)

title: easy cranberry sauce
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine glaze, berries and juice.
Over medium to high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook 10 minutes or until berries are soft, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Pour into a bowl.
Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve with cooked pork, ham or poultry. Refrigerate
any remaining sauce.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Please chicken in a 9x12 baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream, pour over chicken.
Mix cracker crumbs, poppy seeds, and melted butter.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Butter bread and cut into small cubes. Place in bottom of buttered 13 x 9-inch dish.
Sprinkle sausage over top of bread cubes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Combine remaining ingredients, beating well and pour over top of sausage and bread.
Chill at least 8 hours.
Bake at 350°
for 40 to 50 minutes, covered, except for last 10 minutes so to allow browning.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter. Add cheese and sour cream. Add seasonings. Put Tater Tots in casserole dish. Pour mixture over potatoes. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Uncover and bake 20 minutes longer. Serves 8.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in airtight container until used.
Mix 2 or 3 tablespoons mix to cup of hot water for single cup servings.
Great for large gatherings or holiday parties.

title: chicken lasagna(microwave recipe)
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Saute onions and margarine.
Add soup, mushrooms, milk and parsley.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer alternately noodles, soup mixture, cottage cheese, chicken and cheeses.
Microwave 12 minutes at 80% power.
Let cool before serving.

title: hot crab meat dip
directions: Combine the cream cheese with milk, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix with crab meat and onion.
Put in small baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve cool with fresh apples.

title: old mexican chili
directions: Brown stew meat in oil; add onion and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and water.
Stir, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: crescent roll dessert
directions: Put 1 can of rolls in bottom of 9 x 13 inch dish or pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Pour over rolls.
Put other can of rolls on top of this.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top of rolls.
Then sprinkle brown sugar on top of cinnamon.
Melt butter and drizzle on top of sugar.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: easy spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain. Add rest of ingredients and simmer 30 minutes (or however long it takes to boil the water and cook the spaghetti or vermicelli). Enjoy!

title: apple butter
directions: Quarter and core apples but do not peel.
In a 3-quart glass bowl, combine apples and cider.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes until apples are soft.
Transfer to blender.
Blend until smooth.
Return to glass bowl.
Combine with sugar and spices.
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes until mixture thickens.
Store in jars.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in two greased loaf pans for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Poke holes in loaves with skewer when taken out of oven and while warm.
Pour glaze over top.

title: baked shrimp in cream wine sauce
directions: In heavy pot, melt 1/4 pound butter and saute all seasonings until done, 5 minutes.
Add flour and blend well.
Add cream, stirring constantly, until thick.
Season to taste.
Add wine.
In a separate saute pan, saute shrimp in 1/2 cup butter and garlic until done.
Remove shrimp and drain well.
Place shrimp in a layer in a heavy casserole dish.
Top with wine sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake until bubbly.
May also serve over pasta.

title: shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Measure flour and salt into sifter and sift together.
Add brown sugar and mix well.
Add butter to bowl in chunks.
Use pastry cutter to mix butter into flour until you have pea sized lumps.
Use your fingers to work the butter into the flour until the mixture is smooth.
Press shortbread into pan. Use a fork to prick the shortbread all over.
Bake for 20 minutes until light brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix and bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Cover with sugar; let stand for several hours.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add orange juice, pineapple and remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise.

title: garlic cheese grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in water until thick (quick grits cook in 5 minutes, regular grits take about 20 minutes).
Mix egg, margarine and cheese with grits and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until crusty on top.
Serves 6.

title: quickie peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Beat well. Pour peaches (sweetened) over butter, but don't stir.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon goop
directions: Combine all ingredients together; beat at high speed with an electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Fill 2 loaf pans 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (until top of loaf is brown).
Let cool only slightly (10 to 15 minutes), then pour/scoop baked mixture into a bowl.
Gently stir it once or twice to mix cake/liquid; let cool for 30 minutes.
It is best served warm or at room temperature.
This recipe is actually a mistake!
The original recipe passed to me called for a small package of vanilla pudding and a baking time of 45 minutes.
In that form, it becomes a sweet loaf of bread and is quite good, especially when spread with cinnamon butter.
The goop form, however, is a lemonier bread pudding and makes for a richer dessert, especially suited for the fall or winter.

title: bran bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add dissolved yeast and water. Knead.
Set to rise in moderate temperature for 3 hours.
Knead, put in pans and let rise until dough doubles in size.
Bake 45 minutes in moderate oven.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients. This can be made ahead of time. Pie filling keeps bananas from discoloring.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Chilled cookie dough often crumbles when you slice it.
But if you first warm the blade of your knife in hot water and then wipe it dry, you can avoid the crumbling.
When the blade cools, warm it again the same way.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix, Jell-O and Crisco oil.
Add apricot nectar, eggs and lemon and lemon peel.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (varies).

title: pea salad
directions: Boil peas 2 minutes; stir in rice and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
When serving, decorate with strips of ham and cheese.
Keep refrigerated.

title: thumbprints
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, 1/2 teaspoon salt and vanilla.
Beat well.
Gradually add flour; mix well.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls, dip in egg whites and roll in nuts.
Place 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Press down centers with thumb; make a small well in each.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool and remove from pan.
Fill centers with preserves.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Brown onion in small amount of butter and set aside.
Cook chicken with bay leaves until tender.
Skin chicken and mix in large bowl the tomato sauce, mushrooms, green pepper, garlic salt and paprika.
Cook spaghetti and set aside.
Add mixture of chicken and other ingredients to onions in skillet.
Simmer with broth from chicken.
Bake in oven for about 15 minutes at 350°. Serve with Parmesan cheese, tossed salad and French bread.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Pour into greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and crumbs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: collard greens
directions: Wash and remove stems from greens.
Boil ham hock or salt pork for 1 hour in water.
Tear leaves into bite sized pieces.
Add greens, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook greens slowly until tender.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: cappuccino cooler
directions: In blender container place coffee, ice cream and syrup. Cover; blend until smooth.
Serve immediately over crushed ice. Makes about 4 six ounce servings.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in 3 layers.

title: lemon whipper snappers
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and drop by spoonfuls into the powdered sugar.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sunset salad
directions: Mix together and chill.
This makes a lot.

title: ground beef soup
directions: Mix all ingredients except rice.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Add rice and cook until done.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: czech dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Beat eggs and water together.
Beat into sifted ingredients with wooden spoon.
Beat for 10 minutes.
Stir in bread cubes.
Divide dough in bowl in half with wooden spoons.
Shape into 2 ovals and drop into rapidly boiling water.
Cook in covered pan for 20 minutes, turning dumplings over after 10 minutes.
Remove from water and drain.
Slice immediately with knife or thread.
Makes 2 large dumplings, enough for about 6 servings.

title: praline cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients in order as listed.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: frosted salad
directions: Dissolve jello in
boiling
water
and	then add ginger ale. Add bananas, pineapple and marshmallows.
Let set.	Make topping by combining 1/2
cup
sugar
and 2 tablespoons flour. Stir in 1 cup pineapple
juice
and
egg (slightly beaten). Cook in double boiler until
thick.

cool, fold in 1 cup Cool Whip and frost over
lemon
layer.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup shredded American cheese, if desired.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Boil first three ingredients for 15 minutes.
Strain and add the remaining ingredients.
Serves 6.

title: holly cookies
directions: Melt together butter and marshmallows.
Add vanilla and coloring.
Pour over cornflakes.
Drop by teaspoon.
Add red hots. Let stand 24 hours.

title: frosted chocolate brownie supreme
directions: Beat margarine at medium speed until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar; beat well.
Add egg whites, milk, sour cream and vanilla; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients together, then add to creamy mixture, mixing well.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack. Spread with Creamy Chocolate Frosting.

title: onion-dill bread
directions: Mix all first 9 ingredients well.
Add flour last and mix. Turn out on lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place dough in greased bowl and turn to grease all sides.
Cover; let rise until double, then half.
Place each half in loaf pan and let rise again until double.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: no peek stew
directions: Place ingredients in casserole.
Cover and bake in a 300° oven for 3 1/2 hours.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: julie zalar's rye bread
directions: Break yeast into water.
Add sugar and let stand until foamy. Make a well in flour.
Add salt and 2 tablespoons oil.
Add foamy yeast mixture.
Mix with wooden spoon, adding enough lukewarm water to form dough.
Mix well.
Let rise 10 to 15 minutes.
Then knead dough and place it in a greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Form 4 round loaves.
Grease and flour 4 pie plates.
Place loaves on pie plates and let rise until doubled in size.
Brush top of loaves with milk.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt and soda, add alternately to mixture with milk.
Add bananas and pecans; mix well.
Cook at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (makes 3 loaves).

title: texas cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Pour 1/2 stick in bottom of 9 x 12 pan.
Layer all of the
above ingredients in order given and then pour rest of butter on top. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sliced potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; let cool.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Place the potatoes into mixture.
Do not stir because the potatoes will break.
Ready to serve.

title: pork chops gumbo
directions: Spread mustard on both sides of chops.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides.
Cover with the soup plus 1/2 cup water.
Simmer about 1 hour until tender.
This dish is wonderful served with mashed potatoes.
It makes a delicious brown gravy.

title: red devil's food
directions: Butter a 9-inch square cake pan and dust it with cocoa.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut in butter.
Add buttermilk.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut biscuits with 2-inch cutter.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Cook pasta.
Mix hamburger, pasta and sauce together.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until cheese melts.

title: chocolate chip fudge candy
directions: Mix the sugar, milk and butter and cook by clock for 8 minutes.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, pecans and vanilla.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet or wax paper. When cool, cut into squares.
Makes 6 pounds.

title: pralines
directions: In large 6 quart boiler, mix sugar, buttermilk, soda and salt.
Cook over High heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Turn heat to Medium and add butter and pecans.
Cook, stirring occasionally until mixture forms soft ball in cold water.
Drop onto wax paper.

title: flour tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix the first four ingredients together and then spread on whole tortillas.
Roll up and chill.
Slice into 1-inch pieces. Serve with salsa.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix the whipped topping, sugar and peanut butter together; pour into the pie crust.
Garnish with chocolate shavings or miniature chocolate chips.
Chill for two hours.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla to sour cream.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with liquid to creamed mixture.
Chill and roll cookies as thin as desired.
Cut into various shapes.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: baked pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and keep 3 tablespoons juice; combine sugar and flour and stir in the 3 tablespoons juice in small bowl.
Mix cheese and pineapple chunks and pour in the juice mixture.
Spoon in a greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine butter and crackers and pat on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Shape all ingredients, except nuts, into a ball.
Cover outside with crushed walnuts.

title: steak fingers
directions: Cut round steak into 1-inch wide strips.
Dip in eggs and milk mixture in which you have added a little garlic powder, Lawry's seasoned salt, pepper and salt.
Roll in flour until steaks are well coated.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: wine rabbit
directions: In small roasting pan, layer bottom with parsley, sage, rosemary, salt, pepper and onion.
Rub rabbit in vegetable oil. Lay on top of seasonings.
Repeat seasonings and onion on top of rabbit.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Add 1 cup white wine cover and cook for another hour.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Put ingredients in saucepan.
Boil for a couple of minutes. Slice hot dogs.
Put in baking dish.
Pour sauce over hot dogs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: southern-style baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Cook	macaroni as package directs; drain.
To hot macaroni in same saucepan, add remaining ingredients except	1/2 cup of cheese.
Mix well.
Over medium heat, cook	and

5 minutes or until cheese melts. Turn into greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup of cheese.	Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: peach crescent rolls
directions: Separate crescent rolls according to package directions.
At the small end of each triangle, place a peach slice, adding 1 teaspoon of peach preserves to each.
Roll each into a crescent shape.
Bake according to package directions.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Melt butter, dip chicken into butter, then into mixture of 4 dry ingredients.
Place chicken into well-greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter, cover with foil.
Bake
for 45 to 50 minutes.	Remove foil last 5 minutes of cooking.

title: lila barger icebox rolls
directions: Bowl #1:
Mix sugar, water and yeast.
Wait approximately 5 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cherry jello cheese cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup sugar and butter (save a little for top).
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cream cheese; mix jello and water; let cool.
Add jello mixture to cream cheese and whip.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pan. Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Chill well.

title: championship chocolate chip bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugar; cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir in 1/2 cup chips; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
In same bowl, mix milk, egg and vanilla; add remaining 1 1/2 cups chips and nuts.
Spread evenly over crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly golden brown.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage, drain and cool.
Cook bacon, drain and cool. Beat eggs and milk together.
Add bread, salt and mustard.
Stir in sausage and cheese.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan, sides sprayed with Pam.
Refrigerate overnight.
One hour before serving, sprinkle paprika on top.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: elegant caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter or margarine. Add brown sugar and bring to a boil. Boil exactly two minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and bring back to boiling.
As soon as it has again reached the boiling stage, remove from heat and add the powdered sugar and flavoring. Beat until smooth.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Crush Ritz crackers.
Put half in bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan. Steam veggies and put in pan.
Melt cheese with milk and pour over veggies.
Top with remaining crackers.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until top is browned.

title: walnut molasses pie
directions: Fold under extra pastry and crimp the dough on edges all around.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl combine eggs, corn syrup, sugar, butter, molasses and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in walnut pieces.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer bread cubes, meat and cheese in a 9x13 casserole dish. Stir milk and mustard into beaten eggs.
Pour over layers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for one hour, uncovered.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, drain and set aside.
In covered saucepan cook soup mix, rice and water for 7 minutes.
Then combine all ingredients and place in baking dish.
(Can prepare the day before needed.)
