Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Good served with mushroom gravy.
Yield:
8-10 servings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, butter and cream cheese.
Add the sugar gradually and cream together until fluffy.
Add eggs, 2 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add the flour, baking powder and salt to cream mixture.
Mix well.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 315° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Serves 16.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread the bean dip on bottom of shallow casserole bowl.
Mix up the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning together.
Layer on top of beans.
Next, layer the cheese, olives, onions and tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: quick fudge
directions: Melt morsels and milk.
Take off heat and add other ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Thoroughly
mix
the ingredients, except the applesauce and soda.
Add	hot applesauce, unsweetened, in which you have dropped 2 teaspoons soda.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate flake candy
directions: Combine pecans, dates, corn flakes and salt.
Melt chocolates together in double boiler; pour over corn flake mixture.
Mix well, slightly crushing corn flakes.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Chill several hours.
Keep in a cool place.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Mix eggs and fruit cocktail together.
Add sugar; mix well. Sift flour, salt and baking soda together.
Add dry mixture to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: impossible crab quiche
directions: Butter pie plate.
Mix crab and vegetables in plate.
Blend eggs, milk, sauce and biscuit mix for 15 seconds.
Pour over vegetables and crab.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool a little before serving.

title: sugar-free fruit salad
directions: Use only fruits in their own juice.

title: patsy's triple chocolate cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes in greased and floured Bundt cake pan (40 minutes for 13 x 9-inch pan).

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream oleo, salt and sugar. Add one egg at a time, beating after each addition.
Add lemon rind. Sift flour with baking powder.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with milk.
Then stir in nuts.
Bake in well greased loaf pan at 350° for 55 minutes. Place pan on cooling rack and spoon mixture of juice of 1 lemon and 1/2 cup sugar over hot loaf.
Cool in pan.
Remove, wrap in foil and place in refrigerator.
Allow to ripen for 2 to 3 days.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a 10-inch pie pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: easy black beans and rice
directions: Heat black beans.
Saute a little garlic, onion and green pepper in a small amount of olive oil.
Add to beans.
Just before serving, add a splash of red wine vinegar.
Serve over rice.

title: quick rhubarb cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Then add diced rhubarb.
Heat half stick of margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake until lightly browned.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.

title: frozen rum punch
directions: Blend pineapple and cherries in blender. Pour in a large bowl with the rest of the ingredients.
Freeze at least 24 hours before serving.

title: giant cream puff
directions: Boil water. Add margarine. Take off heat when melted. Add flour. Then add eggs one at a time. Spread into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Cool. Mix instant pudding with cream cheese and milk. Spread on cooled crust. Top with regular Cool Whip. Spread over pudding. Sprinkle all over with Magic Shell.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; then add other ingredients. Bake in 1 deep dish pie shell at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes on lower rack. Do not overbrown.

title: cheesy meatball supper
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, eggs, milk, salt, pepper, bread crumbs, parsley and oregano; mix well.
Shape in 1 inch balls.
In large skillet, brown meatballs in a little shortening on all sides.
Drain off excess fat.
Combine soup, water and wine.
Add to meat in skillet.
Cook, covered, over low heat 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix with hot cooked spaghetti.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.
Serves 6.

title: meat rolls
directions: Cook hamburger; drain.
Add onion, salt and mustard; sprinkle with a little flour to hold together.
Prepare Bisquick as for rolls.
Roll out Bisquick like a jelly roll.
Spread with meat mixture and roll up.
Slice in 1 1/2-inch slices and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Top with white or brown gravy and enjoy.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, cool and slice into a baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with celery and parsley.
Mix tarragon vinegar, cider vinegar, olive oil or bacon fat and lemon.
Heat to the boiling point.
Remove the lemon and pour the dressing over the potatoes.
Cover and let stand in a 350° oven until heated (about 10 minutes).
Serves 6.

title: potatoes casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except corn flakes and 3 tablespoons butter.
Pour into a large baking dish about 9 x 13-inches.
Sprinkle with corn flakes and top with melted butter. Bake for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: cole slaw
directions: Chop the cabbage and onion by hand and place in large bowl.

title: unbelievable lasagna
directions: Grease 13 x 9 pan. Mix ground beef, spaghetti sauce and parsley. Spread 1 cup sauce to cover bottom of pan. Cover with 3 uncooked noodles. Top with 1 1/2 cups sauce, 1/2 cottage cheese and 1/3 Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses. Be certain all noodles are covered with sauce. Repeat noodles, sauce and cheeses 2 more times, ending with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan. Cover tightly; refrigerate overnight.

title: liver and onions
directions: Cut liver in strips and lightly flour.
Slice onions.
Saute onions in butter or margarine until soft.
Remove from skillet and put aside.
Brown liver on both sides.
Add 1 to 2 cups of wine and let simmer on low to medium heat until tender.
Add peas and cooked onions and cook another 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream
butter, sugar and eggs.	Add flavoring and soda. Add sifted flour and buttermilk alternately.
Pour in floured and greased tube pan.
Bake 2 hours at 275°.

title: mini blintzes *
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together cream cheese, egg yolk, sugar and vanilla.
Cut crust off bread and roll each slice thin. Spread each slice with cream cheese mixture and roll up.
Dip each roll in melted margarine and roll lightly in cinnamon-sugar. Freeze for one hour on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: vanilla chiffon cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, oil, water, egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat about 5 minutes at high speed.

title: scallops and pasta
directions: Saute scallops in margarine until opaque.
Add seasonings. Serve on cooked noodles.

title: janik's pretzels
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, 1/4 cup warm milk, 1/4 cup water, malt and yeast.
Knead; let rise 10 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon salt, sugar, oil, 1/4 cup warm milk, 1/4 cup water and remaining flour. Knead until dough is not sticking to hands (add more flour if necessary).
Let rise 30 minutes.

title: hash potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potato chips.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place in ungreased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery together. Add the rest of the ingredients. Put in a greased casserole pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Sprinkle some chow mein noodles on top of casserole before serving.

title: red apples
directions: Mix sugar and jello and sprinkle over apples. Bake 10 minutes in microwave or 40 minutes in a 300° oven. Great cold.

title: shrimp christina
directions: Clean and devein shrimp.
Place the shrimp in a large bowl and combine with the vegetable oil, olive oil, minced garlic, pepper and bread crumbs.
Mix until the shrimp are well coated. Refrigerate for approximately 2 hours.
Grill the shrimp until they are golden (about 2 minutes on each side).
Squeeze fresh lemon juice over the shrimp after they are taken off the grill. Serve immediately.

title: cold pickled beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1/2 cup juice to dilute vinegar.
Put sliced beets in a jar; sprinkle with salt and sugar or Equal. Heat vinegar and beet juice until boiling.
Pour over beets. Cool.
Keep in refrigerator several hours before serving.
Will keep a week or longer.
Fresh thin sliced onion rings may be added, if desired.
Can also be made in a dish.

title: easy cheese sauce
directions: Melt the fat and blend in the flour and salt.
Stir in the milk, slowly.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Cream oleo; add sugar and cream.
Add eggs one at a time.
Cream well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with mashed banana mixed with milk and lemon juice.
Add nuts and vanilla; blend.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Divide batter between two pans.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Roll in balls and press on cookie sheet.
Bake in 325° oven.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until clear.
Add broccoli and soup. Simmer 5 minutes.
Add cheese and rice; mix well.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican stuffed shells
directions: Cook and drain pasta shells. Brown meat and drain. In small bowl, mix sauces and water. Stir 1/2 cup sauce in meat mixture along with chilies, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions. Mix well. Spread 1/2 of remaining sauce on bottom of 10-inch round pan. Stuff cooked shells with meat mixture. Arrange shells in dish. Top with sauce. Bake, covered, for 30 minutes. Top with remaining onions and cheese. Bake, uncovered 5 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: appetizer's crabmeat
directions: Cut muffins in half; set aside.
Mix together crabmeat, butter, cheese, mayonnaise and garlic salt.
Spread on sliced muffins.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 minutes, then broil a few minutes.
Do not burn.

title: quick quiche
directions: Grease 9x13 inch baking dish.
Cover bottom with lasagna noodles.
Add layer of meat sauce, then layer of cottage cheese mixture, then mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
The top layer should be sauce and parmesan cheese.
Bake 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix well and freeze in small bowls.
Let set 45 minutes before serving.
Pour ginger ale on top.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs, then add dry ingredients with buttermilk, alternately along with flavors.
Bake in four 9-inch pans in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 4-layer cake.

title: mixed greens
directions: Boil neckbones in water about 30 minutes or until tender.
Pick greens.
Wash greens 3 times or until water is clean.
Put greens in the pot with neckbones.
Boil on low for 2 hours.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add salt, sugar and bell pepper.
May add turnip if desired.
Slice 4 turnips.
Wash and add to greens.
Let greens cook on low with turnips 1 hour.
Cook greens 2 hours.
Cook neckbones 30 minutes before adding greens.

title: golden hush puppies
directions: Combine.
Mix well.
Carefully drop by tablespoonfuls into deep hot oil.
Cook only a few at a time, turning once.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: sunshine chicken(serves 6)
directions: Combine curry powder and paprika. Sprinkle over chicken. Rub seasonings onto top and bottom surface of each chicken piece and set aside.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, green pepper and onion together.
Add salt to taste.
While this mixture is browning, boil noodles according to package directions.
When meat mixture is browned, pour off grease and add cubed cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and bake in a 2-quart casserole for 30 minutes at 300°.
Casserole can be frozen and baked later.

title: tailgate salad
directions: Bring the sugar, oil and vinegar to a boil.
Pour over the vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Keeps up to 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: richie's shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery; drain off fat.
Drain tomatoes, green beans and carrots thoroughly.
Combine with meat mixture lightly to mix.
Add pepper and garlic.
Place this mixture in a baking dish.
Cover with prepared mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly warmed.
Remove from oven; top with cheese and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: spring dip
directions: Do Ahead:
Stir cream into cottage cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: ma's christmas cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake mix by directions on box or you can make your favorite yellow cake from scratch.
You will need 3 layers.

title: venison shanks with herbs
directions: In a heavy skillet, brown shanks on all sides in 1 tablespoon butter.
Add 1 1/2 cups water and salt.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 1 hour.
In a small skillet, add flour to 2 tablespoons butter; cook and stir until flour is brown.
Stir in 1/2 cup water until smooth.
Add to meat and stir until smooth.
Add herbs. Cover and cook slowly 1 more hour until meat is tender.
Add more water during cooking if needed to maintain a good gravy.
Place shanks on a bed of hot cooked noodles.
Spoon gravy over them. Serves 4.

title: surprise preserves
directions: Peel ripe figs, trimming off the stem completely.
Sprinkle with sugar and add enough water to start cooking (about 1 or 2 cups).
Use wide kettle.
When figs reach boiling point, mash. Cook until mixture thickens.
Stir in strawberry gelatin.
Cook until desired consistency.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal while hot.
Makes 5 pints.

title: orange tapioca pudding
directions: Mix puddings, Jell-O, orange juice and water.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Cool completely.
Then add Cool Whip and fruit.

title: eggs for a bunch
directions: Saute onion, green pepper, ham and mushrooms in butter.
Beat eggs and milk until frothy, then scramble in butter.
Mix together scrambled eggs and sauteed ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cream of mushroom soup and Velveeta or American cheese.
Bake in a 225° oven until bubbly and heated through.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box. Bake in 9 x 13 glass dish. Cool. Drain pineapple; spread pineapple over cake. Mix pudding according to package directions. Spread pudding over pineapple. Spread Cool Whip over pudding. Spread coconut over pudding and sprinkle nuts over coconut.

title: sweet 'n sour carrots
directions: Saute pepper and onion in oil.
Boil carrots until almost done.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to carrots.
Simmer until hot.

title: daily bread
directions: Heat water to boiling; add instant potatoes.
Mix well.
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to warm.
Add yeast.
Heat cottage cheese to lukewarm and add soda.
Add eggs and mix all liquids well.
Add flour to make stiff dough.
Knead.
Let rise until double.
Knead again.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Punch down and let rise for 10 minutes.
Shape into loaves and let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 5 loaves.

title: pat's pineapple cheese pie
directions: Whip cream cheese and sugar together well.
Fold in whipped cream, then pineapple. Pour into pie shell and chill 2 hours or until set.

title: billy goat cookies
directions: Add water to raisins and boil for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Stir in soda and let stand.
Crem the sugar and shortening.
Add vanilla, eggs and cold raisins.
Stir in other ingredients, leaving the flour until last.
Bake at 400° on greased cookie sheet for 12 minutes.

title: baked chicken with marinara sauce
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in brown bag.
Add chicken a few pieces at a time and shake until coated with flour mixture.
Place chicken in a single layer in a shallow baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour the sauce over the chicken.
Sprinkle with dill and grated cheese. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 minutes more.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Spray a 2-quart casserole with a vegetable oil.
Place in it a mixture of the cranberries and apples.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Cover with sugar.
In a medium mixing bowl, blend just to moisten the oatmeal, walnuts, brown sugar and melted oleo.
Pour crumb mixture over fruit.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Delicious with turkey, chicken or served hot over ice cream.

title: lawn spray
directions: Mix all.
Spray lawn and plants about once a month.
NO bugs, no critters!

title: aunt maudie's noodles
directions: Beat egg yolks, salt, butter and milk together.
Add flour. Roll out thin and cut in thin strips.
(No need to let them dry.)

title: individual meat loaves
directions: In a bowl, beat egg. Add milk, Worcestershire sauce, onion salt, pepper and crumbs. Add pork and mix well. Shape into two 5 x 2 1/2-inch loaves. Place in a small baking pan.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add raisins and nuts to flour mixture.
Add to batter.
Add applesauce last.
You might need to add the applesauce a little at a time to mix better.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan in 325° oven 1 hour and 20 minutes or until tests done.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients; cut in margarine until mixture becomes coarse.
Then add buttermilk and egg.

title: holly taters
directions: Wash, but do not peel potatoes.
Cut into wedges.
Mix dry ingredients and put into plastic bag.
Add potatoes and shake well to coat.
Potatoes should be damp, so coating will stick.
Put on cookie sheet.
Dot with margarine.
Bake for 1 hour in 400° oven, uncovered.

title: blender peanut mousse
directions: In saucepan, heat 1/2 cup milk just to boiling.
In blender, sprinkle gelatin over 1/2 cup cold milk.
Let stand 2 minutes. Add hot milk. Blend 1 minute. Add 1/2 cup peanut butter pieces.
Blend until melted.
Add sugar, cream and 3 ice cubes.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into 4 dessert dishes.
Freeze 20 minutes. Garnish with remaining peanut butter pieces.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Fold in oranges.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Fold in bananas and sprinkle with nuts.
Yields 8 servings.

title: bread sticks
directions: Cut each roll into 4 pieces, lengthwise.
Melt butter.
Season with garlic, thyme or dill.
Bake in slow oven at 225° about 1/2 to 3/4 hour, until as brown as you wish.
Good served hot or cold.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour in oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: golden glow congealed salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water.
Combine other ingredients and add to jello.
Put in refrigerator until congealed.
Serve.

title: mama lou's swedish oatmeal and fruit
directions: Mix together the night before serving and refrigerate the oatmeal, mild???, raisins, honey and salt.

title: salad bowl puff
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Heat water and margarine to boiling in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add baking mix, all at once.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 1/2 minutes, remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, continue beating until smooth.
Spread in pie plate (do not spread up side).
Bake until puffed and dry in center, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Just before serving, fill with ham salad.
Cut into wedges.
Serves 6 to 8. Bowl puff may be frozen after it has cooled from baking.
Wrap and freeze no longer than 1 week.
To thaw, put puff on serving plate.
Let stand at room temperature for 60 minutes.

title: play doh
directions: Combine all ingredients, except food coloring, in saucepan. Heat on medium-high and stir until thick.
Turn off heat.
Add food coloring.
Knead on flat surface until mixed and good texture (carefully, mixture will be hot).

title: cookie dough ornaments
directions: Mix and knead dough for 7 to 10 minutes.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased pan.
Place hole in ornament with toothpick.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Paint with acrylic colors.
Spray with clear gloss or lacquer.

title: creamy cauliflower soup
directions: Heat 2 cups water, cauliflower, celery, onion and lemon juice. Cook until tender, about 10 minutes. Do not drain.
Press cauliflower mixture through food mill or blender until uniform consistency.

title: ma's spaghetti
directions: Simmer all ingredients together for a couple hours, stirring occasionally.
Skim fat off top.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: In Dutch oven, make dark roux with peanut oil and flour; add onions, celery and green pepper and saute for about ten minutes. Add tomato paste, then all liquids, and then all spices and chopped tomatoes.
Simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add more wine, if necessary.

title: delicious lemon bars
directions: Mix cake mix and margarine together.
Pat in greased sheet cake pan.
Mix frosting and cream cheese together.
Set aside 1/2 cup of icing.
To the remaining mixture, add the eggs and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and spread remaining icing on top of bars.

title: flank steak fix-up
directions: *Cut lightly in a crisscross pattern; usually done by your meat retailer.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until
tender;
drain
and
mash. Beat eggs.
Add milk, cheese, butter, salt and pepper.
Add to squash and onions.
Blend in stuffing
mix with a spoon.
Pour into 2-quart buttered baking dish.
Bake
until	done, but not dry, about 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chicken wings
directions: Melt butter in heavy medium saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients except chicken and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange chicken in ovenproof glass baking dish.
Brush with sauce.
Bake 15 minutes and brush with sauce again.
Continue baking until crisp, 15 to 20 minutes. Reheat sauce.
Serve immediately.

title: curried chicken rice salad
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Add chicken and celery; mix well. Mix rice and pimento, layer with mixture.

title: spicey chicken soup
directions: Mince one chile and heat in oil in pan, add next 4 ingredients and saute 4 minutes.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Bring to boil and then simmer 3 minutes.
Serve with crushed corn chips or shredded monterey jack cheese on top.

title: pound cake
directions: In mixing bowl, cream oleo, shortening and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Add flour and milk, alternating and beginning with flour.
Add baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Grease and flour tube pan generously.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: snicker cake
directions: Mix cake mix
according
to directions on box; pour 1/2 of batter into greased
and
floured 9 x 13-inch pan.	Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
While cake cooks, melt the stick of butter and	caramels in microwave.	Add the evaporated milk and mix until
well
blended.
Remove
cake from oven and pour caramel mixture
over
cake.
Sprinkle
chocolate
chips
over caramels. Pour rest
of batter over chips and bake another 20 minutes.
Be sure
not
to
overbake.
(Nuts
may
be added to caramel mixture, if desired.)

title: succotash
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add in salt and pepper to taste. Heat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: olive-cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese and butter in mixer. Add sauces and mix.
Add flour and mix.
Press teaspoon of dough around an olive.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hot chili beans
directions: Brown
hamburger.
Drain
grease.
Pour meat into large saucepan.
Add
both packs of chili mix, picante sauce, kidney beans, chopped onions and tomato soup or tomatoes.	Simmer for 10 to	15
minutes.
Taste.
Add Texas Pete to desired taste. Simmer 5 more minutes.
Garnish chili with shredded cheese, if you like.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour the juice off into a pan and add pudding mix.
Cook until thick.
Cool lightly and add other fruit.
Chill.

title: tuxedo brownie hugs cookies(makes approximately 5 dozen cookies)
directions: Remove wrapper from Hugs|.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well and flour cookie sheet or line with parchment.
Stir brownie mix, pouch of Hershey|'s syrup, cocoa, water, oil and eggs in medium bowl until well blended.
Drop by scant teaspoons, onto prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes or until set.
Cool 1 minute.
Press Hug| into center of each cookie.
Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.

title: caramel corn(cracker jacks)
directions: Boil
brown sugar, margarine, syrup and salt 5 minutes. Remove from
heat and add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour over corn and peanuts.
Stir
until well mixed.
Spread on 2 large cookie sheets and bake 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes while
baking. Remove
from
oven and continue stirring until cool.
Store in airtight containers.

title: oriental salad
directions: In large bowl, combine cole slaw mix, almonds, sunflower seeds and green onions; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine oil, sugar, vinegar and seasoning packets.
Pour dressing over salad; toss to combine.
Refrigerate several hours.
When ready to serve, crush Ramen noodles and stir into salad.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and dry Jell-O.
Mix well.
Add cottage cheese, drained pineapple and nuts.
Refrigerate.
Let set before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend
peanut
butter,	egg,
vanilla
and butter until mixture becomes light and fluffy.
Sift together the flour and soda;
blend into creamed mixture.	Add remaining ingredients. Drop
by
spoonfuls on cookie sheet and press with fork.
Bake in a
350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes until light brown around edges. Makes about 3 dozen large cookies.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Melt butter in sauce pan on low heat; gradually add brown sugar and corn syrup. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly for 1 minute or until sugar dissolves. Add whipping cream gradually and bring to a boil again. Remove from heat. Makes about 2 cups.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and let cool.
Dissolve shortening in boiling water and let cool.
Mix two mixtures together.
Add sugar, eggs and salt; beat.
Gradually add 6 cups of flour.
Let rise until double in size, then knead dough for 10 minutes.
Roll dough out to 1/4 to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut dough in small pieces (to look like dumplings).
Dip each piece of dough into melted margarine.
Distribute pieces evenly into tube pans and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Wrap bread in foil to keep fresh.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Arrange asparagus in the bottom of shallow 6 1/2 x 10-inch baking dish.
Combine cheese and soup.
Mix well and add peas. Spoon over asparagus.
Top with almonds.
Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
May be frozen and reheated.
Reduce heat to 375° to reheat and you may need to cover with foil.
If I know I am going to freeze them, I reduce the baking time 2 to 4 minutes.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Combine sugars, flour and oatmeal in bowl.
Cut in peanut butter.
Add egg, vanilla and melted margarine.
Mix well.
Press into a well-greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add icing as soon as it is removed from oven.

title: frank burgers
directions: Combine hamburger with egg, Worcestershire and salt.
Blend well and press around each frankfurter.
Cook 15 minutes on grill, turning often.
Serve in frankfurter rolls.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt oleo and then add eggs, mix well.
Add dry ingredients one at a time, add nuts last.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cut up orange slices and flour then mix other ingredients well. Then add orange slices, dates, and walnuts. Pour in several small cake pans or bundt pan.
I usually make this at Christmas time. Bake at 325-350° for about 40 minutes. Keep check on it.

title: joy mann's dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients; divide in 3 parts.
Roll very thin; dry for 20 minutes.
Cut in strips.
Cook until tender.

title: padua bean casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add chili powder, garlic salt and onion.
Blend together refried beans and enchilada sauce.
Add to meat mixture. Add corn chips.
Place in casserole and top with extra corn chips and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter until smooth.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour, milk and pecans.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Combine powdered sugar and milk.
Roll cookies in the sugar mixture and then in coconut.

title: hot-milk coconut pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
After cake comes out of oven, take a fork and make holes all over cake.
Bring milk and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 can of coconut, then spoon this all over cake. Drain pineapple and spread over cake.
Refrigerate cake and after is is completely cool, mix the other 1/2 can of coconut with Cool Whip and spread over cake.

title: tomato-garlic vegetable soup
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, combine chicken broth, potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, cauliflower, green beans, 2 teaspoons salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Add Great Northern beans and zucchini. Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.

title: california zucchini bake
directions: Saute beef, zucchini, onions and seasonings in a lightly greased skillet, until vegetables are tender-crisp, stirring frequently.
Drain, add green chiles, rice, sour cream and 1 cup cheese.
Turn into a buttered shallow 2-quart casserole.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Stir in all ingredients except 1 cup pecans.
Turn into bowl lined with waxed paper and chill. Shape into ball and unwrap; roll in remaining cup of pecans. Re-wrap in plastic wrap and keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: beef barbecues
directions: Cut beef in chunks.
Cover and simmer 4 to 6 hours.
Shred.

title: fruit loaf
directions: Mix butter and sugar well.
Add the eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Mix baking powder and lemon rind with half of the flour and mix well with butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix walnuts, candied peel, raisins and cherries in rest of the flour.
Mix all together.
Grease a loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crumb cake
directions: Grease and flour 12 x 17-inch pan.
Make cake mix from box mix for 4 minutes.
Bake for 17 minutes at 375°.
Mix butter, flour, sugar, cinnamon and vanilla by hand until it starts to crumb.
Put crumbs on top and bake again for 17 minutes.
When cool top with confectioners sugar and cut.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper in skillet.
Cook 1/2 hour slowly.
Add beans, tomatoes and spices.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 4 to 5 hours.

title: pineapple refresher
directions: Drain and rinse ditalini with cold water.
Cook pudding using 1 egg only.
Add everything together and chill for several hours.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Mix together and
let
stand until juice appears.
Cold pack for 15 minutes.

title: lemon "brownies"
directions: Cut butter into powdered sugar and flour until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Press into 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes in a 350 degree oven.
While baking, mix eggs, sugar, flour, and lemon juice.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake 20 minutes longer at 350 degrees.
While still hot, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips, and spread into a 9 x 13 pan. Melt 1 large bag of semi-sweet chocolate chips and spread on top. Cut into squares.

title: swiss steak ranch style
directions: Cut round steak into 6 pieces.
Pound flour into the meat. Brown well in shortening.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add garlic and onion and continue cooking until the onion is tender and browned.
Add paprika, onion salt and water.
Cover and bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 2 hours, or until meat is tender. Add more water if necessary.
Makes 6 servings.

title: raspberry french toast(casey's favorite)
directions: Marinade raspberries in liqueur overnight.
Whip softened cream cheese together with raspberry mixture and almonds.
Spread this mixture between two pieces of bread.
Heat and grease skillet with butter.
Dip in egg mixture and cook both sides until golden brown.
Place on the plate, cut into quarters and dust with powdered sugar.
Lightly drizzle with maple syrup and serve.

title: party fruit freeze
directions: Gradually
add mayonnaise to cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add fruit and food coloring.
Fold in marshmallows
and whipped cream.
Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Freeze until firm.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into two 9-inch pie shells.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for approximately 40 minutes.
So good and so easy.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in boiling water, cook over direct heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils. Set over boiling water and cook 10 minutes longer.
Beat egg yolks slightly, beat in a little of hot mixture and add to hot mixture in double boiler.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from hot water.
Blend in butter, lemon juice, rind and pulp.
Cool.

title: venison roast
directions: Boil roast with pepper and salt until tender.
Place in baking dish.
Top with onion which has been sauteed in bacon drippings, catsup and mustard.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare Uncle Ben's wild rice as directed on box. While preparing rice, saute onions, celery, green pepper and mushrooms in margarine.
To the prepared rice, add the soup (undiluted), pimentos and sauteed ingredients.
Mix well and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You may add 1 can of chunked chicken or hamburger, if you wish.

title: edna's fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine together sugar, salt, cocoa, corn syrup, milk and butter.
Cook to a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and stir in marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Beat and stir in nuts. Pour into a buttered pan and let sit.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar.
Put in refrigerator.
Cream sugar and butter together until well blended. Add egg yolks, 2 at a time.
Alternate cream and flour and mix well until creamy.
Add vanilla and fold in egg whites from refrigerator.
Beat on high speed with mixer for 10 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and carrot and pepper real fine. Mix all ingredients together.

title: william and frances' 7 layer salad
directions: In a deep casserole, layer lettuce, celery, onion and green pepper.
Top with Miracle Whip.
Next layer will be the peas.
Top them with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Then top with bacon and follow with grated cheese over top.
Refrigerate until served.

title: prospector's sourdough bread
directions: Mix ingredients
in a crock-pot or glass jar and set in a warm place
to
sour.
When
it
sours
and
really
gets to bubbling, add
a
little
flour,
some sugar and a teaspoon of soda (these last
ingredients
are
in addition to the listed ingredients). This is
a
very old recipe and you may have to do a
little testing and some experiments!
Mix until a stiff dough,
adding needed
flour.
Put in a pan or Dutch oven and let
rise.
This can
take 16 to 18 hours or more.
Bake in a moderate oven until done.

title: holiday spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour 13 x 9-inch baking pan; set aside.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon in water (large pot).
Add broccoli and cook until well done.
In a saucepan, make a roux.
Melt butter; add onions and cook until limp.
Sprinkle flour over onions, stirring with wire whisk until all is stirred in, then add milk.
Stir; thicken and add to soup stock.
Add cheese and spices and cream.

title: white icebox icing
directions: Cook sugar, salt, syrup and water until spins a long thread. Remove from heat; add cream of tartar.
Pour over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Beat well, then add powdered sugar and extract.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix Jell-O, sugar and cornstarch in pan until smooth.
Add boiling water.
Mix.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and turns deep red.
Remove from heat and cool about 10 minutes.

title: coney sauce
directions: In a large pot, simmer all the ingredients together until thick, then add 4 or 5 chopped up hot dog franks.
Simmer 15 minutes longer.
Very good on hot dogs.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in mixer.
Fold poppy seed in by hand. Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in casserole.
Mix the soup, broth and Veg-All; pour over chicken.
Mix the flour, butter and buttermilk; pour over chicken.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix together the jello, water, pineapple and pie filling. Chill.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and cover top.

title: good corn
directions: Drain corn; put in pan with remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Heat until cheese is melted; stir often.

title: orange frosted-carrot bars
directions: Mix flour,
baking
powder
and
salt;	set aside. Beat butter, sugar,
eggs
and
vanilla until fluffy.
Stir in carrots, nuts
and
flour
mixture just until blended.
Spread in greased 13 x
x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake on center rack in preheated 350°
oven	for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly in pan on rack, then spread
Orange Frosting over top.
Cool completely and cut in 48 bars or smaller squares.

title: crazy crust pie
directions: Place butter in a 3-quart Pyrex dish in a 350° oven to melt. While melting butter, prepare batter.
Mix flour, 3/4 cup sugar and milk together and pour over butter.
Spoon fruit over batter, pouring juice over all.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 5 minutes. Gradually beat in sugar and lemon juice. Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt together.
Fold in pumpkin. Spread on greased and floured 15 x 10-inch pan.
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on Saran Wrap.
Place another piece of wrap on top
of cake.
Roll up together.
Cool.
Unroll and spread with filling.

title: melting moments - england
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Sift cornstarch, confectioners sugar and flour together.
Blend in margarine with spoon.
Mix until soft, smooth dough forms.
Shape into balls, logs or crescents.

title: favorite potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss lightly to mix.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn and eggs together thoroughly.
Mix flour and sugar well with milk.
Add corn and eggs to this mixture.
Dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening, eggs, honey, vanilla and lemon.
Mix buttermilk and teaspoon nutmeg; set aside.
Sift together 4 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Alternate, pouring buttermilk mixture and flour mixture into first mixture.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, use extra 1/2 cup flour to roll out dough.
Cut with cookie cutter 1/2-inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: zucchini pie("like apple")
directions: Cut up and cook zucchini until crunchy-tender.
Measure 4 cups.
Add the lemon juice and dash of salt.
Let set while measuring the remaining ingredients.
Put zucchini into mixture. It will be "soupy."
Pour into unbaked pie crust; dot with butter. Cover with crust.
Makes a 9-inch pie, like apple.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until browned.

title: quiche
directions: Mix together eggs, cream and cheese.
Add salt, nutmeg and onion.
Pour into crusts and bake at 375° until firm.
Brown crusts first.

title: poppy seed-nut roll
directions: Roll out bread dough into rectangle shape.
Cover with melted butter.
Combine walnuts, brown sugar, and white sugar in a bowl. Spread evenly and generously over dough.
Roll long side to long side.
Brush with melted butter again.
Cover and let double in bulk.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: Chop the tomatoes finely until almost pulp-like.
Add the diced, unpeeled cucumber, the chopped garlic, olives, onion, green pepper, oil, vinegar, seasoning and herbs.
Chill the mixture before serving.
Sprinkle with hard-boiled eggs.

title: orange glazed pork chops
directions: Stir contents of mix, 1-1/2 cups hot water, oranges and 1/4 cup margarine until mixture is moistened and set aside.
Spoon into a 8 x 12 baking dish - top with chops.
Mix marmalade and mustard, spread on chops and bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes or until chops are cooked thru.
Serves 4.

title: spiced cucumber rings
directions: Bring to a boil and stir until red hots dissolve.
Add cucumbers and boil gently about 30 minutes.
Remove pickles and pack into hot jars.
Bring syrup to a boil and simmer about 30 minutes.
Fill jars and seal.
Pickles can be left in syrup overnight, then brought to a boil next morning and put into jars and sealed.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix, adding corn and butter last.
Pour in greased casserole dish and cook at 450° until it begins to brown.
Reduce heat to 300° and cook until firm, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fried squash and onions
directions: *Can use Pam cooking spray.
Use several times during cooking time.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in water seasoned with the salt and pepper until the chicken is done and falling off the bones. Remove chicken from the water.
Set aside to cool.

title: grilled bass and vegetables
directions: Secret for "barbecuing" ribs without burning (no small trick) is to cover grill with foil. To keep them juicy, baste with beer, water or broth. The finishing touch is to baste ribs with spicy barbecue sauce until they are glazed. This combined with the charcoal flavor makes them irresistible.

title: vegetable parmesan casserole
directions: Drain beans and add pepper.
Combine beans, pepper, sour cream and mayonnaise; mix well.
Put in a 2-quart casserole; sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: solar tea(sioux narrows sunshine makes this especially good)
directions: Fill gallon glass container with cold water.
Add tea bags. Cover and place in the sun for 3 to 4 hours.
Remove tea bags and keep in refrigerator.
Add sweetener and/or lemon to taste.
Serve over ice.

title: sensational double-layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into mixing bowl; add pudding.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended (1 to 2 minutes).
Let stand 3 minutes.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla, cinnamon with flour. Add zucchini and
nuts
or
raisins.
Bake in muffin pans with paper cups for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 24.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: brownie cake
directions: Mix cocoa, salt, flour and sugar together.
Add melted margarine and eggs.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Flour and grease pan. Bake at 375 degrees for 35 -40 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir meats until brown.
Drain off fat.
Add tomatoes; break up with fork.
Stir in tomato paste, garlic salt, oregano leaves and basil leaves.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer uncovered 20 minutes or until mixture is consistency of spaghetti sauce.
Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together cottage cheese and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese. Set aside 1 cup of meat sauce and 1/2 cup of the Mozzarella cheese.
In ungreased baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, alternate layers of 1/3 each noodles, remaining meat sauce, remaining Mozzarella cheese and the cottage cheese mixture.
Spread reserved meat sauce over top; sprinkle with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle reserved Mozzarella cheese across lasagna.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti (break into 2 1/2-inch pieces before cooking). After spaghetti is cooked, rinse in hot water.
Combine all ingredients, saving some cheese for topping.
Put in casserole and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: spinach dip(for vegetables or chips)
directions: Place frozen spinach in a bowl; cover with Hellmann's mayonnaise.
Spoon chives and parsley on top.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Blend.
Serve with raw vegetables or potato chips.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding spinach last.
Chill and serve with raw vegetables.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Mix sugar and syrup together. Bring to a boil. Stir in butter, peanut butter and vanilla. Remove from heat and stir in corn flakes. Place on wax paper in small (about 1/4 cup) mounds to firm.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over the first mixture.
Let set in refrigerator 12 hours before serving. Will keep in refrigerator several weeks. Drain before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, syrup, vanilla, nuts and butter together. Mix flour and milk together and add to the other mix.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake real slow for 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: saltine candy
directions: Boil milk and sugar 3 or 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop on wax paper by spoonfuls.

title: wonder chicken
directions: Spread first three ingredients over chicken which has been placed in a casserole dish.
Bake 2 hours, covered, at 300°.

title: anadama bread
directions: In
a
large bowl mix 3 cups flour, salt, corn meal and yeast. Add
margarine
and gradually add hot water and molasses.
Beat 2 minutes with mixer.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough. Knead until smooth, about 8 minutes.
Put dough in
greased
bowl, turn dough, and grease top.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Crush crackers.
Put baking powder into crackers.
Add vanilla and salt into egg whites.
Beat until stiff.
Add sugar gradually; beat thoroughly.
Fold in crackers and nuts.
Put in slightly buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until light brown.
Cool.

title: fried okra
directions: Slice okra into 1/2-inch rounds.
In a paper bag, combine corn meal, salt and pepper; add okra and shake.
Fry in hot oil until okra is browned.
Drain on paper towels.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Cooking time:
15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and brown sugar until smooth.
Add vanilla and peanuts.
Stir well.
Chill.
Serve with any good apple.
It's delicious!

title: easy fudge pie
directions: Grease a glass pie plate with margarine.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, sugar and cocoa.
Melt margarine; mix with sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pie plate; bake for 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar and blend well with the melted butter.
Take pan from heat and cool.
Add unbeaten eggs and vanilla.
Beat vigorously with a wooden spoon.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix flour and sugar mixture together (pecans may be added).
Spread batter evenly in greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut in strips while warm and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 3 dozen bars.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until blended.
Add flour, then flavoring.
Place in cold oven.
Set at 350° and bake 60 to 70 minutes.

title: chili con caso dip
directions: Melt butter in medium frying pan.
Saute onion and tomato with 2 or 3 hot chili peppers.
Add cheeses with onion, tomato and peppers.
Stir over medium heat until cheese is melted.
Serve hot over tortilla chips. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: okra with cheese
directions: Wash okra well; drain.
Cut off tip and stem ends.
Cut okra crosswise into 1/2 inch slices.
Dip okra in egg, then in flour seasoned with paprika.
Fry in hot oil until brown and crisp; drain slightly.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir gently to coat.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: neenie's sugar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 300° until pie is well done.
Double recipe for 2 pies.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Cut chicken as for frying and fry slightly.
Remove chicken and stir flour into shortening in which the chicken was fried. Stir constantly until golden brown (not burnt).
Add onions and stir until soft.
Place chicken again in pot.
Add 9 cups of water (hot) and let simmer slowly.
Season to taste and add green pepper and celery.
Gumbo should be allowed to simmer 2 to 3 hours. About 1 hour before serving, add finely cut onion tops and parsley.
Gumbo file is put in as you serve your plate; a pinch or more can be added.
Never cook the file.
Serve with steamed rice. Serves 6 people.

title: diabetic fruit cake
directions: Bring shortening or margarine, cinnamon, Equal, raisins, dates, nutmeg, cloves, carrots and pineapple to a boil for a few minutes in the hot water.
Cool and add flour, soda, salt and nuts, if desired.
Mixture will be very stiff, so mix with hands. Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour at 300°.
Store in a cool place.
Will keep for a long time in the refrigerator.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple, then add other ingredients.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate; cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and coconut.

title: chicken and sun dried tomatoes
directions: Brown garlic in oil.
Add chicken, cook until white.
Add broccoli in pan; stir and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes (cut real small).
Add basil, pepper, wine and broth.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Cook then stir in pasta.

title: english toffee
directions: Spread well chopped pecans on bottom of an 8-inch square baking pan.
Melt butter slowly in a skillet.
Add sugar and water to melted butter, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil over high heat. Cook and stir until mixture turns light brown, about 5 minutes. Pour this mixture immediately over pecans and spread evenly to sides of pan.
Break chocolate bars into squares and place on hot toffee.
When melted, spread over toffee.
Cool; break into pieces and store in covered container.

title: chicken salad kabobs
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Cut chicken breasts into 1/2-inch wide strips.
Combine chicken and green onions in a shallow, nonmetallic container.
Combine pineapple juice and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over chicken mixture and toss.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Thread chicken, green onions and reserved pineapple chunks onto wooden skewers. Broil with skewers 5 to 6 inches from heat source, brushing with marinade often.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cook zucchini, onions and bouillon with a little water until tender.
Pour contents into blender and puree.
Pour mixture back into pan and add 1 cup milk.
Bring to a boil.
Garnish with fresh crumbled bacon bits and croutons.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream the first three ingredients.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla mix thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in cereal and nuts.
Roll into walnut-size balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Yields five to six dozen.

title: fudge
directions: Cook chocolate until melted; add milk and cook until thick. Add all ingredients.
Pour on buttered dish.

title: robbie's 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each.
Add
extract and flour.
Add 7-Up last. Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake
at
for 1 hour and 25 minutes. Don't open door
while cake is baking.
Let cool for awhile, then loosen from pan while still barely warm. Turn out of pan.
Keep under cake cover. Can be frozen.

title: nana's icebox cookies
directions: Cream
sugar
and
butter.
Add
eggs	and
beat.
Add vanilla.
Mix
rest
of
ingredients and add to the sugar mixture. Lightly flour wax and make 2 rolls of cookies.
Wrap in wax paper and Reynolds Wrap.	Place in refrigerator overnight. Next day, slice
and bake at 325° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: low-fat caesar salad
directions: Coat one side of each slice of bread lightly with cooking spray.
Sprinkle evenly with garlic powder.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cut into cubes and set aside.
Rub inside of a large salad bowl with garlic. Place lettuce in bowl.
Combine chicken broth, lemon juice, Worcestershire, anchovy and mustard in a small bowl, stirring well. Drizzle over lettuce.
Sprinkle salad with Parmesan cheese and cracked pepper.
Toss well.
Top with bread cubes.
Serve immediately.
Contains 82 calories, 27% from fat per 1 cup serving.

title: summer sausage
directions: Prepare turkey and stuff as you normally would.
Before you put turkey in the oven, lay uncooked strips of bacon to cover top of turkey.
This will baste the turkey while it cooks.
Turkey will cook up juicier and tender.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Put on bottom of a casserole dish. Pour pizza sauce on top of hamburger.
Put cheese on top of pizza sauce.
In a separate bowl; mix Bisquick, milk and eggs until smooth.
Pour evenly on top of cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.
Bake, uncovered.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; melt and cool chocolate.
Blend into butter and sugar mixture, then add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat for 5 minutes after each.
Turn into pie crust shell and chill for several hours.
Top with whipped cream, if desired. Add orange extract.

title: custard pie
directions: Put strips of foil around the edge of pastry.
Bake pastry for 5 minutes at 450°.
Cool.
Beat eggs; stir in other ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into pastry.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and bake 30 minutes longer at 350°.
Remove from oven and cool 2 hours.

title: hot dutch potato salad
directions: Dice bacon and fry.
Add chopped onion and green pepper.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add vinegar, salt, pepper, sugar and beaten egg.
Cook slightly; add cubed potatoes, grated carrot and hard-cooked eggs. Blend and serve.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Brown beef and onion; drain off fat.
Spread on pie plate.
Beat milk, Bisquick, salt, pepper and eggs until smooth.
Pour in pie plate and bake for 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, approximately 5 to 8 minutes.

title: sauerbraten (modern)(six generous servings)
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper together.
Coat roast with flour mixture.
Brown in Dutch oven in oil.
Add wine vinegar, wine, water, onion, bay leaf, cinnamon, allspice and cloves.
Cook on simmer 2 hours or until meat is tender (covered).
Remove meat from pan.
Add raisins and gingersnaps.
Cook until thickened.
Serve sauce over sliced meat.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Cook cranberries in very small amount of water until they pop. Run through strainer.
Add gelatin dissolved in cold water, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Heat to dissolve.
Pour into oiled mold to set.

title: leo's twinkie pudding
directions: Cut enough Twinkies lengthwise to cover the bottom of a 9 x 13 pan. Cook the pudding at a low temperature and then increase the temperature until you see the first bubbles. Remove from the heat and let cool for 5 to 10 minutes. Pour over the Twinkies. Place the pan in the refrigerator overnight or at least 3 hours. Spread the Cool Whip just before serving and sprinkle with a few nut meats on top. Make sure the pudding is cold before spreading the Cool Whip.

title: 14 carrots
directions: Cook carrots.
Make a sauce of rest of the ingredients, but crumbs and pour over carrots in casserole dish.
Mix 1/4 cup margarine with bread crumbs and put over sauce and carrots.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients except blueberries in bowl, mixing to blend.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon into greased and floured muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: zucchini-pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini. Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and blend well.

title: orange-pineapple delight
directions: Mix crackers, sugar and margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan (save 1 cup crumbs for topping).
In large bowl, mix together Eagle Brand milk and orange juice.
Add oranges and pineapple and fold in Cool Whip.
Spread mixture over the crumb crust.
Sprinkle reserved cup of crumbs on top.
Dot with maraschino cherries. Chill in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: jalapeno peppers
directions: Boil 5 minutes with peppers.
Enough for 1 jar.
Pack and seal.

title: baked apples
directions: Core and peel apples.
Garnish with the remaining ingredients. Bake in an 8 x 10-inch dish at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pie crust(stir and roll)
directions: Mix together in a bowl.
Roll between waxed paper.
Bake at 425°.

title: u.m.w.'s chickenetti(for "eight")
directions: Cook spaghetti as package directs; drain.
Mix chicken, pimento, soup, salt, pepper, broth and grated cheese.
Put in 9 x 11-inch casserole.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: On a sheet of waxed paper, combine flour and salt.
Dip eggplant into the milk and coat with flour mixture.
Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Combine in top part of a double boiler.
Both the egg whites and the water should be cold.
Set over briskly boiling water in the bottom of a double boiler.
After beating, about 3 or 4 minutes, add six large marshmallows.
Continue beating until the mixture will hold a stiff peak without falling to one side.

title: carol's banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in mashed banana.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to banana mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pig lickin' cake
directions: Icing:
Before baking your cake, blend by hand the Cool Whip, vanilla pudding and crushed pineapple.
Set in refrigerator and let cool until cake is done.

title: potato casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1 stick margarine.
Add to soup and sour cream. Pour over potatoes.
Add shredded cheese.
Crumble 1 individual package of Ritz crackers over top.
Add 1/2 stick margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: confetti salad
directions: Drain beans and corn; rinse in cold water.
Put ingredients in deep bowl with green peppers, celery, onion and pimento.

title: mock crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into cakes.
Fry in shallow oil.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender and drain.
Return to pan and add onion, sauteed in margarine.
Mix all other ingredients.
Put into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream butter and shortening well.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla; heat again.
Add hot milk a little at a time and continue to beat with addition of milk. When all ingredients are thoroughly mixed, beat for 15 minutes. Use a Mixmaster.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix squash, onions, peppers and salt together.
Cover with ice water for 1 hour, then rinse.
Mix in sugar, vinegar, turmeric and celery seed.
Then cook for 15 minutes.
Put in pint jars and seal.

title: brown sugar chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until center of pie is firm when shaken.

title: chinese
directions: Lightly saute minced onion, add rice and toss until the grains are covered, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Add beaten egg and stir-fry until cooked.
Add diced (small diced) meat and rareripes. Shake in soy sauce until rice becomes a light brown.
Stir constantly.

title: strawberry ice cream pie
directions: Mix well, jello,
gelatin,
water
and sugar until dissolved. Stir in
ice
cream
until	melted	and
smooth.
Add strawberries.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip (Cool Whip is what I use).
Keep in refrigerator.

title: tasty ground beef soup
directions: Wash and trim cauliflower.
Thinly slice the florets.
Set aside.
In medium saucepan, saute onion in the heated butter until onion is limp.
Add the garlic.
Saute 1 minute longer.
Crumble meat into pan.
Saute until browned.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in cauliflower, tomato sauce, water, broth, lemon juice, herbs and seasonings.
Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix in bowl flour and sugar.
Mix and bring to a boil cocoa, butter and Coca-Cola.
Remove from heat and cool slightly, then add buttermilk, vanilla and beaten eggs.
Mix well with spoon.
Add to flour and sugar.
Mix well with spoon, not mixer.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 to 35 minutes.
Immediately after removing from oven, spread one jar marshmallow cream over top.

title: lemony gingerbread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium bowl; beat at low speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Gradually add hot water, mixing well.
Add flour and next 8 ingredients; beat at low speed until blended, scraping bowl occasionally.
Beat at high speed 1 minute.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil cranberries, juice, water and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add jello, when dissolved add rest of ingredients.

title: black bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Best served at room temperature.

title: lemon loaded party cake
directions: Bake cake per box instructions in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
While cake is baking, mix the jello in boiling water.
Cool until cake is baked.
When cake comes from oven, poke full of holes (good size ones) with a fork.
Spoon jello into holes until used up. Refrigerate cake until cold and jello is set.
Beat pudding with 3 cups cold milk.
Spread over cake, then top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cracker snackers
directions: Combine dressing mix, dill weed, lemon-pepper and garlic powder.
Toss well.
Add crackers.
Drizzle oil over cracker mixture; toss well.
Place mixture in a large paper bag and fold closed.
Let stand for 2 hours, shaking bag occasionally.
Store mixture in an airtight container.
Yields 11 1/2 cups.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and taco seasoning as you would for tacos. Mix all ingredients into pot; simmer. Cook in crock-pot on high for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or on low for 4 hours. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix together oranges, sour cream and pineapple.
Fold in marshmallows.
Chill and serve.

title: festive corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter 9 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Melt 1 Tbsp. butter in medium nonstick skillet over medium low heat.
Add onion and saute until tender, about 10 minutes.
Cool. Mix cornmeal and next 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Add 7
Tbsp. butter and rub in with fingertips until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Whisk buttermilk and eggs in medium bowl to blend.
Add buttermilk to dry ingredients and stir until blended.
Mix in cheese, red peppers, basil and onion.
Transfer to prepared pan.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: Mix all together and chill. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Slowly cook the tomato sauce and pressed garlic for about one hour.
In a large bowl, mix beef, bread crumbs, Worcestershire sauce, eggs, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Use hands to mix and form into meatballs about 1-inch in diameter.
Cover with sauce and cook in a 350° oven until browned.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage over medium flame until done, stirring to crumble well; drain on paper towels and set aside.
Spread each slice of bread with margarine; cut into cubes.
Place bread cubes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; sprinkle with sausage and top with cheese. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over sausage mixture. Chill at least 8 hours.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayo, vinegar and sugar together and pour over the ingredients.
Let set for several hours.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to directions on box.
Using the jel-ring mold, put strawberries in first.
Put in angel food cake upside-down on strawberries.
Pour Jell-O over top of cake; use spatula to help cake absorb all the Jell-O.
Seal and freeze for 1/2 hour.

title: mock cheese souffle
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer bread and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over bread and cheese. Pour melted butter over top.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Set in pan of water and bake 45 minutes at 350°. Cover with foil for first 30 minutes.

title: better than kisses cake
directions: Bake the cake as instructed.
Cool for 45 minutes.
Poke holes with a fork.
Pour Eagle Brand condensed milk over cake; let stand for 45 minutes.
Pour the ice cream topping over cake.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: stuff
directions: In large skillet, layer the ingredients in order given.
Cover and simmer on low for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Do not stir.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and divide into thirds.
Use one-third to cover bottom of flower pot or deep bowl.
Cream margarine and cream cheese.
Set aside.
Mix pudding and milk, then fold in on low speed Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Combine with cream cheese mixture.
Use half of the cream mixture on top of first layer of cookie crumbs.
Layer cookie crumbs, then cream mixture, being sure cookie crumbs are on top.
Chill.

title: chocolate crispies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside. Beat butter, sugars and egg until creamy; add Choco-Bake.
Add rest of ingredients and stir together well.
Drop by tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until firm.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: captain's soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until vegetables are done.
Serve with Italian bread.

title: strawberry cheese dessert
directions: Beat cream cheese, 2 tablespoons milk and 2 tablespoons sugar until smooth.
Spread onto crust.
Add a layer of strawberries.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: In a medium bowl, whip cream with electric beaters until stiff peaks form, adding powdered sugar, vanilla and corn syrup near the end of beating.
Cover and refrigerate.
Clean beaters.
In another medium bowl, combine instant pudding and milk, then beat for 2 minutes at low speed, until thickened.
Fold whipped cream into pudding mixture until well blended.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan with squares of graham crackers.
It will take about 15 squares.
With a spatula, spread 1/2 pudding and cream mixture over crackers.
Top with another layer of graham crackers.
Refrigerate. Melt chocolate chips in a bowl in a microwave oven.
Stir sour cream until smooth.
Remove chocolate from oven and stir sour cream and salt into it until it makes a smooth, shiny icing.
Take cake pan from refrigerator and smooth icing over top with thin spatula or spreader.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight allowing time for graham crackers to soften.
Use a sharp knife to cut into serving pieces.
Wiping blade clean between cuts.
Makes 16 servings.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into unbaked crust. Bake at 350° until crust is golden brown.

title: cheesy hash brown bake
directions: In bowl, combine potatoes, soup, sour cream, 1 3/4 cups Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese. Transfer to a greased 3-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining Cheddar cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until bubbly and cheese is melted. Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: forget 'em cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) at high speed of an electric mixer until foamy; add salt. Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold vanilla, chocolate chips and pecans into beaten egg whites.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto aluminum foil lined cookie sheets.
Place in oven and immediately turn off heat.
Do not open oven door for at least 8 hours.
Carefully remove from aluminum foil.
Yield: about 3 dozen.

title: pink lemonade ice cream loaf
directions: Slice cake horizontally into 3 layers; set aside. Combine ice cream and lemonade concentrate; swirl gently. Spread half of ice cream mixture on bottom layer of cake. Top with second ice cream mixture. Place the third layer over ice cream and freeze loaf for 30 minutes. Beat whipping cream until foamy; gradually add powdered sugar, beating until soft peaks form. Frost top and sides of cake with whipped cream. Freeze until firm. Slice cake and serve with additional strawberries.

title: pepper steak
directions: Roast should be frozen firm.
Slice into small bite-size pieces and brown.
Drain.
Slice onions into small pieces and place in water with 1 tablespoon lemon juice and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Slice green peppers and place in water.
(Keeps fresh.)
After browning meat, take out and cook onions and green peppers.
Simmer with lid. Mix 1 tablespoon flour with 1/2 cup hot water.
Add to mixture to thicken along with soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Add vegetables (takes about 5 to 8 minutes to cook).
After vegetables cook, place meat back in pan and simmer with lid on for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: peach delight cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour two round cake pans, 8 or 9-inch.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add rest.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: irish oatcakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix in oatmeal.
Sift flour and salt, adding to creamed mixture alternately with baking soda dissolved in the half cup of hot water.
Roll thin, cut and bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Remove and mince mushroom stems. Put caps in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch

baking dish and set aside. Heat oil in a medium nonstick skillet over medium heat; swirl to coat bottom. Saute mushroom stems and garlic for 5 minutes. Stir in bell peppers and cook until soft, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add green onion and cook for 2 minutes. Remove pan from heat and stir in remaining ingredients. Stuff filling into mushroom caps.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes. Serves 6 (3 mushrooms per serving).

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan; in it combine sugar and milk.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture boils.
Cook to soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat; quickly add Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter, chocolate chips and vanilla. Blend.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Score; cut when cool.

title: camper stew
directions: Put ground meat to cook in a large pot until brown. When the meat turns brown, drain the grease and return the meat to the pot. On a medium fire, mix in your tomatoes, water, coffee powder, chili mix, pork and beans and seasoning to taste. Stir real good and bring to a boil. Once the mixture is brought to a boil, lower the fire and let simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: "fluffy" pineapple pie
directions: Combine pineapple and pudding mix until thick; fold in whipped topping. Spoon into crust and refrigerate before serving.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage and Bisquick, mixing thoroughly.
Add cheese and mix well.
Roll into walnut-size balls and place on cookie sheet for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
These freeze well.
Yield: About 125 walnut-sized balls.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken; cool.
Cube and set aside.
Save 1 cup chicken stock. Chop broccoli. Cover with water and bring to a boil for 5 minutes. Drain and let stand in colander.
Combine celery, onion, cream of chicken soup, margarine and chicken stock. Simmer until celery and onion are tender.
Add cheese; mix until melted.
In a large casserole, place 1 cup rice, then chicken, then broccoli. Pour cheese mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Pam spray 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine eggs and milk in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Butter both sides of all bread slices.
Dip each in egg mixture.
Place one layer of bread in bottom of baking dish.
Cover with 1 cup of cheese, all of the ham, 1/2 of the sugar/cinnamon, then the remaining bread, then the remaining cheese.
Pour remaining egg mixture over cheese.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Sprinkle remaining sugar and spice over.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: grandma rose's peach cobbler
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Pour can of peaches
and juice into pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over peaches. Dot margarine over dry cake mix.
Bake for 45 minutes until golden brown.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: double sherbet punch
directions: Mix orange juice and lemonade as directed on package.
Combine juices.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Put in bowl; add sherbet and ginger ale.

title: apple pie in a bag
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash and peel apples, then quarter them.
Cut each apple quarter into 4 pieces, making 7 cups of large chunks.
In large bowl, toss apple chunks with a mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons flour; add nutmeg or cinnamon. Toss until apple chunks are fully coated.
Fill pie shell, piling them high in middle of pie.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Thoroughly mix 1/2 cup each of sugar and flour and butter into a paste.
Spread over top of apple chunks.
Place in large brown paper bag, closing open end.
Bake for 1 hour or until browned. Let cool in bag for 5 minutes before removing.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon; set aside.
Cook onion (and celery and pepper) in bacon fat.
Combine corn, milk and soup.
Stir in all the vegetables.
Heat, but do not boil.
Before serving, stir in bacon and top with margarine and shredded cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add oil and egg.
Let rest a few minutes.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Put in oiled bowl.
Let rise until double.
Shape in rolls; place in greased pan.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mother gave me the recipe which is a little different, but which will make a little more pie crust.
It also keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add all ingredients except sour cream to jello. Chill half of this mixture while the other half remains at room temperature.
When first half of the mixture is firm, spread sour cream.
Add remaining mixture and chill.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Drain and quarter cherries.
Set aside.
Melt chocolate chips with 14 ounces almond bark in large saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour into greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries; sprinkle with coconut.

title: golden rice
directions: Saute noodles in butter until golden brown.
Add water and bring to boil.
Add rice and salt.
Lower heat and cover.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes until rice is tender.

title: gift-wrapped green beans(a dinner party dish; no last minute preparation)
directions: String beans.
Trim tips so beans are uniform in length. Bring 2 inches of water to boil in a large saucepan.
Add beans and salt.
Simmer uncovered 5 minutes.
Cover and continue to simmer 10 to 12 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Remove from heat and plunge in cold water to stop cooking; drain.
Divide beans into 6 bunches.
Wrap each bunch with bacon and secure with toothpick. Place in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour dressing over beans and marinate a minimum of 1 hour in refrigerator.
Bake with marinade 30 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: shortbread
directions: Knead the flour into softened butter; then knead the sugar into flour mixture.
Press firmly into a well greased 8 inch square pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325° or until delicate brown.
Cut into squares while still hot; return to oven to dry edges.
Let cool.

title: old-fashion potato soup
directions: Cut up pork into small cubes, removing all fat.
Cover with water in a large pot.
Bring water to a nice boil; skim top of water.
Add salt and pepper according to taste.
Add onion and celery; cook about 1 hour until meat is done.
Add potatoes, cut into bite size cubes.
Cook until potatoes are done, not mushy. Mix in a medium bowl 2 cups of flour and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Beat in eggs and 1/2 cup of milk.
Add milk if too dry.
Drop into soup at full boil.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes.
Turn soup off.
Add milk to taste.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cover potatoes, onions and celery with water and boil together until tender.
Add broccoli, then add Carnation milk, bouillon cubes, oleo, cornstarch, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook and add Colby cheese when soup is done.
Serve with corn bread muffins or crackers.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge pork chops in flour mixture.

title: lucille's glazed carrots(serves 8)
directions: Mix frozen orange juice, sugar and water and cook down until clear and the drips are sticky.
Add crunchy cooked sliced carrots and chopped parsley.

title: irish candy
directions: Beat egg whites, salt, cream of tartar and vanilla until peaks form.
Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold in chocolate and nuts.
Drop onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: caramel fudge
directions: Cook in a large iron skillet.
Combine first 4 ingredients; stir constantly.
Add vanilla and salt.
Pour into mixing bowl and stir until cool.
Add nuts.
Spread on wax paper.

title: aunt fanny's baked squash
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain thoroughly, then mash.
Melt butter.
Pour mixture in baking dish, then spread melted butter over top and sprinkle with cracker meal or bread crumbs.
