Bake in 370° oven for 1 hour.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix all other ingredients except crabmeat.
Add cream cheese and mix thoroughly. Add crabmeat and mix and mix again.
Put into mold and refrigerate several hours.
Remove carefully onto bed of lettuce.
Serve with crackers.

title: greens and beans
directions: Wash and tear escarole.
Slowly saute garlic cloves in oil. Add red pepper, water and beans and cook.
Add greens that have already been steamed in separate pan.
Salt and pepper to taste. May top with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: southern squash and shrimp casserole
directions: Scrub squash and cut off ends.
Slice or cut into small cubes. Place in pan depth of 1 inch.
Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes or until just tender.
Drain well and mash.
Heat butter, add onion and saute until soft and golden, not brown.
Stir squash, onions, shrimp, salt, pepper and beaten eggs.
Blend thoroughly and turn into well-greased 1-quart casserole.
Dust with bread crumbs.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until puffed and nicely brown.
Serves 6.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Layer ingredients like you would lasagne and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: orange mandarin salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add orange juice, pineapple, oranges and bananas.
Cool and let set in refrigerator.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Melt oleo and semi-sweet chocolate in microwave on Low.
Add sugar and eggs; stir.
Fold in flour and pecans; add vanilla. Stir well.
Bake in greased 9 x 6-inch pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 300°.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry ground beef; drain and add taco seasoning and chili beans. Cool.
Break lettuce in bowl and add tomatoes, onion and cheese. Add meat mixture last and just before serving, add Fritos, so they don't soften.

title: ham and cheese party rolls
directions: Slice rolls lengthwise.
Do not separate rolls.
Mix together margarine, mustard, worcestershire sauce, poppy seed, and onion. Spread mixture on both sides of bread.
Layer one side with ham and cheese.
Cover with other 1/2 slice of bread.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: spaghetti with clam and shrimp sauce
directions: Saute onion, garlic and parsley in 5 tablespoons butter for 3 minutes.
Drain clams, reserving juice.
Add enough water to measure 1 cup of liquid.

title: cream puffs
directions: Boil together hot water and butter.
While boiling, stir in sifted flour.
Remove from heat and stir to a smooth paste.
When cool, add eggs, stirring 5 minutes.
Drop on a greased pan with a small tablespoon and bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: apple bread pudding in a pan
directions: Heat milk to almost a boil. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir and serve warm.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Put everything in blender and blend 5 minutes on low speed. Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: apple crumble
directions: Place apples in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Cream butter and brown sugar.
Blend in flour, salt and rolled oats.
Sprinkle on apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Tasty hot or cold.

title: pork parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Trim excess fat off pork chops.
Coat with Shake 'n Bake.
Mix and arrange in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Drain off excess fat.

title: reduced calorie strawberry cream parfaits
directions: In bowl, combine sliced berries with whipped topping, folding topping into berries.
Set aside.
In blender combine milk, yogurt, and extract.
Add pudding mix and process on high speed until combined.
Working quickly, spoon 1/8 of pudding mixture into 4 parfait glasses, top each portion of pudding with 1/4 of the berry mixture, 1/2 teaspoon syrup and 1/4 of the remaining pudding mixture.
Garnish each parfait with reserved berry.
Cover and chill until serving.
Makes 4 servings, 125 calories each.

title: mini quiches
directions: Grease 2 dozen (1 3/4-inch) muffin pans.
Separate each dinner roll in half.
Press into muffin pans to make shell.
Place 1 shrimp in each shell.
Combine egg, cream, brandy, salt and pepper.
Divide evenly among shells, using about 2 teaspoons for each.
Slice the cheese into 24 small triangles.
Place one on top of each appetizer.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Wrap in foil and freeze.
To serve, place on baking sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 24.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Cool to room temperature.
Add lemon juice.

title: toasted marshmallow cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Place potatoes, onion and bouillon cubes in a large pot.
Add enough water to cover.
Cook until tender.
Add milk, cheese, salt, pepper and parsley.
Simmer for at least 20 minutes.

title: bohemian crescents
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Chill dough overnight.
Roll thin.
Cut into squares.
Fill with any filling desired.

title: two caramel pies
directions: Separate eggs.
Brown 1 cup sugar over low heat, stirring often to keep from burning.
Add lump of butter and 2 or 3 tablespoons water.
Stir until all dissolved.
Heat milk.
Add beaten egg yolks, flour, salt and the other cup of sugar to warm milk.
Add the milk and egg mixture into the browned sugar. Continue to stir over low heat until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into pie shells.
Let cool while beating the egg whites into a stiff meringue.
(Add sugar to taste to egg whites.)
Top pies with meringue and brown in oven until golden.

title: punch
directions: Add pineapple juice to water in large jar.
On the stove in boiler, put 1 quart water and sugar; bring to a boil.
When it starts to boil, add Kool-Aid (I prefer lemonade flavor).

title: pizza
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
warm
water.
Stir
in
remaining ingredients.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Allow dough to rest 10 minutes.
Turn
dough
onto
greased pizza pan.
Place in a warm place to rise for one hour.
Sprinkle dough with Parmesan cheese, then
of a jar of spaghetti sauce or prepare your own. Sprinkle
with
Mozzarella
cheese
and
your
favorite topping. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, remove and add a little more Mozzarella cheese.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Brown ground beef and drain.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle more cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients (except sugar).
In another bowl, mix sugar and oil.
Alternate adding other dry ingredients and eggs to oil and sugar mixture.
Add carrots and nuts to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a Bundt pan.

title: roast chicken
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Unwrap chicken and remove giblets from cavity.
Thoroughly rinse chicken inside and out.
Place bird on roasting pan with shallow sides (no higher than 1-inch) and place in oven.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 400° and bake 15 to 25 minutes more or until the thigh meat registers 160° on a meat thermometer or the juices of thigh run clear when poked with a fork.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 10 to 20 minutes before carving.
Serve with baked potatoes and cooked green beans or salad.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apple liver delight
directions: Mix water, bouillon, onions, celery, soy sauce and pepper. Cook in Teflon frypan until celery is tender.
Set vegetables to one side of the pan and quickly brown liver on both sides.
Core apple; do not peel and cut into slices.
Place apples on top of liver.
Cover pan.
Cook until apple is tender.
Serves 2.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Mix together sugar and shortening; cream.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add flour and milk alternately. Add vanilla and mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 325°.
Bake until real brown.
Let cool and invert pan.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Combine flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda; add to egg mixture.
Stir in rhubarb. Put into 4 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy lemon sauce
directions: Mix well.
Microwave 100% for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir.
Continue until thick.
Cool before serving.
Good on slice of pound cake or gingerbread.

title: picadillo dip
directions: Lightly spray medium nonstick skillet with nonfat cooking spray, and heat over medium heat.
Add turkey, cumin, garlic, onion and cayenne pepper to skillet; cook until no longer pink. Add tomatoes, water, tomato paste and raisins to turkey; cook until mixture starts to boil.
Cover and reduce to low heat; simmer 10 minutes until heated through.
Serve with fat free crackers, pita chips or tortilla chips.
Serves 8.

title: velvet salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in one cup hot water and melt marshmallows in one cup hot water.
Mix together and let cool. Whip cream until stiff.
Mix pineapple, cream cheese, salad dressing and whipped cream.
Add to jello mixture and let set. Then mix raspberry jello with 2 cups hot water.
Chill until syrupy and pour over first jello mixture.
Refrigerate until set. Cut in squares and serve on lettuce with small spoons of salad dressing.

title: catfish stew
directions: Cut up catfish fillets into potatoes and onion mixture.
Add boiled eggs and V-8 vegetable juice.
Serve with saltine crackers and tossed salad.

title: surprise devil's food cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In large bowl, mix sugar, cocoa, baking powder and baking soda. Whisk in buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in beets.
Pour into prepared dish.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack. Cut in pan.
Serve with Chocolate-Buttermilk Sauce (recipe below).

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients and add to oil mixture.
Stir in vanilla and pineapple.
Pour into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan or 12 cup Bundt pan.
Set oven temperature to 300° to 325°.
Bake for 1 hour or until tested done.
Invert pan and let cool about 10 minutes.
Remove cake carefully.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle 10x powdered sugar on cake before serving, if desired.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Melt oleo.
Add
remaining
ingredients
and
mix well. Form into small	balls and place on cookie sheet, then flatten with a fork.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well and chill for 2 hours.
Serve with vegetables.
Use only Hellmann's mayo.

title: french onion soup
directions: Fry onions gently in butter, but not brown.
Stir in flour and let cook a few minutes before adding salt and pepper to taste. Add stock; stir and simmer 15 minutes.
Fry bread in butter; place in ovenproof earthenware tureen or individual soup bowls and pour in hot soup.
The bread will rise to the top.
Sprinkle with a thick layer of the grated cheese.
Place in preheated 375° oven until cheese becomes stringy.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: rock 'n roll peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, 1 stick butter, milk and salt to form crust.
Roll out dough about 1/4-inch thin.
Sprinkle sliced peaches on top of crust.
Hand roll crust into a log.
Slice log vertically into 1 1/2-inch sections.
Stand sections upright in pan.
Mix sugar, water and 1/2 stick butter.
Bring to a boil to make a light syrup.
Pour over peach rolls.
Bake until brown.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco with sugar.
Add one egg at a time and mix well.
Add milk and flavorings.
Mix dry ingredients and add to mixture last.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Cool in pan.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill overnight.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Mix chips and peanut butter together.
Melt in saucepan.
Pour a little less than half the mixture into a chilled jelly roll pan. Set remaining mixture aside and add salted peanuts.
Mix together the evaporated milk, pudding mix and butter.
Bring to boiling and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Blend well.
Add to the first layer carefully. Chill 10 minutes.
Spread remaining chocolate mixture on the top.
Chill.
Cut in small squares.

title: leftover pork
directions: Cook and drain rice.
Make a sauce with next 4 ingredients. Add parsley, onion, sage and half the cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted; add rice and pork and put in shallow baking dish and sprinkle with remaining cheese and some paprika.
Bake in 375° oven about 30 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain fat. Add tomato sauce, chili powder, green chiles and salt.
Layer flour tortilla in bottom of lasagna pan, then layer of cheese, then hamburger and so on.
Top with cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil; bake for 30 minutes.

title: turtle candy
directions: Line baking pans with foil.
Lightly butter foil.
In a heavy saucepan, combine all ingredients except vanilla, nuts and chocolate.
Cook, stirring with wooden spoon over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cook hardball stage (244°).
Remove; stir in vanilla.
Turn into prepared pan; let cool 30 minutes.
Cut into 26 pieces.
Roll into balls; place on buttered cookie sheet.
Make feet and head by pressing 5 pecan halves into each ball.
Melt chocolate.
Spoon 1 teaspoon chocolate over each ball, leaving part of pecans showing.
Refrigerate to allow chocolate to harden.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix all together, folding in crab last.
Chill and serve on crackers.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water until tender (10 minutes).
Drain.
Cool.
Make marinade with remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cool.
Pour over carrots. Cover. Refrigerate overnight.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa 3 times. Mix with buttermilk; add vanilla and red coloring.
Fold in soda and vinegar.
Do not beat.
Makes 2 layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes in greased and floured pans.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid. Combine sugar and flour. Stir in 3 tablespoons liquid. Add cheese and pineapple chunks. Mix well. Put in greased casserole dish.

title: party mix
directions: Melt margarine. Add salts and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix and add other ingredients.
Stir well to coat.
Heat for 1 hour in a 250° oven stirring well every 15 minutes.

title: heart healthy potato soup
directions: Add bouillon mixture with potatoes, celery, onion, parsley flakes and pepper.
Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Then add milk and cheese and simmer until cheese is melted.

title: barbecue roast
directions: Sprinkle generously with onion powder, garlic powder and celery salt.
Pour 1 whole bottle liquid smoke over meat. Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake 3 hours at 300°, covered. Pour Cattleman's barbecue sauce over roast and bake uncovered for 1 hour longer.
Total cooking time is 4 hours at 300°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple, marshmallows, cherries, pecans and dates. Sprinkle pudding mix on top.
(Do not add liquids; use the dry pudding mix).
Add Cool Whip and stir everything together.

title: vegetables and dip
directions: Light sour cream and soup mix can be used to reduce calories.

title: oriental salad
directions: Brown nuts and seeds in a little oil (or toast nuts and seeds).
Cool.
Combine slaw and onions.
Combine dressing. Break up noodles and put on top.
Pour on dressing.
Add seeds and nuts.
Let set 1 to 2 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: grilled catfish
directions: After coals have burned, place fish on grill.
Combine all ingredients for basting sauce and baste frequently as fish cooks. Cook for 20 minutes on one side; turn and cook an additional 15 minutes, basting often.

title: brownies
directions: Cream together everything except flour, nuts and vanilla. After you beat this, add the flour and stir well.
Then add nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cupcake icing
directions: Melt the candy bars in a double boiler.
Add the milk and powdered sugar; stir well.
When cool, spread over cupcakes.

title: sunset punch
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl, stirring well. Stir in mango. Garnish punch with lemon lime slices.
Makes 2 1/4 quarts.

title: easy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.

title: pumpkin apple streusel muffins
directions: Peel and finely chop apples.
In large bowl combine eggs, pumpkin and oil.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients.
Stir until just moistened.
Stir in apples and spoon batter into greased or paper-lined muffin cups, filling 3/4 full.
Sprinkle streusel topping over batter and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in ready made pie crust.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix all of the ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until a knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine in large pot of boiling salt water just until al dente, 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain well.
Return to dry pot.

title: flank steak broil
directions: Simmer all ingredients together, except steak, 10 minutes. Cool to room temperature.
Marinate steak overnight, turning occasionally.
Broil over hot coals (charcoal) about 5 minutes on each side.
Slice very thin across grain and serve.

title: funnel cake
directions: Heat oil to 370° in deep fryer.
Fry 6 to 8 minutes, turning once.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: low-fat alfredo sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients with blender.
Put on high until thoroughly heated.
Pour over cooked fettucini noodles.

title: odessa's tory pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, all at once, beating well, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Blend in flavorings.
Combine dry ingredients; add alternately with buttermilk, beating just until thoroughly combined.
Spread evenly in two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans or 1 greased 10 x 4-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 1 hour and 10 minutes for tube pan or until cake tester inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool in pan(s) or wire rack(s) 10 minutes.
Remove from pan(s); cool completely.

title: granny topsy spears' crackers and noodles
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain and place on a large platter.
Put margarine in large skillet and crumble crackers into skillet.
Cook and stir until medium brown.
Spread over noodles.
Serve warm.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Spread ground beef mixture on the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread mushroom soup, right from the can, then a layer of cheese. Top with Tater Tots and bake for 35 minutes at 350° or until Tater Tots are done.

title: poppy seed coffee cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
If cake mix calls for more water, add it.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add oil and pudding; beat to mix.
Add poppy seed and blend in.
Bake in angel food cake pan for 45 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and invert on bottle until cool.
Remove from pan onto serving plate.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Frosting not needed.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well with a spoon.
Can make ahead of time and refrigerate in Tupperware container.
Best on chicken!

title: velvety white pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco together.
Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour and add to egg mixture with milk.
Add vanilla and salt.
Bake at 325° in a tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.
Grease and flour pan before pouring the batter in.

title: strawberry cream dessert(diabetic)
directions: Trim 3/4-inch from ends of ladyfingers.
Place ends on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Stand rest of ladyfingers around side of pan (cut sides facing in).
Reserve 2 strawberries for garnish. Mash rest of berries.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl at least 2 minutes until dissolved.
Add ice cubes and stir until melted.
Add Cool Whip and mashed berries, stir gently until well blended. Refrigerate 10 minutes until very thick.
Spoon into pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Remove side of pan.
Garnish with reserved berries.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together and then add others.
Pour into crust and bake 350° for 30 minutes.
Chill and serve.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour dressing over it.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Cook coconut, eggs, salt, sugar, dates and butter in skillet, stirring constantly until very thick.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies, nuts and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Let cool until you can handle.
Work into balls the size of half dollars.
Roll in flaked coconut.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients while strawberries are frozen.
Add bananas.
Pour 1/2 mixture in 8 x 8-inch pan until partially set. Cover with 1/2 pint sour cream.
Pour remaining 1/2 on top; place in refrigerator.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: sour cream swiss steak
directions: Pound flour into meat.	Dust with salt, pepper, paprika and mustard.
Heat oil; add butter.
Sear steak on one side.
Turn, add onion, water, soy sauce, brown sugar and sour cream.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: chocolate sour cream cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Bring cocoa, oleo and water to a boil.
Stir into flour mixture.
Mix cream and soda.
Add eggs and add to mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Best when topped with Betty Crocker chocolate sour cream frosting and is kept covered and refrigerated.

title: meat loaf squares
directions: Combine hamburger, onion, bread, mayonnaise, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix together tomato soup and onion soup mix.
Spread half of soup mixture on bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread hamburger and top with soup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring cocoa, milk, sugar, vanilla and oleo to a boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and quick oats. Spoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: "philly" miracle whip wreath
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.

title: barbecue rib sauce
directions: Add all ingredients in saucepan; bring to boil, stirring for 2 minutes.
Pour over any kind of ribs.

title: whoop-n-tail
directions: Drain off syrup from fruit.
Mix with Cool Whip and then add nuts and food coloring.
Kids love this and it's so easy to prepare.
Also good for any type of party or reception.

title: peanut butter drops(sugar-free)
directions: Cream peanut butter, oleo, baking chocolate and vanilla extract together and gradually add sugar replacement, sorbitol and liquid fructose.
Continue beating and add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift flour and baking soda together.
Add to creamed mixture with water; mix well.

title: fresh apple nut cake
directions: Coat nuts and raisins in some of the flour.
Sift flour, spice and salt together.
Beat eggs slightly, add sugar and oil. Mix well.
Add flour, a little at a time, until all is used.
Mix in nuts, raisins, apples, vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into a tube pan and bake at 325° for one hour and 15 minutes.

title: orange juice punch
directions: Freeze 7-Up in ring mold overnight.
Pour orange juice in punch bowl.
Place frozen 7-Up ring in middle of bowl.
Float orange slices inside and outside of ring.
Punch will stay cold 2 to 3 hours.

title: jambalaya
directions: Blend flour and bacon drippings until brown, add all vegetables, seasonings, water and beef juice and crushed tomatoes. Cook well together.
Add ham and shrimp just before serving over rice.
Serves a bunch!!!!!!

title: no bake chocolate cheesecake
directions: In a small microproof bowl, melt chocolate chips on High (Full power) for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until chips are melted and mixture is smooth when stirred; set aside to cool.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese, sugar and butter until smooth on low speed.
Blend in melted chocolate.
Fold in whipped topping until blended; spoon into crust.
Cover; chill until firm.

title: broccoli and velveeta cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Pour 1/2 of melted butter over broccoli.
Add cheese.
Mix remaining butter with crushed crackers.
Pour over broccoli/cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: drop tea cakes
directions: Mix well.
Drop with teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° or until light brown, approximately 10 minutes.
Makes about 200 cookies.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken and celery into small pieces.
Mix sugar, vinegar, eggs and mustard.
Bring to a boil and thicken.
Pour onto chicken and mix.
Add mayonnaise and salt to taste.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all well and refrigerate for at least 24 hours before serving.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Soften the cream cheese with 1 tablespoon of milk.
Add sugar, cranberries, nuts and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into mold and freeze.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Take out chicken and dip tortillas in chicken broth until limp.
Line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with tortillas.
Debone chicken and cut up.
Put over tortillas with green pepper and onion.
Mix soups and tomatoes with chiles.
Pour over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese has melted, about 1 hour.

title: great fruit dip
directions: Mix with beater and chill for 1 hour.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Combine sliced strawberries and 1/4 to 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir gently and chill for 1 to 2 hours.

title: chicken in foil
directions: Cut a piece of heavy-duty foil and place chicken in center. Top with vegetables.
Sprinkle Molly McButter on top of vegetables. Wrap well.
Place on baking sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: date-nut sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine sausage, Bisquick and cheese until thoroughly blended.
Knead in remaining ingredients.
With hands, roll dough into small balls (about 1-inch) and place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 13 minutes.
Cool.
Store in airtight container or freeze.
Yields 6 to 8 dozen.

title: no bake rum balls
directions: In a bowl combine crumbs, the 1 cup confectioners sugar and cocoa.
Add
nuts,
syrup and rum; mix until well blended. With the hands, shape mixture into balls; place on waxed paper covered surface.
Let
stand 1 hour. Roll balls in confectioners sugar to coat.
Store balls in tightly covered container 3 days before serving.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all the ingredients and press out on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° 9 to 10 minutes.
Cut in 3 inch pieces before they cool. Remove to rack to cool before packing in an airtight container.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: kellogg's rice krispie bars
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Press into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon onto a cookie sheet lined with foil.
Cool before serving.

title: pound cake(grandma jennie shull)
directions: Cream together shortening, butter and sugar. Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each one. Add milk alternately with flour. Add salt, flavoring and baking powder. Pour into greased and floured 9-inch tube pan. Put in cold oven. Set on 350° and bake 1 hour or until done.

title: yummy dessert
directions: Mix the oleo, flour and pecans together.
Bake in pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool layer.

title: cobbler
directions: Put fruit on bottom.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Mix together gelatin and hot water.
Stir until dissolved. Add bananas, drained pineapple and cold water.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until jelled.
Combine sugar, flour, egg, butter and pineapple juice.
Cook over low heat; stir well until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in cream cheese.
Mix until cheese is melted.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Cool and then spread on top of congealed salad.

title: stir-fried vegetables
directions: Brown
chicken	breast pieces for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add oil and frozen vegetables.
Saute for 5 minutes.

title: heavenly hamburger
directions: Brown beef in butter.
Add minced garlic, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and sugar.
Simmer covered about 20 minutes.

title: jimmy dean casserole
directions: Crumble sausage into large skillet and cook bread until browned; drain thoroughly.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Pour into 3-quart baking dish and sprinkle with 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt margarine.
Dip biscuits in margarine.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar that has been mixed together.
Place in ungreased pan and bake at 375° until done, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sauerkraut with apples
directions: Drain sauerkraut and set aside.
Saute onion slices in butter in a saucepan.
Meanwhile, quarter and core the apple.
Cut into thin slices.
Add to onion.
Saute 1 or 2 minutes.
Add drained sauerkraut and brown sugar, gently mixing with a wooden spoon. Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes over low heat.
Spoon into a serving bowl.
Serve hot!
Makes 4 servings.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together with a mixer.
Chill and shape into a ball.
Roll ball in chopped pecans.

title: headlight meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oil; mix thoroughly.
Add a little water if mixture seems dry.
Shape into 24 balls and brown slowly in hot oil.

title: cheese dip
directions: Saute onions in 1 tablespoon butter.
Add Velveeta and soup. Melt.
Add chilies and tomatoes while cheese is melting.
Keep warm in crock-pot.
Serve with tortillas or chips.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat egg white and add to mixture.
Put mixture in unbaked crust and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed on box.
Add cream cheese.
(You can stir it in so that it'll dissolve in jello or let it be "chunky".)
So that the other ingredients will be dispersed evenly throughout the salad, add them later after mixture has begun to congeal.

title: butter icing for sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, vanilla extract and milk, adding a few drops of milk to reach desired consistency. Add coloring. Spread over cooled cookies.

title: pureed potato soup
directions: Heat butter.
When hot, add onion and leeks.
Cover and cook 8 minutes over low heat.
Add potatoes and spices.
Season generously.
Mix and continue cooking, covered, for 3 minutes. Add chicken stock and season well.
Bring to a boil.
Cook soup, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes over low heat.
Puree soup in food processor or food mill.
Stir in cream and serve.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half; remove stem and seeds and place in baking dish.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Mix together the cheeses.
Add milk, flour and pepper to eggs. Grease a rather large, flat pan well; grease sides, also.
Spread half of the cleaned chilies in bottom of pan.
Cover with half of the cheeses.
Add the other half of the chilies and top with the other half of the cheeses.
Pour the beaten egg mixture over all. Best to let this rest for awhile before baking, even overnight. Bake about 3/4 hour in a 350° oven or until set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup.
Spread Cheez Whiz on top of soup.
Put cracker crumbs on top of Cheez Whiz.
Cut up butter or margarine. Place over top of mixture.
Cook, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes, then uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, garlic and seasonings.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
In a 12 x 8-inch baking dish, layer half of noodles, meat sauce, Mozzarella, Velveeta and Parmesan.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: yummers
directions: Grate cheese.
Add butter to cheese and mix.
Add flour and Rice Krispies; mix well.
Form into little balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Yummy!
Serves 6 to 8.
We triple this recipe!

title: grilled chicken and nectarine salad
directions: Place chicken in shallow dish.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon lime juice, 1 tablespoon thyme and 1 teaspoon olive oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Turn to coat.
Cover and refrigerate from 1 to 4 hours.

title: lentil and bean stew
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven, combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 45 to 55 minutes or until vegetables and lentils are tender.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss broccoli, onion and raisins.
Mix salad dressing with sugar and toss with salad.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle over salad just before serving.

title: apricot glazed brussels sprouts
directions: In saucepan, cook Brussels sprouts according to package directions.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake at 350° to 400° (depending on your oven) for 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: cheddar cheese nut ball
directions: Bring all ingredients to room temperature and combine.
Chill. Form into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: broccoli  casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy pepperoni rolls
directions: Thaw 2 loaves of dough (to make 1 dozen) until completely soft (do not let them rise yet).
Cut each loaf into 6 to 8 equal slices.
Flatten out each slice with your hand into a circle.
Cut up about 3 slices or so of pepperoni into small pieces and place onto circle of dough all over.
Roll up dough like jelly roll and place on greased cookie sheet.
Tuck edges of ends under roll. Slightly grease top of roll with shortening.
Cover with towel and let rise a few hours.
When completely raised, put pan of rolls in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven and slightly butter top of rolls if desired.
Remove from pan to cool.

title: american cheese soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water; add carrot cubes and celery.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Cook onion in butter in heavy kettle.
When onion is tender, but not brown, blend in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until thickened. Add bouillon-vegetable mixture, stirring occasionally.
Season with salt and pepper.
Heat but do not boil.
Add cheese and stir to melt.
Serve piping hot, topped with a spoonful of crunchy, thinly cut celery and sprinkle of parsley.
Yields 4 servings.

title: canned apple slices
directions: In nonmetal container sprinkle sugar over apples slices in layers.
Cover with cloth and let set overnight.
Pack divide juice in container between jars.
Do not add any other liquid.
Water bath for 15 minutes.

title: baklava
directions: Boil 10 minutes and cool.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break cake into bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients, except strawberries and glaze.
Put a layer of cake, then a layer of mixed ingredients, layer of strawberries and glaze.
It makes 2 layers.

title: cheddar-beer cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut a 9-inch round of parchment paper and place in the bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan. Line the bottom of the pan with the bottom of the crust. Reserve the rest of the crust. Bake for 10 minutes. Remove the pan from the oven and cool the crust. Press the remaining dough around the sides of the pan and attach it to the bottom crust.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine flour, oats and baking soda; set aside.
In a small mixer bowl, beat margarine and peanut butter with an electric mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add brown sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add egg, 2 tablespoons milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients, beating at low speed until combined. Spread in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with peanuts. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until done.
Cool.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat to boiling point; serve.

title: grandma's applesauce cake
directions: Mix together oleo, milk and water.
Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched in center.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts.
Mix in bowl all ingredients.
Pour in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with a basket of small slices of sourdough bread.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir in remaining ingredients and chill for 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls, then flatten them on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper.
In covered cooking dish, mix rice, soups, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and mushrooms; mix well, then add browned beef, onion and pepper mixture.
Mix again. Add hot water to make sure mixture cooks moist (about 1 cup). Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve hot.
Can be frozen for storage before cooking.

title: christmas salad
directions: Soak first three ingredients overnight.
Drain, then combine with the rest of the ingredients.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate oat chip cookies with chocolate chips
directions: In small bowl combine flour, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
In large bowl cream butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; beat well.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts; mix well.
Chill some.

title: grandma's homemade ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into ice cream maker.
Add milk until container is full.
Makes 5 quarts of liquid, including milk.
If ice cream maker is smaller than 5 quarts, be sure to decrease all ingredients proportionally (yes, even the rum).

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into strips.
Brown in butter with salt and pepper. Add mushrooms and juice, onion and soups.
Cook gently until meat is tender.
When serving (over noodles), bring to boil; add small carton sour cream and return to heat to serve.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar together; set aside. Fix Dream Whip according to directions on box.
Fold the above together.
Press graham cracker crumbs for crust (according to directions on box).
Pour Dream Whip with cream cheese on top of crust.
Then top with blueberries.
Chill overnight.

title: popcorn balls
directions: In a heavy 5-quart Dutch oven over low heat, stir marshmallows and butter until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Add popped corn and stir until well coated.
With buttered hands, quickly shape into 3-inch balls using about 1 cup of mixture for each ball.
If mix begins to cool, heat pan slightly and stir popped corn mix.
Wrap each ball in plastic wrap.

title: jazzercize punch
directions: Blend in blender all of the ingredients except the 7-Up. Freeze in a mold.
Before serving, thaw halfway and add 7-Up or ginger ale.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Use fresh or uncooked frozen shrimp for this dish.
Heat oil; cook onion, garlic, green pepper and celery slowly for about 5 minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce and water; simmer for about 10 minutes.
Add shrimp; cook until shrimp are pink, about 3 minutes. Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.
